review_headline: Show your support, get out and VOTE! #Walker2016
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:18e1633fb034b12fe8e76bc268ea3172]] I am so pumped for the [[ASIN:B013EX3XD0 2016 presidential campaign]]! Aren't you? The drama is on a whole new level! I have my favorites, and I am sure you do too, but I'm kinda curious about this [[ASIN:B013EX1I8M Walker]] guy.

Scott Kevin Walker is the 45th Governor of Wisconsin He's obviously doing a good job because he's been doing it since 2011. The reason we are gonna talk about him today though is because he is a candidate for the [[ASIN:B00WYA8FVU Republican Party]]'s nomination to the 2016 presidential election.

I received some Walker swag this week so I'll try to be nice going forward. It didn't come from the Walker camp, but from a veteran owned company AW Fashions. They hooked me up in return for telling everyone what I honestly thought of their products. I honestly think they make the most [[ASIN:B011802SS2 comfortable T-shirts]] on earth!

Wisconsin governor and [[ASIN:B00I8GG566 vanilla pudding]] made flesh Scott Walker is going through a bit of a slump in his campaign for the White House. After a debate performance that had all the pop and energy of a funeral, Walker's poll numbers took a dive, both nationally and in Iowa. Then he alienated fiscal conservatives and [[ASIN:B011802SS2 Tea Party]] types by signing off on a new taxpayer-funded stadium for the Milwaukee Bucks. Walker needs something new and exciting to drag him out of this rut, so this week he's going to try to recapture the affections of his party by taking direct aim at the one thing conservatives and Republicans hate most: [[ASIN:0893348627 Obamacare]].

While Mr. Walker will not be receiving a vote from me, this high quality comfortable shirt that AW Fashions sent me sure will!

These tee shirts would be wonderful for a Tea Party rally, Republican GOP Presidential debate, a [[ASIN:B00WRBQODC Glenn Beck]] event, or just to show your support around town! The shirts are lite weight, super soft, and thin. The shirt is made of sweat wicking material making it perfect for crossfit, hiking, running, the gym, cycling, surfing, and beach! They are the optimal athletic apparel for both men and women.

Support America and [[ASIN:B00A45G6EA Don't Tread on Me]] with Constitution Conservative Patriotic shirts!

product_title: Women's Fashion Below the Knee Offic Pencil Skirt USA (Plus Sizes)
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:a59cf0c0ccbe43617e457e40ba24da1f]]This skirt comes in a super cute reusable bag, which I love because anything that helps save the planet is a yes for me. It's also HUGE so it's going to be added to my shopping reusable bags. :)

Ok. Skirt.
The red is RED. It's not a bland kind of red, but more like a vibrant red which is beautiful. The fabric is 75% Polyester, and 25% rayon. Which means it's going to hug you in all the right places.

The waist band is elastic but a thicker band than other skirts that I've had. I actually prefer the longer waist bands that are elastic because it helps them to stay in place. product_title: Tulle Shirts and Blouses for Women
review_headline: Perfect fit, cute...but does snag easily
review_body:
This is a lovely, silky, flattering shirt! I have to disagree with another reviewer about it not fitting based on cup size alone. Cup size is not the issue, overall chest circumference is...it's not fair to fault the shirt if you didn't measure that beforehand. I followed the sizing chart exactly, purchased a small, and it fit perfectly (and, for the record, I'm a C/D cup!) It's flattering without being tight, and it's appropriate to wear to work.

Here's why I docked it a star:
1) There is a seam that goes around the shirt, under the chest (where you'd expect something like that on an empire/babydoll waist top). It's a bit distracting given the slight shininess of the material, yet it was not really visible in the model photo. I didn't expect it and I feel like it doesn't really belong, but it's a very minor quibble...it still looks lovely overall.
2) A bigger complaint for me is that the material is VERY prone to snagging. As a cat owner, this always matters but is not something I would normally dock a product for. However, the material's sensitivity to snagging is so severe that it snagged on a hangnail on my finger, and then on a nail itself that was only slight rough (not torn) within a short period of time after putting on the shirt. I'm concerned about how long this will hold up as a result.

If this item was more expensive, I might have docked it more points for the snagging issue, but it is a fantastic price for a cute shirt. I purchased this shirt at a slight discount for my honest and unbiased review, which this absolutely is. Hope it helps!

review_body:

This dress fix as expected as far as size goes - I know some people mentioned that it was off, but for me it was right on in the XL size. The reason I took away a star was first, the button closure is super hard to work - it took me a good 2 minutes to get it opened to put on, and it seems like I might have to replace the string holding the button to the dress. Secondly, the armpit areas gape in front and really could use a bust dart, at least in my case. Aside from those issues, I absolutely LOVE this dress. product_title: Look Hot but Stay Cool with These Stunning Dresses Perfect for Summer
review_headline: Cute and comfy dress, as long as you triple check the sizing
review_body:
This dress is definitely cute and flowy and perfect for summer. The material is lightweight, but it has a liner so I am not worried about it at all. I like the fact that you can remove the halter straps by unbuttoning them. The dress also comes with an extra button, which is always welcome in my house. I did intend on this dress to be for me, and thought I checked the sizing chart throughly, but the image of the chart for the flower dress was missing key bust measurements that I discovered (later of course) the other styles had. While the dress technically fit, it was not flattering at all. I ended up giving it to my much smaller 13 yr old daughter. It is baggy on her, but we solved that by tying the halter top tighter and using a plain white scarf to cinch the waist and it looks nice on her. It is near the end of the summer here, so I'm sure it will be a good fit for her next year.

That being said, I based my rating on the dress itself, not my sizing issues. Take the time to measure yourself and use the company's sizing chart, and you should be fine. I did recieve this summer dress at a discount in exchange for an unbiased and honest review, which I have given here. As long as you size up and make sure to check the chart, this is a great dress.

product_title: Look Hot but Stay Cool with These Stunning Dresses Perfect for Summer
review_headline: Cute dress, but check their size chart image, don't go by Amazon's!
review_body:
I chose the black dress with the bright pink flowers with a low v-neck. The dress is very cute in person, nice fabric, not too short if you're petite (I'm 5'3") however please note that the Amazon-provided "size chart" listed next to the size drop-down menu is NOT used for this dress. They have a third image with a size chart which shows an XL as an 8-10. This does not come close to American standards for sizing. Normally a large would be a 10-12 or 12-14. I normally wear a large dress and a size 14 pants, so I made the mistake of looking at the Amazon size chart and ordering a large. According to their chart, my 38DD chest might not even fit in their XL. I was able to get the dress on but the bodice was tight and didn't sit correctly. They need to remove the Amazon size chart from their listing so people don't make the same mistake as I did.

I contacted the seller for a return/exchange and they were accommodating and friendly, however when I offered to try this dress in an XL, I was told they don't have that size in this dress though Amazon shows they do. I purchased this item at a discount in exchange for an honest, unbiased review.

product_title: Clover Men's Aluminum Wallet
review_body:
A nice everyday carry item. Originally, I purchased to consolidate some of the items I carry with me.

Pros:
It holds your keys, credit cards, ID, and money. The keys don't flop around and are held solidly in place. I was able to add a USB key which fits nicely. Great for the price, there are comparable wallets that are much more expensive. Quality is pretty good.

Cons:
A bit heavy. Clunky to carry in your back pocket. The jagged edges tend to jab you in the butt, which is fine once you start developing a callous. The online video instruction didn't cover what to do with the extra washers. Some were bent and some were plastic.

If this could be a little bit smaller or lighter I would give it more stars. I think based on the design, materials, and the niche market that this appeals to it is hard to come up with a decent product. This does come close to being great though. My biggest disappointment was I expected it to take up less space than conventional wallet and keys, which it doesn't (depending on how fat your wallet is). It simply organizes them better for you than a conventional wallet. A simple TGT wallet and KeySmart key ring comes pretty close as an alternative.

In spite of what it sounds like, I would certainly buy this again. If they come out with a refined version, I would probably buy that too.

product_title: Clover Men's Aluminum Wallet
review_body: Great product.......Already put to use in my daily life!

product_title: Clover Men's Aluminum Wallet
review_headline: If your gonna carry something everyday, you must absolutely LOVE IT!
review_body: First of all, I hardly ever leave reviews online. But I felt like I should definitely share my thoughts regarding this wallet. Its a phenomenal design for a wallet. I have had a leather wallet ever since i can remember, and after 2 days of using this I threw away my leather one. I ordered the Silver one and it looks amazing.  The clear anodized finish is absolutely beautiful. Few times when I have taken it out to pay for something at store , people have asked me first what it is, and where I got it.  It's definitely unique in its look.  Furthermore The wallet offers RFID protection, I have 4 banks cards and 3 of them recently sent me new cards with rf chip in them. I had no idea what that was until i came across this wallet and did some online research. Most banks and credit cards switching over to this new style of cards which supposed to be more secure than standard old magnetic strip cards. The down side of the new cards is that your card data can be skimmed by thieves wirelessly. I'm might be more paranoid than an average user but I think wallet with RFID protection like this one is a must for the future.  I currently carry 4 cards , driver license, and  work id with few dollar bills. I like that I only have to fold my bills in half to make them fit. I initially thought it would not be that comfortable in my pocket since its aluminum frame, but I was surprised of how comfortable it actually is. I commute approx. 3 hrs daily for work and its always in my front pocket. I sometimes even forget its there. I would however like to say that it may take couple of days to get used to the form-factor for using it to open doors. My main house door has an old lock which requires quite of bit effort to open (I been meaning to use WD-40 for months but never did). Since I started using this wallet with keys I have noticed that it requires considerably less effort to open it.  I give  the wallet 5-STARS, I would definitely recommend it to people. I assure you that you will ditch your leather wallet.

product_title: Clover Men's Aluminum Wallet
review_headline: Interesting concept with a lot of room for customization.
review_body: This takes some getting used to because it's so different. There is a strong elastic band to hold your credit cards and a few stacked bills. The other side has four pins that allow for four keys to be held. The clip has to be taken apart so the keys can be put in place but they have to be standard keys. I have a built-in key fob for my car so I can't say whether this feature is useful. I wish the Clover people would put out accessories as there is no end to what they can add. They could easily make swing out items such as a bottle opener, a carabiner type clamp to hang this from your belt loop, a flat LED flashlight to use at night. I could go on for hours. I haven't seen anything like that at their website yet. It will not replace your bloated wallet because it holds fewer items. This is for those who are sick of a fat wallet and are forcing themselves to go smaller to break that habit. It's very sturdy and VERY well made. The Clover company did not skimp anywhere. I dropped this on concrete and I can't find any spot where it dented. I do wish the edges were rounded off as you feel the corners if you have pants with very thin pocket liners. This is an uber-high quality item and when you hold it, you know it'll probably outlast you so you can hang on to it and give it to your kids when they grow up. I see myself hanging on to this for life!

product_title: Clover Men's Aluminum Wallet
review_body: This is a great wallet, it holds my keys very snug and all of the cards I need. I would definitely recommend this to anyone looking for a nice wallet that also holds keys. It is a little large but thats because of the keys. It's a good trade off, the extra size to hold the keys.

product_title: Clover Men's Aluminum Wallet
review_body: Allows me to hold a lot more cash and cards than my previous leather wallet for half the width. I also enjoy the ability to hold several keys, so now I don't have to worry about my keys and wallet being in a separate place. What I enjoy the most about this wallet is that it is made of a sturdy aluminum. I would by another one for my friends and family.

product_title: Clover Men's Aluminum Wallet
review_body: If you don't have a thick car key, this wallet will garner a five star rating from you. Having such a key, I used the two-holed bicycle-chain-link-type spacer that comes in the little hardware packet. When installed like a key, but with the second hole outside the Clover's body, you can clip an external key ring to the wallet. I tried it: it was too bulky in my pocket, and the wallet hung off the car key in the ignition switch. I now carry my car keys and house key on a separate key ring like before, except the other keys are in the Clover. I keep an extra house key in the Clover too. One could carry a valet key for the car in case you lock your keys in the car.  So why didn't I give the Clover just four stars? After assembling and reassembling the wallet several times, I lost track of the bag of hardware. All it took was one email and a replacement came in the mail. Extra stars for extraordinary customer service.  The nylock (nylon lock) screws and wavy washers allow the tension to be adjusted "just so" for each key, so each key has exactly the same tension and feel when rotated in and out of the body. Clever Clover.

product_title: Clover Men's Aluminum Wallet
review_headline: It’s a niche wallet if there ever was one
review_body: I came across this wallet after the Kickstarter and preordered it in, I believe, June of 2015. I had about 30-40 bucks I wanted to spend on a new wallet. I had been, and still am, using a TGT Wallet I bought last year. What made me settle on the Clover over all the other styles of wallets out today was its all metal design and its key integration. What has made me stop using the clover has been its all metal design and key integration. '  The metal is rough and well metal lol. Many of the edges are rounded but at the end of the day it is a big metal block as a wallet. Holding it in my hand is a little uncomfortable because its about an inch or so longer than a normal credit card and wider and thicker. You cannot but this in your back pocket. It is strictly a hold/carry or front pocket wallet. For me it’s a no go because I usually walk out of the house with three things. My wallet, my phone, and my car keys. I CANNOT hold my phone and this wallet in the same hand. One because it’s too big and two because it will of course scratch the hell out of it. I know its metal but for some reason in my head I thought i could carry it like my current wallet. I was mistaken.  The other issue is the key integration. Like i said previously I carry my keys, phone and wallet when I leave the house. And while using the clover I continue to carry three separate items. I thought it would reduce that number to two initially. But it just can’t. My car key is too thick to put on the wallet. At the same time though I added my 3 house keys to the wallet and it just isn’t practical. On the first day when my sister needed to use my car I told her to remember her house keys because mine were now on my wallet. Problem: I can’t readily share my keys with anyone because I would need to take a hex screw to the thing.  It’s just not practical for me.  Lastly is the card holder part of the wallet. The most integral and necessary part of any wallet. Well the only positive I have is that those cards ain’t moving. The strap Clover uses on this thing is top notch. Strong, gives a little when needed and keeps everything in place. The negative: it can comfortably only hold about 5 cards. There is a lip underneath the card that is short, so after the fourth card anything else can be pushed out from the top. There is little chance of this considering how strong the strap is but I noticed it. Also due to the strength of the strap getting a particular card out is a bit of a challenge. I can’t sort of shuffle through my cards like the TGT and because the other side of the wallet is dedicated to the keys i can’t turn my identification cards around in the back in order to have faster access to them. So I end up standing at the register trying to find one of my three debit cards and because the strap is Hercules strong I have to push all five of my cards up and out just to retrieve the correct one. It’s a hassle.  Look I like the idea of this wallet. That’s why I threw down 30 bucks to get it and then waited a month to have it. It’s a niche wallet if there ever was one. It likely won’t reduce the amount of items you carry by acting as a wallet and key ring, it isn’t easier to handle, and it isnt smaller than other wallets. I think this would be ideal for a high schooler or a single person living alone. But for me I’ve gone back to my TGT Wallet. I will more than likely try out the X-Wallet or end up just buying another TGT. But for the Clover Wallet it will end up as a gift or collecting dust in my closet.  Update: Yes I am aware of the piece that comes in the pack allowing you to attach your key ring to the wallet. The problem with that is that I dont want my wallet dangling from my wallet or vice versa. So still no bueno.  (ps Im not trying to troll with the TGT card in the pics. Its just the only thing that was the size of a credit card around that didn't have personal info on it.)

review_body: Absolutely love this wallet, it was a tad strange to get used to but now 100% comfortable

product_title: Clover Men's Aluminum Wallet
review_body:
Overall opinion: Great wallet, sturdy, well made. The elastic is sturdy, the wallet is strong. Definitely glad I purchased it.

Tips for buyers:
-- keep in mind this is meant to keep "everything" in one place, meaning it will not fit your ENTIRE wallet. Currently I have seven bills folded in half and four cards. I might be able to keep another card if I shoved them all in. I'd say maybe seven cards without bills would fit.
-- In women's jeans, since the wallet is metal, it doesn't fit as comfortably as a flexible wallet. It sticks out when you sit, and I didn't want holes in my pockets, so I opted to keep it in my bag. I could keep it in the front pocket without having the "sticking out" problem, but it's not completely comfortable. Depends on the person, it's SLIGHTLY larger than a standard wallet, and it doesn't bend, so just keep that in mind. It is also not completely flush on the one side, so it has to be put in your pocket the one way or else it will get caught on the pocket when you try to put it in.

When I went to use the keys today, they actually ended up getting really loose and swinging around. I had to re-tighten the screws. Not sure if they weren't tight enough or if that just happens after use. I didn't want to tighten it too much, because that makes it difficult to swing the keys out to use. I tightened the screws a little more than before, so I will have to see if it happens again. If it does, that will be a major negative to this. I'll have to carry around the tool just in case it happens.

I opted not to keep my car key on it because it's a little heaver than I'd like, and it makes it a little bulky, but I do like how the extension gives me the option for bigger keys. I might use it in the future for keys, or even non-key things.

The loosened screws is the only thing that worries me about the wallet. I knew going in it might not work for pockets as well as a regular wallet.

product_title: Clover Men's Aluminum Wallet
review_body: I purchased this wallet based on a  brief TV segment with the creators on Good Day Sacramento.  The closest thing I have found to this wallet retails for over $100 (liquid essentials wallet or something like that). Backing this product through kickstarter at less than $30 was well worth it.  Pros:  This wallet appears to be very well constructed. It was packaged well, and easy to put together. As long as you do not over tighten the screws, the keys are very easy to move.  The elastic is pretty heavy duty. My cards don't slide even when placing my id and 2 other card with nothing else in the open slot.  Cons: With only a few days use, I don't have too many negative comments to post in my review.  If I had a complaint, it would be regarding the space allotted for cards/cash.  After placing my Costco, Sams, id card, 2 credit cards, and a couple of folded bills, I am maxing out the space big time. Carrying all those cards defeats the purpose of a minimalist wallet, so I guess its not really a con, just a reminder that I have to adjust/minimize what I carry with me on a daily basis.  Comfort As A Wallet:  It is no more uncomfortable than having an iPhone in your back pocket.  I drive for a living, and I have to pull out my id 5-10 times a day at various gates and checkpoints.  I have yet to have a card slip out. I hardly notice it in my pocket while driving.  I hardly notice its there.  Would I Recommend This Product?  100% yes.  I already sent pics to my brother and my wife's brothers. Great guy gadget/wallet. I would give it 5 stars but for the lack of space in the card area. I think this is easily 4.5 out of 5 stars.

product_title: Adorable Dresses for Women for a Casual Yet Distinctive Style
review_body:
Really cute, fully lined, cotton summer dress. Adjustable spaghetti straps. Delicate lace and buttons add to the simplicity of this dress. The elastic waist is very stretchy and forgiving. The darts at the bust, make a little extra room. The length of the dress falls above the knee. I love that this dress is fully lined, otherwise it would be see through and I wouldn't be happy. product_title: Ezcosplay Womens Lucky Hand Print Cross Back Sleeveless T Shirt Vest Tank Tops
review_headline: Cute design, but thin & rough texture make this a no go for me
review_body:
The design is very cute and the printed on logo looks as if it will stay on over time without fading or peeling. The back is almost completely open as pictured in the listing, which creates a very cute open back design.

The material of this is not as listed "soft, breathable and flexible", but rather a thin, rough material that feels & looks like a mix of polyester and gauze. The tag indicates it is made of cotton; I have never felt such a rough texture on a 100% cotton shirt. I hoped it would soften with a wash, but it came out the same uncomfortable texture.

Due to the shirt's thinness and rough material, I am unsure when it could be worn. This might make a good top for throwing over a bikini top when going into restaurants in a beach resort.

I received this top at a discount in exchange for my honest review.

product_title: Ezcosplay Womens Lucky Hand Print Cross Back Sleeveless T Shirt Vest Tank Tops
review_headline: Very cute, soft and stylish tank for summer
review_body: One of my favorite go to tank tops for summer. Its super soft which is a huge plus, because when its warm outside who wants to be wearing something scratchy or stiff? Not me! It fits me loose but not loose enough to look like it doesn't fit. Does that make sense? It is not a skin tight sort of fit, it is a more relaxed fit which I love for summer. The design itself is eye catching and a high quality print. Plus, you won't see 10 other people wearing the exact same shirt as you at your company cook out or beach party. I have found I can easily wear this for super casual errand running or dress it up with bangles, earrings and a necklace for a more put together look. I'm happy to find that, after a few washings the print has not faded at all nor has the shirt size itself shrunk even when put thru the dryer. Ive found it has got softer, if that is even possible, with every wash so far. When I opened the package it did not have any sort of weird smell or feel to it either, which Ive had happen with other clothing items I have ordered online. All in all I would highly recommend this tank top, its fun, eye catching and very durable. I received this product at a discount in exchange for an honest review, and honestly I am beyond pleased with it.

product_title: Aonal Unisex Fashionable School Canvas Zip Bohemia Boho Style Backpack, Blue
review_body:
This Canvas Boho Style Backpack by Aonal is really nice. The material is a high quality canvas and the pattern is neat. Stitching all around the backpack is done very well. Zippers all worked great. I like that it has a pouch and a zippered pocket on the front and also small pockets on the sides. There are also numerous pockets inside for storage as well instead of just one whole opened area. The straps that go over your shoulders are nicely padded and don't dig into your skin. Straps are adjustable as well. Size is good and is a standard sized backpack measuring at approx. 12 1/2" x 6 1/8" x 16 3/4". Great for carrying all your books and supplies to and from school, college or work/office. Perfect for male or female. Definitely like this and would highly recommend.
**I received this product for free in exchange for an honest and unbiased review. No compensation for a positive review was provided. All of my reviews are based 100% off of my experience with the product and I never guarantee a positive review.

product_title: Ezcosplay Womens V-neck Loose Irregular Hem Summer Chiffon Short Beach Dress
review_headline: Size chart is VERY wrong. This is more China sizing, not US (i.e. XXL is like a US8)
review_body:
I loved the fabric of this dress but the thread is sloppy and hanging all over. I think I ordered an XL because these things run small (I wear a US sz14). This dress came with an XXL tag, which isn't even on the size chart, but you can make the assumption from the rest of the chart that it would fit larger than a size 16...This dress only fits someone who is like a 6, maybe an 8! Very disappointed that the sizing chart is not correct and that I paid over $10 for this dress!

I can't recommend this product, for the sizing chart being SO wrong and at a $16.99 price point, the threading on the hem should be better.
*Product received at a discount in exchange for honest review*

product_title: Ezcosplay Womens V-neck Loose Irregular Hem Summer Chiffon Short Beach Dress
review_body:
I would give this a 0!!!!

Email I sent with NO response after a week!

I wanted to give you the chance to correct the situation/purchase before I write a poor review for the Ezcosplay Womens V-neck Loose Irregular Hem Summer Chiffon Short Beach Dress. There are so many things wrong with this dress I am not sure where to start.

1. It is made poorly
2. The tag is stitched upside down
3. It is most definitely NOT a dress, (more like a crappy shirt)
4. I ordered up a size (XXL - I normally wear a L) and there is no way it will fit
5. The back (design) straps are completely uneven, one is sewn up higher than the other
6. The front does not lay like the picture on amazon
7. The dress is sewn much tighter in the middle than shown

these are just a few reasons I am not pleased. I know I received this at slight discount (~$11) but I would not have paid that knowing how poorly this was made. I got another dress from your company and it was much better! I do not know what you can do for me but this is very disappointing. I was looking forward to wearing this but now I cannot

product_title: Genie Slim Jeggings- Slim Fit-skinny Jeans Leggings
review_body:
These are great, but wouldn't day they beat the competition. I bought jeggings from Kohls which matched in quality and appearance, but these did win in the price aspect. How can you beat 3 pair for the little cost?

They did start to pill fairly quickly in the thigh area, but most of them do.
I would purchase again if I needed to, but definitely not to just add to my wardrobe.

I didn't bother ordering them with the extra lining on the inside because I'd be screwed when summer came around.
Just something to think about.

product_title: Disney Classic Minnie Mouse CUTE Junior Womens Long Sleeve T Shirt Top - Red Grey Black
review_body:
I was a bit unsure about purchasing this shirt because there were no prior reviews and no true photos of the product. (At the time of my purchase there was only a drawing of the shirt) For the $14.99 price tag, I'm satisfied with the shirt though. A few things that would have been nice to know before purchasing however...
First, this is not a red shirt, it's much more of a berry color, on the pink side. Personally, I like it better than true red but since an trying to coordinate outfits for a Disney trip, this won't really work now. Second, Minnie's bow and skirt have a little sparkle to them. Again, I like it better than being plain, but it would have been nice to know. Third, this is Juniors sizing, not Women's. I would order up a size. Fourth, the material is relative thin, so if you're looking for long lasting, this is not the shirt. Perfect for a short term Disney trip, but I don't see it holding up for years to come.

They're comfortable, he likes them, and they look great on him.  A little hint related to Nike's wild swings in sizing.  I carefully checked the size charts to see which size I should order. product_title: Men's Stringer Y Back Cotton Tank Top Camo
review_body: I ordered both the blue and camo colors.  Both tanks arrived quickly, individually folded in their own sealed plastic bags.  When I opened the bags and unfolded the tanks, I immediately noticed the camo tank was much narrower than the blue tank, even though both were tagged as "large".  When I tried on the camo tank, it fit very tight around the torso, more like a small.  That wasn't the biggest issue, though.  The scoops on both tanks were cut very deep, more than any other stringer tank I've worn.  With other stringers, I've experienced the frequent nipple reveal and need to reposition during a chest workout.  With these stringers (both colors), however, my entire pecs are exposed as soon as I put them on.  These tanks look ridiculous on me...I'm 5'9, 178 pounds, somewhat muscular with a 45" chest, 32" waist.  I can't imagine how these these tanks would look good on any body type.  I did not contact the seller.  Given the cheap price, will likely just trash them.

product_title: Areke Women's Overbust Corset Waist Cincher Bustier Tops Lace Boned W/ G-String Color Black-2 Size S
review_headline: Runs a Little Small, Fabric is Comfortable, Corset is Totally Adjustable
review_body:
The Areke Women's OverBust Corset is really a beautiful corset. I can't say it's a true corset, as the boning is flexible plastic, but it definitely looks sexy, and the corset can be tightened to breath losing tightness if you so choose. The fabric is smooth and very detailed with shiny looking vining flower motif. It feel smooth to the skin, and didn't cause any discomfort when wearing it. There are two ribbons on the front (folded in half so four ends are free) that can be tied into a box, and the back is completely laced up with close ended ribbons. The closed ended (no free ends) ribbons are incredibly useful as you can use them to tighten the corset by yourself without having to hold onto the ribbons - you can simply hook the ribbons around your thumbs and pull back (stretch!). Once tightened, you can tie them into a simple bow and call it a night. Note that this corset does run a little small, although because the back is entirely laced up, you can adjust it to fit your body. I normally wear a 0-2, and I had to loosen it so there was a 3" gap on the back. I still had plenty of ribbon to let out further if I chose, and honestly, it still looked good, but I wasn't used to have that much space between the opening.

The corset can be put on very easily by unlatching the small metal hooks on the front. I would definitely loosen the corset from the back if you're putting it on for the first time because those hooks can be difficult to latch. There are 6 of those to latch, and when trying to put this on while sucking in, it can get difficult. The corset is definitely not as hourglass shaped as in the display picture, and the amount of hourglassing you'll get depends highly on your figure and how tightly you lace up this bad boy. If you're looking for a huge bust lift, you may also want to consider wearing this with a strapless bra - when you tighten the front ribbons, it will make things look awesome.

This corset does come with a very tiny thong which I personally don't care for, but luckily this corset paired perfectly with a nice lacy pair of undies I already had. Add some [[ASIN:B000ZHGBU6 Dreamgirl Women's Silicone Lace Top Thigh High, Black, One Size]] and have a fun night in, or have fun rockin' this top out at a Rocky Horror Picture show - either way, it'll look awesome.

FYI - I was selected for this opportunity to review this item free of charge. The content and opinions expressed here are all my own.ich I personally don't care for, but luckily this corset paired perfectly with a nice lacy pair of undies I already had. Add some [[ASIN:B000ZHGBU6 Dreamgirl Women's Silicone Lace Top Thigh High, Black, One Size]] and have a fun night in, or have fun rockin' this top out at a Rocky Horror Picture show - either way, it'll look awesome. product_title: Neon Nightlife Light Up Bow Tie, One Size
review_body: I bought this bow tie and the glasses to wear out to a neon glow party at a club in Los Angeles. Let me tell you, this product is an amazing conversation starter. Any bit of shyness I had seemed to go out the window for the night. I was approached by tons of people all night long complementing me. The attention I got seemed to amp up my ego and made me to let go of my fear to approach women. The women responded well - most wanted to take a photo with me. It's a really weird feeling having strangers wanting to take a photo with you. I felt like a celebrity for the night. Good times!  The actual bow tie itself is made pretty well with clear stitching to attach the light up wire. The wire leading to the battery pack comes from the center of the bow tie and I was able to completely hide the wire under my collar. The battery pack was small and lightweight enough to be attached to my shirt in the back (concealed). The battery pack comes with a sticky side to stick the velcro to your shirt. It actually works pretty well. I was able to temporarily remove the battery pack to switch to the blinking mode and then stick it back to my shirt using the velcro.  The sizing is fine. It has a slider to adjust the neck size to fit most dudes. Longevity is great. It lasted from about 8pm to 2am so far with no loss in brightness.  Overall, I would totally recommend this to anyone who likes attention and wants to stand out in the party crowd.

review_body: I bought these for my girlfriend and I. She was way more into than I expected, and next thing I knew, this gag gift was leaving the house with me in it. These things are pretty cheesy, maybe just a little cute. I received these at a discount in exchange for my honest review, I'm not sure if I'd have honestly bought them otherwise, but that's a matter of my personal taste. I'm just embarrassed is all! That said, let's talk about quality. These are actually a better quality than  any custom shirt I've bought, and the material is really soft and nice on the skin. For $25 together, these come out to about $12.50 each, which is a really good deal if we're talking specifically shirt quality. Anyway, if these cheesy little shirts are your jam, then don't hesitate to buy them, they're seriously great quality. Also, if you want something that you consider kinda silly and ironically edgy, these also might be the shirts for you! They certainly were for me.

The color difference was not a bad thing, but something to be aware of.  I received this product in exchange for a review.

review_body:
I received these for review purposes. These run a little on the large side! but I guess I should have know that given they are unisex. a woman's Medium is Not a Mans medium. however I'm sure given they are made out of cotton Give it time and they will shrink up a bit.
The shirts are Fruit of the Loom Heavy HD Cotton that feels soft to the touch. The screen print in INCREDIBLY soft! and flush with the shirt. Overall I think it's a good purchase for you and your Bestie~

product_title: Fresh Tees Brand We Are Best Friends Cause Everyone Else Sucks Matching T-Shirt Set
review_headline: and it fits my shoulders and torso just fine, but the sleeves are slightly long
review_body: Cute shirts! I ordered an XL, and it fits my shoulders and torso just fine, but the sleeves are slightly long. Also, the lettering on one shirt is definitely more green than blue, which is what I saw on my monitor. Still, these are awesome shirts! Very comfy, bold colors, and a deep, true black. I like 'em.

product_title: Q.T. Bamboo, Men's No Show Socks Invisible Liners Made from Bamboo
review_headline: I'll probably just buy normal bamboo socks next time
review_body: I've not worn socks like this before, but I really like bamboo socks. With these, my feet felt warmer somehow than the other socks- and my feet seemed sweatier and smelled more than usual- like cotton socks. There's a different knit - about an inch wide in the front for traction I guess, it works but detracts from the comfort. They do seem durable, and stay on the foot well. I'll buy more full size socks in the future. I like Rambutan but they don't make these.

product_title: Q.T. Bamboo, Men's No Show Socks Invisible Liners Made from Bamboo
review_headline: A no-show sock that is actually no-show!!
review_body: I bought these for my husband and he was very impressed with them. I have tried a few different kinds of socks, but few are actually no show. The socks fit him well and are cut low enough to actually be no show. A lot of other socks are sold as no show but still are high enough on the ankle that you can see them. They breathe well and have a slight compression feel to them. These socks are soft, comfortable and the silicone grip on the heel insures that the socks stay in place. I might even take a pair because I see no reason why a woman can't wear them as well. I purchased this item for a discount in exchange for my fair and unbiased review.

product_title: Q.T. Bamboo, Men's No Show Socks Invisible Liners Made from Bamboo
review_headline: Great for under the husbands shoes and cradles the feet pretty well
review_body: I got these for my husband in the summer I have a very hard time getting him to wear socks. So I thought these would be a nice compromise since i wanted to control shoe odor. I put odor eater powder in the shoes let them sit over night outside. He started wearing these and boom no odor. None at all! These are a blessing to those of us fighting husband foot odor, and he said his shoes are more comfortable,so that is just a added bonus.. They fit him fine and he is a size 13 shoe. The material is stretchy kind of reminds. Me of a thicker nylon.I recieved this under a promotional discount in exchange for a honest, unbiased and non paid review.

product_title: Q.T. Bamboo, Men's No Show Socks Invisible Liners Made from Bamboo
review_headline: Soft and comfortable, No-show, Silicon grip to keep them on. One size fits most.
review_body: These bamboo socks are very soft and comfortable, I can wear them with my low-top shoes and it looks like I'm wearing nothing at all, but the best thing is that I feel like I'm wearing nothing at all. These socks are tight fitting, yet loose enough so that they don't overstretch and they don't bunch up in my shoes. The first time I wore these I completely forgot I had them on! They are one size fits most, but I believe I am on the bigger end of that with my feet. These socks do have a silicone grip in the heel to help the socks stay on your feet, something I believe was very helpful in keeping these on. This product was purchased at a discount in exchange for a review.

product_title: Fifth Sun Nintendo Splatoon Ink It Up Womens Graphic Racerback Tank
review_headline: Fabric quality speaking, this shirt shouldn't be valued more than 5 dollars.
review_body:
First of all, I ordered a womens small, and got shipped a womens large.

Second, 22 dollars is a rip off for this shirt. The fabric quality is so bad that I'm afraid of even grabbing it, since I am positive that I can rip it apart without effort with my bare hands.

I won't spend anymore money to send it back since I live in Panama and I would need to pay local inbound fees, which is not worth it. I have purchased for my wife shirts of much better fabric quality at 10 dollars or less. I don't recommend this shirt at all.

The design is cool and my wife will wear it even though it's large for her, but I have a strong feeling this fabric won't last more than 3 months of at least using it once per week.

product_title: PrettyGuide Women's Floral Lace Off Shoulder Blouse Tops
review_headline: This is a stunning set, very versitile, easy to dress up OR down!
review_body: I can't wait for this hot weather to be gone so I can justify wearing this during the daytime!!!  It's so pretty, let's start with that.  I really like the way that it fits, it's not bunchy around the shoulders, and The sleeves don't ride up so that I am constantly pulling it back down onto my arms. Which is really nice and kind of unexpected, especially since buying clothes online has never been very much of a success for me.  I think maybe because it is stretchy, that it makes it to where it stays where it supposed to. It's 90% cotton and then 10% stretchy material, it's super comfortable. The lace is soooo soft and doesn't make my skin itch, which is really out of the norm for me. My skin is somewhat sensitive to materials like this the majority of the time.  I love that this comes with the tube top that is worn underneath the lace. It means that I don't have to go rummaging through my closet to find an undershirt or cami to wear with us. It's a 2 piece set and the tube top is its own peace, it is not attached to the lace top. It's a plane tube, but it has the elastic stitching on top which is also really comfortable, and because it has the elastic top that means that it's going to stay in place a lot easier.  It's a beautiful set and really comfortable. If you have sensitive skin that's usually bothered by lace material I think you will be ok. My skin usually turns a bright red when it gets irritated, but it didn't with this top.  I received this product at a discounted rate for an honest review.

product_title: Cocoship Retro 50s Black Blue Floral Vintage High Waist Bikini Carnival Swimsuit(FBA)
review_body:
This is a great bathing suit. For the money you pay, it's really worth it. I got a size large, and it fit perfectly with the measurements that I have. The fabric is very high-quality, and the product looks identical to how it appears in the picture.
In case anyone was wondering what the fabric is made of, it's 82% Nylon and 18% Lycra and Spandex.
The swimsuit top does come with inserts for more breast support, and (if need be) these can be removed through a little hole that's on the inside.
While the top does not have an underwire, it does have a hard stick-like object sewn into the hem underneath each armpit for extra support and to prevent the top from twisting while in the water; also a very good thing.
As for the bottom, it has the same fabric components, and comes up above the belly button, as others have mentioned before me. There is a paper hygiene liner at the bottom, which I would recommend tearing off before you get it wet, because then it makes it hard to get off. There is a piece of fabric sewn on top which hides the, "pizza pouch" us thick girls often have. On the whole, it's very comfortable and well-made.

However, there is one complaint I have which I would like not to happen again. Earlier, I tried to order the other version of this swimsuit, the one which has a slightly different top: the one that ties in the front and shows more cleavage. When I placed my order, it was shortly deleted. I didn't receive any notice of this whatsoever and I had no idea what had happened to my order. Nothing had been taken out of my card account either, so it was as if I had never ordered it in the first place. I came back a few days later to find out that swimsuit was no longer available in my size. That explains why my order was deleted, but I never received a notice about it, or an apology for inconvenience, which I would have liked.

On the whole though, I'm very satisfied with this current bathing suit, and if it had not been for the order mishap, it would have all five.

review_body: Just got a pair of these to supplant my Pearl Izumi shorts.  The padding on these is much more dense than the Pearl's.  While the Pearl's do well for 90 minute, 25 mile rides, I've decided to break these in for my century in two days.  The thought of riding 100 in the Pearl's made me very happy these showed up today.  Rating cycling shorts is tough.  They'll all make your butt hurt less, but there are so many factors....type of cycle, type of seat, skinny butt, fat butt. product_title: Ezcosplay Women's Sexy Plus Size Swimsuit Super Size Bikini
review_headline: Too sexy for this bikini, I guess?
review_body:
I took a risk on this because it looked gorgeous. Online shopping got me again! This says a US 2XL and it is not. I'm a 40D with fairly large hips and was hoping the long torso on the bathing suit would flatten my unflattering flab. No, no and no. This did not fit any part of my body. While the fabric was nice and quality, my boobs weren't fitting and the straps were cutting into my skin. I struggled for fifteen minutes to get myself out of the top. I leaned over to put the bottoms on and they were cutting into my skin before I even get the second leg in. I tried giving this to my older sister who wears a XL and no, this was still incredibly uncomfortable and too tight on her. I don't know what US 2XL they've seen but I dress in a 1 or 2 in Torrid's sizes and haven't had an issue like that. Please make sure to follow their size chart carefully and hopefully they will update it and introduce more sizes because this is a nice quality bikini.

product_title: Boys Straight Jacket
review_headline: Painfully Cruel to Those Living With or Caring for Mental Illness
review_body:
I am writing to share a serious matter of importance as it relates to this costume.
My younger daughter, once an honor student, athlete and musician before her illness presented during the onset of adolescence, has lived with schizoaffective disorder for the past six years, and was hospitalized as a child. We’ve taken her to UCLA and Stanford, as well as our local hospitals, hoping to make sense of her devastating illness. If you have ever spent anytime visiting a loved one in a mental health treatment facility, I assure you, you would understand that this costume is painfully cruel.
Human suffering is not an appropriate inspiration for a Halloween costume. I doubt you would sell a Stage Four Cancer, Holocaust or Slave costume. Why would you sell a costume that makes fun of a severe brain disorder?
Stigma only encourages hopelessness and despair. Please reconsider stigmatizing our daughter’s very real illness by removing
this costume and other mental illness inspired costumes from your inventory.

review_headline: Protect your credit cards from RFID readers with this wallet
review_body: I am so impressed with this leather bi-fold wallet!  It is beautifully made of genuine cowhide leather,  and is lined with RFID blocking material.  There are 6 slots for credit cards, a clear window for your ID or license, and a divided currency pocket, so you can separate your large and small bills. Even though this is a bi-fold wallet, it is no larger than the tri-fold wallet my husband currently uses.  The wallet arrives in a gift box, and a fabric envelope, making it perfect for gift-giving.  I was delighted to purchase during a promotion, to evaluate this wallet and share my opinion through a review.

product_title: Mellow Judys Women's Sleeveless Striped Maxi Dress, Large, Red
review_body: I'm wearing this dress today for the first time, and it's super cute. It's coming from oversees somewhere, so it took FOREVER to arrive, so be mindful of that. It's a stretchy material. I'm very busty, so I went with a large. It's nice to find a dress that fits overall when you're busty, without looking trashy, so this is a big plus. The only complaint I have is that the stitching is cruddy. Along the waistline and down each side seam there is some bunching. Since its gathered and the bottom half is a colorful pattern it's not very noticeable, but still, more care could have been taken in making it. I'm wearing a cardigan with mine, the tank top looks a little boxy, so the cardigan helps the flow a little better. Overall it's a cute dress, I wouldn't wear it to a fancy gathering or anything, because of the stitching, but for a casual day it's great :-) *I received this item at a discount in exchange for an honest review*

product_title: ToBeInStyle Girl's Pack of 6 "Belle of the Ball" Underwear Set
review_headline: Purchase 2 sizes larger than you need
review_body:
ToBeInStyle did a really good job imitating Ariel from Disney on this set. These look like authentic Disney merchandise. I read reviews left on other ToBeInStyle products and they suggested that their products run very small. My daughter is about to turn 4. She's is 3 ft 5 in tall and 40 lbs, very tall for her age. She looks more like a 5 or 6 year old child. She typically wears the XS small in the children's sizes. She can wear 5T shirts but because she's so tall pants are normally way to short on her. For this order I ordered two sizes up, a medium.

The medium on this set is only slightly larger than I would have expected for an XS. The straps on the bra are adjustable so they can be moved all the way up to fit smaller children, like mine. They can also be extended for older children with a more developed torso.

The boy shorts seem to be designed with little thought on making extra room for a kid with a derrière. The fabric is cut the same in the front and the back. Because they are a spandex material they still fit but if you're child is developed and you want them to have a little breathing room you may need to go up an extra size. Since my child is a toddler ordering 2 sizes up worked perfectly. These fit loosely and comfortably. They don't fall off but they don't constrict her either. If I were ordering for my pre-teen I would order 3 sizes up. Which means these wouldn't fit her!

PROS:
Looks like licensed Disney Ariel
Bright colors
Well made
Adjustable arm straps on the bra

CONS:
Run VERY small (2 sizes to be exact)

Ratings (Out of five stars):
Style: *5*
Design: *5*
Fabric Quality: *5*
Comfort: *5*
Value: *5*

Overall rating: 25 out of 25 stars / 5 Star Average

I hope you enjoyed this review. If you have any questions about my experience please leave me a comment. I will be happy to follow up on my experience with this product.

product_title: BabyPreg® Women's Maternity Seamless Nursing Bras Seamless
review_headline: This is NOT a good thing. 3
review_body:
I bought this product as I was looking for a wear all day bra that could be used for breast feeding and hands free pumping. Most of the hands free pumping bras are not designed to be worn all day.

The one and only Pro is that it can be worn all day.

The list of Cons:
1. Can't use as a nursing bra. When I come home from work I need to change to a nursing bra if I want to breastfeed my baby.
2. As the bottles fill with milk while pumping the bra sags and the breast shields tip away from my breasts. This is NOT a good thing.
3. I own the Simple Wishes bra (meant for pumping only) and the area that holds the breast shield is constructed exactly the same way. It's great when you are using the bra for pumping only as you do with the Simple Wishes bra, but not ideal for a wear all day bra. I don't want my nipple poking out of my everyday bra.
4. Not T shirt friendly. If you wear frumpy clothing than I guess it might work for you.
5. You get what you pay for. It must be impossible to produce a quality bra at $18.99.
6. If you want to return you will need to pay for shipping back to China. It will cost you more than the bra.

product_title: Slim Leather Wallet for Men - Bifold Zippered Wallet with 8 Card Slots,Durable wallet with 2 bill holders, Travel Wallet 2 Quick Access ID Windows, Minimalist Leather Wallet
review_headline: Luxuriously soft leather, nice simple design with useful features
review_body:
There is one particular feature I really love about this wallet - the zippered pocket . I always cringe to the thought that I might have given 100$ bill instead of something smaller or somehow given a bill with an extra larger bill sticked to the bottom. Sometimes in a hurry, I get too distracted which this may really happen or may have happened in the past. The zippered pocket will make sure only the bigger bills will be there - 50 or 100$. That way I know for sure what denomination I am getting.

The material is soft and craftsmanship is very decent. It is very simple with an embossed logo on the lower right. There are many compartments for your cards and IDs. I also had wallets where the ID portion can be detachable. Could be a disadvantage or disadvantage but I personally prefer one that is permanently stitched to the wallet.

Sample wallet was provided to me for review and evaluation.

product_title: Slim Leather Wallet for Men - Bifold Zippered Wallet with 8 Card Slots,Durable wallet with 2 bill holders, Travel Wallet 2 Quick Access ID Windows, Minimalist Leather Wallet
review_body: This wallet has a couple nice features. The main one being that it has a zippered pocket which is not something often found in men's wallets. From the outside this looks like a nice high quality leather wallet but there are a few workmanship issues on the interior. There is one corner on the inside that has white showing through were this was sewn or cut wrong. My husband prefers his wallets to be very thin. This one is a little thicker than his previous one. Overall still a nice product. Sampler received in exchange for an honest review.

product_title: Slim Leather Wallet for Men - Bifold Zippered Wallet with 8 Card Slots,Durable wallet with 2 bill holders, Travel Wallet 2 Quick Access ID Windows, Minimalist Leather Wallet
review_headline: Very Nice Wallet, With Special Zippered Bills Section
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:eba6fa51ef9ed789459441958b4a183]] The DANCL® Men's Leather Flipout ID bi-fold wallet is a standard size wallet that should provide many years of service.
The leather is soft and appears to be high quality. The name is embossed on the front and that adds a nice touch to the appearance. The name is also embossed on the inside on the right hand credit card slot. This is a nice touch.

There are three credit card slots on each side of the wallet. You could double up if you have an excess number of cards but that tends to make the wallet bulky. There are two window slots on the \\"flip-out\\" section. The \\"flip-out\\" part is permanently attached to the wallet. You will find some men who prefer a detachable flip-out section while others like the safety provided by a permanently attached flip-out section. The window slots are for your driver's license and any other identification what you might need to show often - such as health insurance card, employer ID, etc.

The bill section has a divider so you can sort the folding money by value. The neatest feature of this wallet is the zippered compartment at the rear of the bills section. If you carry large bills, you will want to store your large bills in the zippered compartment. I like to carry a cash reserve so I never run out of money. I keep my cash reserve in the zippered section and I know if I have to \\"borrow\\" from my cash reserve, it is time to replenish it.

The wallet is very nice. The materials appear to be good quality. If you are considering this as a gift, just be aware that it does not come in a box. If you are buying the wallet for yourself, the lack of a box should not matter.

I was provided a sample for testing/review purposes.

product_title: Shire Mens Genuine Real Leather Bifold Wallet - Made for Protection and Style
review_body:
I purchased this mens black leather wallet to give to my dad. The wallet is 9.5cmx11.5cm (3.7inchesx4.5inches). So, it’s pretty much the same size as most wallets. When I received the wallet, my initial reaction was that it was very stylish and attractive. The wallet is a bifold and meant to fold in half. The bifold wallet is made from leather and throughout the entire wallet, there is a solid black pebble pattern, except for the silver rod on the corner. That aspect gives it a unique finished touch. The silver finish is screwed onto the corner of the wallet. This bifold wallet is perfect for my dad because he likes to keep his wallet in the back pocket of his pants. So, it's nice that the wallet is thin and there really isn’t an apparent bulk there. The wallet has one bill compartment and six card slots and credit card pockets, which is quite spacious.

The quality of the leather seems to be of high quality. I’m glad that the wallet is sanded out to remove imperfections and coated in resin like most wallets nowadays. The wallet is pretty soft and smooth. I like the full grain texture and the wallet seems durable and sturdy. As well as that the wallet is pretty thin. The card slots fit credit cards perfectly and currency does fit perfectly in the bill compartment.

Before I gave the wallet to my dad, I wanted to inspect it a little longer to see if there were any issues with the wallet internally because externally everything looked great. I looked at the edge of the leather weather and it appears to be turned edged. I inspected the wallet and there appears to be small stitching without any flaws.

All in all, the wallet is lovely. It’s spacious and contains a lot of slots. The wallet seems to have been made from high quality materials. Anyways, I gave it to my dad and he really liked it. I would definitely recommend this wallet as it's durable and attractive.

Pros:
-Fashionable/Attractive
-Smooth
-Wallet appears to be well made, with high quality materials used throughout
-Plenty of room for a various of things like credit cards, IDs and etc.
-The wallet is functional and durable

Cons:
-None.

Disclosure: I have received this product in exchange for my honest review. However, my review is 100% my own unbiased opinion.used throughout -Plenty of room for a various of things like credit cards, IDs and etc. -The wallet is functional and durable Cons: -None. There is a nice window slot for your photo ID, which is very convenient. It has plenty of slots for all of your cards, and other needs you might keep in a wallet. product_title: Victorian Vagabond Men's Denim Motorcycle Jacket
review_headline: It's pretty much exactly like the type of leather motorcycle jackets ...
review_body: I bought the jacket because I wanted a non-leather vegan alternative to this type of motojacket and they delivered! It's pretty much exactly like the type of leather motorcycle jackets with the belt attached and the three zipper pockets in front, but it's all denim. The denim is very sturdy and comfortable and it feels like it'll last for years and years. The shiny bits are a light silver. And if you do studding/spiking or any kind of punk modification, the denim is such that it holds two-prong studs without an issue at all. Same with screw-back spikes, pin badges and cloth paint. In the end, the jacket turned out really fantastically and I'm satisfied with my purchase.  I'm 5'8, skinny body type and the medium fit me just fine. It's slightly big on me, but that's what I like in a good jacket.

product_title: Joseph Abboud Men's 6 Pack Full Cut Cotton Boxers Sleep Shorts
review_headline: I like to wear boxer-style shorts to sleep in
review_body: I like to wear boxer-style shorts to sleep in, and women's shorts have inconsistent sizing. I was also specifically looking for 100% cotton. I took a chance on these shorts even though no one else has reviewed them, and I'm very happy I did! First, I got a larger size in men's so that they wouldn't bind or pinch when I was sleeping, and they were the perfect size, and they are very soft. I actually wore some of them before washing them, and then when I took them from the dryer they were even softer.  They are big enough that I don't feel bad stepping outside in them, and they are very pleasing to look at. The whole packet of shorts cost less than $18 and there were six pair. That comes out to $3 per pair, which I think is a steal for what I got! Definitely recommend these.  Edit: I've had these shorts now for a year and a half or so. After the first wash, they shrank in the legs, which caused them to ride up and was pretty uncomfortable. Also, even though all I do in these things is sleep in them--and I have other sleepwear, some of them are sprouting holes.

product_title: Active Shapers Womens Anti Cellulite Workout Capri Hot Pants
review_headline: It works but there's a few cons
review_body:
Pros:
- The fabric stretches and hugs your body well
- It keeps the heat in so during workouts, you sweat more in areas where this is touching your body.

Cons:
- Size. Order a size bigger. I am size 0-2 and got a small (for size 4-6) and it fits well. I don't think it would've fit otherwise.
- Neoprene smell - I guess this is expected but the first time I opened the package, the smell was off putting. Tip: The smell did get less potent after I put it out outside under the sun for a couple days.
- Sound. You get a little squeaking sound as you walk. I'm hoping this will go away after much use but at this point I'm happy I used it for Zumba where the sounds are loud and I wouldn't feel bad about making noises. I won't be using this for yoga right now.
- Price. It seems expensive for a pair of pants. That said I have no idea if pants with the same functions would cost any differently.

This product is purchased at a discount for my feedback with no guarantee for a positive review. I hope you find this review helpful!

product_title: Active Shapers Womens Anti Cellulite Workout Capri Hot Pants
review_body: These fit extremely well! I am so glad to order in sizes instead of the one size fits all. I measured and picked out the size per the chart, and they do fit great. These aren't extremely itchy like others I have tried in the past. They are a little noisy, so I probably won't wear them out and about. They are fantastic however for daily workout and lounging around the house in.

product_title: Active Shapers Womens Anti Cellulite Workout Capri Hot Pants
review_body: First off, these are made from mostly neoprene. They're very noisy and they get hot. It really should've been done at the seam so as not to make a hole. I also think these are too expensive. I usually wear a 4-6 but got a medium, and they fit well. review_body: I received the product for a discounted price in exchange for an honest review. With that said the size runs a bit small for myself anyway. They seem to hold in the heat like they say.  I do not think you could wear them to work etc. I thought I would be able to wear them under a maxi skirt or something to help with cellulite  but they are extremely loud to walk in like a giant diaper.  I will probably work out in them but I cannot use them for yoga or some other work out until I get a little smaller as I said they run small in the waist I bought a size larger than I thought I needed and the waist had no elasticity and digs into my skin no bending in these. Maybe I can update with a better review once they fit better.  But like I said I ordered a size up they are loud and good stretch every where besides the actual waist band they do make it sweat but I do not think they are worth the high price they are asking.

product_title: Active Shapers Womens Anti Cellulite Workout Capri Hot Pants
review_body:
I'm always wary about ordering pants online but I'm glad I took a chance on these. I wear a 2/4 and got the small...they fit really well and I find them comfortable. The fabric is thick (ponte/neoprene) and smooth out all the lumps, bumps, and creases. Time will tell if my bit of cellulite smooths out but you certainly can't see it while wearing these.

I like they way they look as well as feel. 4 stars because I have no way to verify if it really helps cellulite and they do have a slight synthetic odor that will likely go away with more wear. Also the logo on the left knee is fine for work out ...but these are nice enough to wear with regular clothing so I kind of wish it wasn't there because they could easily be dressed up.

review_headline: they are made with such terrible fabric that they are nearly translucent
review_body: Absolute junk, they are made with such terrible fabric that they are nearly translucent.  There is some stitching around the perimeter that barely meets the definition of stitching.  When we washed them with a load of towels, the entire load came out of the dryer saturated with this fairly strong odd chemical smell and they didn't feel right.  Given that these handkerchiefs came directly from China, who knows what was on them.  Using the towels after a shower resulted in *us* having this weird chemical smell.  We had to wash the towels two more times to get them back to normal.    You are paying about 25 cents for the "bandanas" and the rest is probably the shipping directly from China.  Its still overpaying.

review_headline: I charge mostly everything but it's good to have 20$ or so just in case for ...
review_body:
Very thin and compact.

I was tired of carrying a wallet in my back pocket. It was bothering my back. Saw this wallet and was not sure because there were very little review or info. about it.

Pros: 1. thin. 2 fits 6 cards (cc size) and keeps the cards fit snugly. No problem fitting my CC and ID. Even using all six slots, it still very thin. 3. Center of the wallet has slit where you can put some bills. I charge mostly everything but it's good to have 20$ or so just in case for emergency 4. It comfortable when I carry it in my front pocket and not bulky. 5. It has a nice look to it. (Does not look cheap). 6. It's a great price!

I wish one of the cc slots was a clear plastic slot so I would not need to take out my id from the slot. It still gets 5 stars because when I bought I knew that it didn't have a clear plastic slot so it's not a defect of the wallet.

I would definitely recommend this wallet for someone looking for a light, comfortable and nice looking front pocket wallet.

product_title: Cissy's May® Retro 1950s Vintage A-line Fall Pleated Swing Skirts for Women
review_body:
What a great skirt. I ignored the sizing labels and went by the measurements-- I'm usually a size 6 (or medium in misses'), with a waist of 29 inches. Even though the sizing says size 6 is small here, I'm so glad I ignored it. Medium fits juuuust right.

It's such a striking print with great colors. Wore it today and got so many compliments. Goes well with a variety of solid tops: black, gray, orange, blue, or even pink. It's a flattering and modest cut, and I was able to wear it right out of the package without ironing it (though if I wanted to be a perfectionist, I would have-- little creases here and there, but nothing noticeable because of the pleats). The material is fairly thick and not prone to wrinkling. Sewing is good, with a serged hem stitched under the bottom.

Only complaint is that the zipper sticks. I had a hard time getting it zipped up. But it's fine once it's zipped. This is a versatile skirt to add to your wardrobe for when you're feeling bold.

I received this for review.

product_title: Totina Women's Deep-V Neck Elegant Cap Sleeve Pleating Work Dress
review_headline: Would likely be an attractive dress for the right person
review_body:
NOTE: I received a free sample of this dress for review.

This is not a bad little dress, but I wound up having mixed feelings about it. First of all, I'm not sure why it is labeled as a "Vintage Bridesmaid" dress--unless you are having a VERY casual wedding, this would not be an appropriate bridesmaids dress at all! It is a simple polyester cotton blend dress (note that although the item description above says that the dress is 95% polyester, 5% Spandex, the tag on the inside of my dress states that it is 65% polyester, 35% cotton). I think that it would be appropriate for most work environments as well as social occasions, depending on your preferred style, but I will say more on that later.

I first want to comment on the sizing of this dress. This dress is described as "slim fit" and "above knee length." Also, it is made in China, where the sizing tends to run small. Given these factors AND following the sizing chart, I ordered a medium, which was supposed to be equivalent to a US Size 8. This is in fact my usual size in pants, although because I am smaller on top, I often wear a smaller size in dresses that are fitted only at the waist and NOT otherwise form-fitting. Well, it turns out that I SHOULD have ordered a size small, as the medium was definitely too large for me. It is hard to tell from the attached pictures, but the dress was large around the torso--in fact, I slipped it over my head without having to unzip the side zipper--and it was BELOW knee length (I am just shy of 5'5" tall).

Next, I want to mention the color. I ordered the dress in Purple, which appears as a nice, bright, saturated purple in the item description. How the dress appears in the photos I have attached is true to color after a SINGLE washing. (A second note: although this listing says that the dress should be hand-washed, the materials that came with the dress indicated that it could be machine-washed, and I did so in cold, via the gentle cycle.) Finally, I'll address the style. I did like the pleating at the bust and the waist, and the v-neck was flattering. However, the overall effect of this dress seemed somewhat matronly to me. I'm not sure what it was--I'm sure I would have liked the dress better if it had fit me better and wasn't too long, but I think that the stand-up collar and the cap sleeves also added to the matronly effect.

I will probably still wear this dress to work, as it will be an easy choice for a workday that will look fairly polished. But I would feel too dowdy wearing this dress socially or for other occasions. For others purchasing this dress, I would recommend choosing size carefully and keeping in mind that the color might not be exactly as it appears on screen.so in cold, via the gentle cycle.) product_title: Ekouaer Womens Sexy Seamless Lace Soft Boyshort Panties Hipster Brief Underwear
review_headline: much more comfortable than I expected them to be
review_body:
These are more comfortable than I expected them to be. I don't generally wear lacy underwear, so I was afraid the side parts would be scratchy. But they're not. When I have these on, they feel like I am wearing a garment made all of the same material (basically).

I have the size XL in \\"nude.\\" I am normally a size 8 or medium in pants and I think these are in Asian sizes -- I ordered up a few, just to be safe, and that was the right decision, since these ended up being comfortable. They weren't constricting at all. The fit may be slightly different depending on how you carry your weight/what your body shape is. But they're a little stretchy so there is some give in that regard.

Minor criticisms: the waistband can roll up in these. Also, the lace parts and solid parts, being made of different materials, don't stretch in quite the same way, which might make these a little harder to get up over your rear end (since there's more lace in the back). However, they *do* fit.

These are well-made with no loose threads, gaps, or holes. The color is uniform throughout. Overall, a nice pair of underwear. I do wish they came with washing instructions, though. 4.5 stars.

Product provided by the seller for evaluation purposes.

product_title: Mella Bridal Elegant Women's Wedding Dress Sexy Backless Sweetheart Lace Wedding Dresses for Brides 2017 Spring 2016 Winter
review_body:
I was very nervous about ordering these. I had never ordered clothing online before. I am very happy with them. The color is very true to online. The dress fits perfect in both the chest and waist, but need to shorten the length. dress is very light so it will be perfect for the August wedding. This dress is a great find for the price. The material quality is better than I thought, and the fit is exactly as shown in the charts. I am petite (5'2"), and the top strap fit surprisingly well. The chest area is roomy (I'm a B cup), but the strap keeps everything in place. The dress is very long, but nothing an easy hem can't fix. Overall, this is a great find and looks very nice. My husband thought I spent over $200 on it at a department store - definitely recommend this for a formal event.
Btw, they also come very folded up so they are pretty wrinkled up, they will need to be professionally steamed to get the wrinkles out.

product_title: Women Set of 3 Genie Custom Bra w/Removable Pads
review_body: If you are a gymnast or are naturally very flexible and have the patience of Job by all means buy these bras.  I actually like the idea of the bra and if you can get them on they are pretty comfortable; however, getting the straps in the slots is sooo time consuming and if you want to adjust the straps you'd better figure it out before you put the bra on because if you pull the strap down while you have it on, it will most likely come out of the slot and you will have to start all over again.  Here is where the flexibility comes in, if you are able to reach your arm way behind your back and tighten the strap then you'll have it made.  lol.  I also have the problem with the straps falling off when you put it on.  I was able to fix this some by only putting on the back part first and pulling them over and attaching the front after I have it on.  That's a problem too; however, because you have to find the slots. Here is where the patience of Job comes in, I just spent at least 20 minutes with reading glasses on getting the straps into a slot and gave up on trying to tighten them because I'm not a gymnast nor am I very flexible.  I suggest you wake up a half hour early every morning to get this bra on.  Don't even bother to try and call the Genie company.  They are of no help whatsoever.  So, that's my story.

review_headline: I explained that is exactly why I wanted this fine work of art on my head
review_body: Lost in a sea of porkchops on a stick and fried oreos, this hat stood out in the crowd on a late August day at the Iowa state fair. I tracked down the man wearing this hat and asked where he got such a gorgeous item. The gentlemen seemed accosted and immediately attacked my character as well as my red hair that was slowly turning into what he described as a "pathetic auburn". I explained that is exactly why I wanted this fine work of art on my head. I saw his eyes start to well up and the rigid man become vulnerable. As a tear rolled down his face, he slowly removed his hat and said with a quiver "I too am trying to hide a terrible head of hair." He handed me this hat, regained his composure then promptly spewing out nonsense. Odd guy, nice hat though.

product_title: Hitop Women Elastic Sexy Halter One Piece Swimsuit Swimsuits for Youth Girls(S)
review_headline: A bit difficult to get into...
review_body: This is a very cute swimsuit! It's padded which is a plus! It is, however, pretty difficult to put on... I tried stepping into it, but I couldn't get the chains past my @$$... So I stepped into it through the shark mouth and contorted my upper body and wiggled the top part on. The chain got all tangled up in my hair, so don't go getting your hair done before putting this swim suit on! I laughed pretty hard when I finally had it on cuz some of the teeth were tucked into the suit, so the shark's mouth looked like it was missing some teeth! After I pulled all the teeth out in place, I ran out to show my husband. The chain was slightly digging into my neck, so I was trying to adjust the top part and SNAP! The chain broke off! I wish the chain was a little bit longer or adjustable. It looks like I might be able to pry the end chain open and hook it back onto the suit, but I also kinda just wanna get rid of the chain all together and just replace it with an adjustable white strap. The material doesn't feel cheap and the suit seems pretty sturdy, except the chain. I'm usually a size small and this fits just right. I'm a skinny person, but not the most toned person (especially in the midsection) and some of the teeth seem to point in certain directions or sometime lay parallel to the floor... (And now your shark looks like it's got some jacked up teeth) They're not gonna perfectly point up and down like the picture.
