product_title: Sakkas Addyson Drop Neck Long Sleeve Embroidered Boho Dress
review_body:
It's beautiful and well made, but doesn't look nearly as good on me as it does in the picture. It makes it look like I have a thicker middle than I do, and the length is unflattering. It comes to about 2" past my knees and makes me look shorter than my 5 feet and 3 inches. I think this would be lovely on taller ladies, but unfortunately not for me. I tried it with a waist belt and tucked in the front to make it a high-low dress (see attached pictures), which definitely made it look a lot better, but at this price point, I'd like a dress that I like out of the bag, not one I have to spend more money on to get altered.

To help with sizing, I'm 34DD and 135 lbs, and I found the bust to fit me comfortably.

TL;DR: Weird length on me, might look amazing on other body types. Try it!

review_body: I'm one of those OCD people who has to be organized almost to a fault or they get nervous.  For me, that even applies to my pocket book.  No matter what I do, once I take 1 thing oput to use, all the organization goes out the window and I can't even find my cell phone.  I've seen infomercials on similar products, but they didn't appeal to my OCD-ness, but I had to do something.  This organizer seemed perfect, so I ordered it.  First of all, it was delivered on the second day of the delivery time fram I was given.  Impressive.  Second, for the price, I got better quality than I expected and the color even matches what you see online.  However, with all the stuff I put in my purse, this needs to be at least 1-2 inches longer and wider.  But never fear.  It satisfies my OCD because all of the things that slide around in my purse making it a mess all fit in.  If I could give more than 5 stars, I would.  I have to learn to use the outside mesh pockets.  Why?  I still can't find my cell phone!  :-O

product_title: Neon Nightlife Men's Light Up Saw Movie Creepy Halloween Jigsaw Puppet Mask, Red
review_headline: Creepy Movie mask is a hit with the ladies
review_body:
My friend and I bought these masks. He wore the Saw Movie mask in red and I wore the Guy Fawkes mask in aqua . We attended a big masquerade party. Let me tell you, this product is an amazing conversation starter. We were approached by tons of people all night long complementing us. I think we had the best masks out of about 200 people there. Most people who approached us wanted to take a photo. It's a really weird feeling to have tons of strangers approach you to take a photo with you. We felt like celebrities for the night. A bit of caution - this Saw Movie mask is really freakin’ creepy at night. You’ve been warned.

The mask is made of plastic and has a white finish. There is a wire leading to the battery pack comes from the side of the mask. I was able to run the wire above my ear then under my shirt. I placed the battery pack in my pants pocket. The entire wire and battery pack was hidden except for the 6 inch area leading from my ear to the top of my shirt. My friend had long hair and was able to completely hide the wire with his hair when he wore it.

The battery pack was easily stored in my pants pocket. The battery pack makes a slight whining sound when on. When I turned it on at home in silence, I thought I was going to have to listen to it all night. But luckily once it is placed in your jeans pocket you can barely hear it. Add the various sounds of a public location and the sound is completely unnoticeable.

Longevity is great. It lasted hours with no loss in brightness on a single set of batteries.

Overall, I would totally recommend this to anyone who likes attention from a creepy mask and wants to get noticed!

product_title: XCOSER MEN'S Newest V6 Lord Helmet PVC Impressed Red Grid 2016 Adult
review_headline: GREAT HELMET BUY V6 AND UP - DO NOT BUY OLDER MODELS
review_body:
This is the model to buy - skip on older models

OLDER MODEL: I have a 24 inch head, and originally bought the M (22-24 inch head size) older version of this mask, which was a mistake. You apparently were expected to install the light up eyes which then made the helmet not even fit on the max size that was recommended for said helmet.

THIS MODEL: Super Sturdy! Already has pre installed eye lights, that you can actually see out of! You can see perfectly when the lights aren't on, and decently while on - I will say if you are wearing this in a con setting you will be a okay if you wanted to leave the lights on the majority of the time, as well lit rooms (such as convention halls) can be seen fine through the light up lenses, HOWEVER, if you are wearing this to a dark area/halloween party type setting I'd recommend only leaving them on for pictures and posing for brief moments of time (or putting it in blinker mode) because you will definitely not be able to see.

The mold and colors are great, but I had to dock a star because like everyone says they jam this near perfect mask into a tiny damn box and it's warped by the time you get it, thus making you need to reshape it back to form manually by keeping held it in an opposite position of how it's warped (i wrapped mine in a towel and had it pressed against a wall with a heavy chair for example). It's quite an inconvenience to have to do this, and I hope they make note of how many people are complaining about that factor so future shipments won't suffer.

Other than that this mask is great for those looking to cosplay but aren't too craftsy to make their own, or simply don't have the time.

product_title: CrowsRock Outdoor Waist Pack Bag - Camping, Hiking, Cycling, Climbing - Belt Bag Pack Cover (Black)
review_headline: Sturdy enough for back-country hikes, but so attractive that my teen carries it to school everyday.
review_body:
I'm so glad that other reviewers have posted pictures because this pack is MUCH better looking than the pictures on the product page. We were expecting a drab grey bag and received a beautiful black and red one.

There's no penetrating the teen-aged mind and it's probably a waste of time to try. I got this waist pack thinking that some of my relatives could test it for me. They run, hike, bike, and camp and it looked (and is!) so sturdy and well-designed. The minute it came out of the box, my teen grabbed it and she's carried it everywhere since then. And she has a closet full of backpacks and totes.

It really is very pretty and (as she points out) she needs all its nooks and crannies to get organized for school everyday. Since her school has no lockers, she's both a student and a pack-mule. There are three zippered pockets (two large and one small) and the larger two have dividers inside them. And there are two mesh pockets, so she can carry both the thermos of hot tea that she needs in the morning and the water bottle that she needs in the afternoon.

She most frequently snaps on the adjustable nylon shoulder strap and uses it as a shoulder bag, although I've also seen her carry it with the nylon handle on top. And when she's really loaded down (with display boards for school projects, say) and can't spare a hand to keep the strap on her shoulder, she straps it around her waist.

I think the most out-standing feature (other than the looks) is the mesh-and-ridged backing that fits next to your body when you use it as a waist pack. If you've ever hiked (or spent all day at a theme park) with a fanny pack around your waist, you know how the heat and moisture builds up under them. This lets the air in and the moisture out. It's a brilliant design.

Back in my hiking days I would have killed for a waist pack with the features of this one, especially that wonderful ventilation system. I'm amused about my teen taking it over, but I guess it just goes to show that high school really IS a survival course!

Free sample provided for review.n taking it over, but I guess it just goes to show that high school really IS a survival course!

Free sample provided for review.

product_title: CrowsRock Outdoor Waist Pack Bag - Camping, Hiking, Cycling, Climbing - Belt Bag Pack Cover (Black)
review_headline: good balance, large capacity without bulk
review_body:
I was interested in this waist pack for two reasons. The primary one is that it's got two pockets on either side with an elastic band to hold drink bottles firmly in place. I have a hiking pack which is actually pretty nice, but only has one pocket for a drink which is too shallow and I found that the single pouch design creates imbalance. Also, for a longer hike, two drink bottles are better than one.

There are three pouches that are sealed by zippers. The biggest one is big enough to put in a bento box sided lunch (or an ample supply of protein bars) or other snacks. All of the zippers are the plastic sort, but the ones on mine operated smoothly without catches or problems of any sort.

The waist strap has a maximum length of about 42 inches (I measured it as being between 42.5 and 43, but I'm being conservative). It has a fairly standard plastic clasp which is very easy to lock and unlock as well as adjust to desired tightness. I should note that my pouch came with a slightly improper assembly. There are fabric loops at the ends of the adjustable straps that should be hooked into the plastic parts (you'll note they have a little break in the plastic to hook them into) that were just threaded through. I easily just hooked them into the loops myself, and this may be a problem with only mine, but if some of the loops seem to slip out, have a look at this portion to see if it wasn't properly assembled.

The back of the pouch is slightly firm, but seems to be made of flexible ribbed rubber to allow it to lie flat against your body, but also allow for breathing (the ribs) so it doesn't get too hot. This is a nice design touch. There is also a shoulder strap which you can easily attach using loops on either side of the pouch. While this is a nice addition, I'm not sure if it's meant to substitute for wearing the pouch or augment its stability since the flaps will be slack and flapping a bit if you wear it as a shoulder bag (there is no way to secure them).

All in all, this is an excellent pouch which I think will work well for longer hikes which require a few more provisions, but do not quite require a full backpack.

Note: I was given a sample of this product in exchange for my assessment.to secure them).

All in all, this is an excellent pouch which I think will work well for longer hikes which require a few more provisions, but do not quite require a full backpack.

product_title: CrowsRock Outdoor Waist Pack Bag - Camping, Hiking, Cycling, Climbing - Belt Bag Pack Cover (Black)
review_body:
Very nice outdoor bag. It's like a MUCH nicer version than a fanny pack. It is practical and has different compartments to take what you need for a short stroll around the block or even hours of hiking. It has two pockets for water bottles. This is great for longer walks. It is light, it only weighs 13 ounces when empty. The straps are quite adjustable and they fit up to a 42 inch waist. The quality of the material is good and all stitches are well reinforced so no need to be concerned of tearing. The zippers are plastic with a metal slider. The bag I received has some red accents that make the bag look so cool - like some of the customer images.

Product provided for testing purposes.

product_title: CrowsRock Outdoor Waist Pack Bag - Camping, Hiking, Cycling, Climbing - Belt Bag Pack Cover (Black)
review_body:
The company sent me this in exchange for my review.

I really like this item--it's very handy, if you do anything outdoors. Why lug a day pack when you can strap this around your waist and forget about it until you need it?

It's roomy--there's space for two water bottles on either side--and you can pack a lot into the main compartments, which also have zippered sections to keep everything organized. Waterproof and well-made,this should last for many camping trips and hikes.

It's also very cool looking. The one the company sent me is black with red trim, not what I expected but it looks sharp.

product_title: CrowsRock Outdoor Waist Pack Bag - Camping, Hiking, Cycling, Climbing - Belt Bag Pack Cover (Black)
review_headline: Out Foraging - I now have plenty of room to pack much more and hands-free
review_body:
There has been some thought and design put into this bag to cover the expectations of those in search of tedious functionality of this bags intentions. I will list the pros/cons as I see detailed in this bag. However, I may not know the full reasoning for some of the functions but I have included pictures that will hopefully hope one who does know (yes, that is a brown beer bottle pictured in one side of the bottle holder, it was near for a picture so you get the idea).

PROS:

* adjustable main waist strap with a heavy duty clip and slides (?) that hold the remaining straps to your sides without flapping. They are both largely looped at the end for easy adjusting.

* sides are also adjustable once you load in your drink bottles, you can adjust them tightly to your hip so that they don't flop around

* drink bottle pockets have an adjustable elastic band at the top for either small or larger bottles (beer bottle in photo was small - it can take a much larger bottle)

* back of the bag and side flaps are covered in mesh, but inside the mesh is a waffle shaped material about 1/4" thick that seems to be for padded comfort and will definitely prevent whatever is in the larger inside pocket from pressing through uncomfortably into your backside

* two main compartments are double zipped and partially down the sides to easily flap open for quick access

* detachable shoulder straps with swivel plastic clips. Shoulder strap is adjustable and 1" wide without shoulder padding, so if this bag is packed and you use the should strap, it will dig into your shoulder

* a big hand carrying strap (I can fit my wrist through)

I have a small sort of pathetic fanny pack that usually only holds keys, phone, and doggy poop bags and treats. So I will be happy with this on my foraging escapades and will now have plenty of room to also pack some emergency medical supplies.

CONS:

* none

I was provided this sample for an honest review.

product_title: V28 Women Full/ankle Length Elastic Pleated Retro Maxi Chiffon Long Skirt
review_headline: I got the large and it fitted pretty much as I expected in the waist
review_body:
I am 5'5" and usually wear a size 12 pants. I got the large and it fitted pretty much as I expected in the waist. I really wanted to like this skirt, but I usually like to wear my skirts at my natural waist and I was hoping for something that would skim the floor when I wore it that way without shoes. Then I could wear it with heels and they would just barely peek out. When I pulled it up to my natural waist, though, this skirt hit me around the ankles. With heels it would be too long to be a midi skirt and too short to be a maxi. It's like the skirt version of highwaters. If you're like 3-4 inches shorter than me, you're gonna love this length, but I do think it's expected that clothes will fit someone of average height (5'4"-5'5") unless otherwise stated. So that's minus one star for me.

The other star I took off of this dress was for the slip. This skirt is chiffon and the description said "three layer design" so I wasn't sure what to expect in regards to see-through-ness. It turns out that the three layers are the full, flowy overskirt, a completely straight midi-length slip attached underneath that, and a completely straight mid-thigh-length skirt underneath that. Look, I don't know about you, but there's a reason I don't wear straight skirts. I find them really restricting! Imagine my consternation when I knelt down to pick up my cat while wearing this skirt and I had to hike up my underskirt to do it! Because of the slips, I find this skirt really unwearable for casual dressing. I'm going to have to rip out the underskirts and sew in a slip with more ease to be able to wear this skirt.

product_title: Classic Men's Holeless Leather Ratchet Click Belt with Automatic Sliding Buckle - Trim to Fit
review_body:
*UPDATE* I no longer recommend the buckles that go with these belts. If the buckle has a comma shaped lever, it will probably break while you're wearing the belt and you will be trapped! Seriously, stick with SlideBelt. It's the best design; you simply lift the buckle cover and it releases the belt.

Having started with SlideBelt, I was looking to replace my black belt minus the buckle. The price for a leather strap was $25-30, so I looked at some recommendations and saw these EazyBelt offerings. I ordered this and a saddle brown belt, because I figured for $19 I couldn't not try these out when they include a buckle. The leather is bit shinier than I'd like, but seems very decent for the price and the buckle works quite differently than the SlideBelt. A little lever must be actuated on the bottom edge of the buckle in order to release the belt. In some cases you must push in toward the buckle with the belt ot make this work, but it's just a matter of getting used to it.

The buckle is quite handsome, and quite heavy. But, value wise, I don't think you can beat this.

review_headline: By far my favorite pair of fun socks
review_body:
I've always been a sucker for fun and creative socks & these are by far my favorite pair. I am honestly impressed with the quality of these socks since I have found a few in stores that just looked like they would fall apart after one wash but these ones seem to hold up very well. I really like the fact that these are ONE SIZE so I didn't have to do any guessing on if they would fit our not & unlike other socks they don't have any obvious markings where your toes & heel would go (MAJOR PLUS).

I'm not sure if these socks were meant to be reversible but since both of the sides (front & back) are a little different I like to switch it up a bit and one day I may wear them both with the galaxy swirl in the front, one day with it in the back on both feet or even do one with the swirl in the front and one in the back.

I love these socks so much I am going to be purchasing a pair for my niece who has asked for mine so we can match when she comes back down to visit.

product_title: Galaxy Print Graphic Crew Socks - One Size - Purple Crazy Sock for Any Occasion!
review_body:
I don't understand people who wear boring socks. Even if you have to appear stodgy and straight laced for your job, socks are one area where you can go wild and express yourself without any problems. Plus it just feels nice to have your toes covered in fun. These galaxy patterned socks are my new favorites. I love studying the planets, stars and universe. Now I can literally have the stars at my feet. The colors are vibrant and pretty. The fabric is soft and breathable. They feel nicely made and like they will last. They do fit exactly as described, coming up to about mid calf. I'm a size 8 shoe and these were perfect.

review_body: Got this shirt for my girlfriend. I was worried about sizing, because you never know even with sizing charts. But, it fit just as expected. If cleaned properly there is no shrinking and the shirt hasn't shown any signs of issues after a couple washed. The only crappy part is that the current seller, the only one for the item, ships from China, so it takes awhile to get and the price is somewhat high. product_title: RFID Blocking Mens Leather Zippered Wallet
review_body:
I've had this only a few days. So far it seems to be okay, but I'm disappointed it is a rather tight fit in some of my pants. (Talking about the wallet.) It is snug, but fits well in my jeans. In some of my dressier slacks the pocket is apparently a bit narrower, making it difficult to insert and remove. Also, although I wanted this model specifically for its numerous card pockets, when those pockets are filled with credit cards, various membership cards, etc., the overlapping bulk of those cards makes the wallet bulge in the center. I'm concerned I may see cracks begin to appear at the top of some of those cards because of that.

Overall, I like it. The price is right, and the quality seems to be decent enough. However, the jury is still out on whether this will loosen up over time, fit more readily in (and out) of my pockets, and/or damage any cards. I will revise or append to my review in time.

product_title: DesertWolf Vintage PU Briefcase - Shoulder Messenger Bag - Cross Body Bag
review_body:
What a classy looking briefcase/bag. It's thick PU leather but it smells and feels like real leather. There's room inside to fit my 14" or 15" laptop plus there's a padded pouch inside to carry smaller laptops or tablets. It has an attached handle and an adjustable strap that can be attached so it can be carried over your shoulder or across your body. The outside has two zipper pockets, one in the front and one in the back, and they would both fit a cell phone. There's also an open pocket in the front. The inside zips and then the leather flap folds over and has faux buckles that actually snap. The stitching all looks good and I didn't find any coming apart.

This is a very professional looking briefcase and I really like the vintage style (maybe 'cuz I'm vintage myself). :-)

Product received for my honest review.

review_headline: Great but a little big if your short.
review_body: I purchased these at a discount in exchange for an honest review. You have to keep in mind these are novelty socks so they are not super soft there are a lot of threads inside. I purchased these for myself and my Whovian daughter to share. She is five foot one and I am five foot three. On her they were practivally thigh highs. For me they went to the knee but were uncomfortable as I have bigger calves then my daughter. I could not wear these all day she she could. So she gets to keep them. I must mention these also are great for crafting. I use these types of socks to make arm warmers and baby legs.

product_title: Doctor Who Knee High Tardis Socks - Shoe Size 4-10 - 2 Pairs
review_body: As a Whovian who used to sit in my room late at night with a little tv with rabbit ears not moving so I didn't lose the signal just to watch my favorite Dr.  I was ecstatic to be able to get these socks with a small discount in exchange for a review.  I honestly don't wear socks a lot.  But between myself and my children these socks will be worn constantly.  I selected my pair and my daughter has selected hers. I did get more than just this set.  I acutally went ahead and bought other pairs as well.  Gotta be stocked in the Dr.  Very good quality. Arrived very fast.  Very impressed with this purchase.

product_title: Doctor Who Knee High Tardis Socks - Shoe Size 4-10 - 2 Pairs
review_body:
These are as cool as The Doctor! (Ten, of course. No arguing with me on this.) Okay, maybe not as cool. But when he shows up for you (finally!) in the TARDIS, he'll know he's among friends. These are officially licensed and nice quality.

The only gripe I have is while these fit my feet just fine, my calves are ....not tiny. My other Doctor Who socks (egads I'm a geek) are much stretchier and fit my calves with no problem. These are made of a cheaper fabric that doesn't stretch nearly as well, so the graphics look bad and the threads are complaining by the time I get them on all the way. If you are say in the 150lb or lower range without large calf muscles, you should be fine. Otherwise, I would stick with the less than knee high ones because these are just not gonna work.

I received this free or virtually so for product testing and review. I am under no obligation to provide a positive review and receive no incentives or rewards for doing so. My aim is to highlight features and drawbacks that I would want to know about as a buyer, not hype the product for the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.

product_title: Doctor Who Knee High Tardis Socks - Shoe Size 4-10 - 2 Pairs
review_body: These socks are super cute.

product_title: Doctor Who Knee High Tardis Socks - Shoe Size 4-10 - 2 Pairs
review_headline: Great of socks for you, or your companion.
review_body:
This is a great two pack. My wife loves fun socks, especially knee highs. With both of us being huge Doctor Who fans, I couldn't pass these up.

Based on the tag, I would believe these to same set of socks I could purchase in one of the stores in the mall that caters to the younger alternative crowd. The material is stated as being 97% polyester and 3% spandex. Spandex must do wonderful things, I don't remember my 70's clothes being so soft. Luckily, they stretch well too! The Heel and toe seam appear to be very solid.

Upon opening the package, my wife (approximately 5'8") immediately slid the TARDIS blue knee highs on. Normally wearing a women's size 9, they fit her feet very well, leaving the top of the sock about an inch or two below her knee. So far, after working a shift on her feet they've held up beautifully. I was lucky enough to receive this product at a discount for my honest and unbiased review.

product_title: Doctor Who Knee High Tardis Socks - Shoe Size 4-10 - 2 Pairs
review_headline: Finally Doctor Who socks that the Tardis is not covered up when wearing shoes!
review_body: I recently ordered some custom designed Doctor Who shoes for my daughter who is obsessed with everything Doctor Who and the moment I saw these knee high Doctor Who socks I knew that would go perfectly with the shoes. With many decorative socks most of the decorative part ends up covered by your shoes but with these knee high socks the Tardis is nicely placed at the top so it will still be shown off when wearing shoes. These are official Doctor Who socks with the BBC logo on the packaging. These will be a great gift for my daughter and I know she will wear them every chance she gets. I received these Doctor Who socks at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

product_title: Dare Color 6-Pack one-size-fits-most Low Cut Socks Size 6-12 100% Money Back
review_headline: Comfy, cool, good stretch, and extra support through the arch area
review_body:
These socks are great. So comfortable, and they lend support where you need it. There is a different weave around the sock at the area where it hugs the arch. Several areas of the sock provide a bit of compression--without being confining. They stay put and do not slide down at the heel and do not twist--anywhere.

I like the three colors in this set of six--the two grays especially, although the dark blue are always useful, too. I thought the darkest color might be too hot for summertime heat, but these socks were comfortable all day. The material wicks away the moisture of sweating feet. With a regular pair of socks, when I take them off they are damp. Not these: No dampness at all. No odor at all. Nice material!

I am always a bit leery of "one-size-fits-all", especially if the product comes from China, but it is a perfect fit for a Men's 11D shoe size.

*I received a free sample product from Dare Color.

product_title: Dare Color 6-Pack one-size-fits-most Low Cut Socks Size 6-12 100% Money Back
review_headline: Nice Socks But Very Low Cut
review_body:
These are nicely made socks that fit my wife (size 7) really well. She thought they had a nice amount of support but felt they were a little bit too low cut. There is no way these would have fit my size 15 feet and I am surprised that they are recommended for men with up to a size 12 as they seem way too small for that.

The instructions say to hand wash and not to machine dry. Since we received a pair in order to review them and there is no way I'd ever hand wash and dry socks I decided to see what happened to them when they were put through a washer and dryer cycle. Overall, not much. They seemed to come through the washing just fine. Maybe it will lessen the life span of the socks but I can't really tell a difference.

Overall a decent pair of socks that my wife said would be perfect if they were cut just a bit higher.

I love these footies. They look so cool - that gray, yellow / green, and black combination is awesome. These are very low cut socks. They are super soft and feel great on my feet.

There is only one small thing, they run a little bit small. I have a size 11 1/2 foot that's pretty wide. So call it, I'm a big guy. One footie had a little trouble staying on my heel. If you have smaller feet, they will work fantastic. My wife tried these and they fit perfectly. So big guys - maybe choose a different brand.

I still love them. They washed up beautifully, no shrinkage or elastic damage.

product_title: Low Cut Socks Dare Color 6-Pack One-size-fits-most Durable Athletic Socks
review_headline: no dryer thing - that isn't happening in my house
review_body:
When I package arrived, it was in a bubble wrapped kind of box thing - very unusual - I wasn't even quite sure what was inside. When I opened up the wrapper, I found a regular box with six pairs of rolled socks inside. They were clipped at the top and the bottom holding each pair together and there were two white, two gray and two black. While they were different color, they were identically styled. I immediately popped them in the washer as I was doing a load anyway, and then moved them to the dryer without reading the instructions that suggest that you air dry them and not dry them in the dryer. Lucky for me, they came out just fine and don't appear as though they've done any shrinking.

They were "one size" socks and are supposed to fit womens size 7-13 and mens size 6-12. I'm a woman and I wear a size 8 (US) and they fit me just fine. They weren't tight, but they didn't slide around either, so I was happy with the sizing. They were thicker than socks I usually wear for running, so I will be using these for household chores and other around-the-house kinds of things. I could even see wearing them to go hiking or long walks or even shopping at the mall and I do like that there are a couple pair in each color so I can wear them in various leisurely settings.

They are made of cotton, lycra and elastic so I'm sure that's why they have such a good fit. It will be interesting to see how the color holds up after several washes. Oh, and back to that "no dryer" thing - that isn't happening in my house so if the socks fall apart, I'll definitely update this review!

I wore the socks for an entire day and my feet stayed dry and weren't all sweaty, so they do what they are made to do. At $13.99 for six pairs of socks, these socks are a great price too. They are well packaged (although the outer shipping packaging was a little weird).

A complimentary product was sent to me for evaluation. I have no connection to the seller and my review is based solely on my honest review and unbiased opinion.seller and my review is based solely on my honest review and unbiased opinion.

product_title: Low Cut Socks Dare Color 6-Pack One-size-fits-most Durable Athletic Socks
review_body:
This pair of Dare Color one size fits most socks may not work well with many types and/or brands of shoes. The back really is exceptionally low cut and does not have any sort of pull tab. I wear a women's size 9 shoe and the back of the sock can creep halfway down the back of my ankle.

I found the socks to be lower than the backs of several pairs of my shoes. Since they are predominantly cotton, they are more likely to absorb rather than to wick away moisture and thus are likely to ride even lower into closed shoes. I found that they do work well with clogs where the open back allows me to pull them up in back.

I always throw socks in the washing machine before wearing and did measure the socks before and after. I found there was no shrinkage after a normal cycle cold water wash and air drying.

Disclosure: A complimentary product was sent to me for trial and evaluation. I have no connection to the seller or the manufacturer and my review is based solely on my perception of the merits of the product.

product_title: Casual Socks Dare Color 6-Pack Dress Sock -One size fit most, Multicolor
review_headline: As Socks Go, I'm Liking These Very Much
review_body:
A number of years back, we decided to do away with all of the carpeting in our home and, instead, put down either marble tile or wood flooring throughout most of our downstairs. Basically, this change was largely due to our developing allergies … and having four cats (at the time) certainly contributed to our desire to better manage the hair shedding going on throughout the place. As we soon learned, tile and wooded floors tend to be much, much cooler on our feet, so we had to subsequently invest in some nice house slippers as well.

However, I’m not like my wife, meaning that I’d rather forgo the heavy slipper and get by on a pair of socks during the colder months of the year, and that’s why I’m totally loving these lightweight socks from Dare Color. Unlike most athletic-style anklets, these socks are exceedingly lightweight, feeling practically paper-thin (in a good way) on my feet and toes. They’re certainly snug, but the fabric breathes so much that I liken them to feeling similar to that “cooling fabric” that’s making waves in the marketplace these days. They have just enough give to be easy-on-easy-off, but there’s a great stitching in through back end to give just enough support needed for my use (and abuse) around the house.

I’m aware that some of the drawbacks to the entire “one-size-fits-most” issue may be a bit offputting for some consumers. I wear a size 9 (mens) and my wife wears a size 9 (womens), and these fit our feet perfectly with enough give (as I mentioned above) not to feel tight or confining in any way. If you’re a size eleven or twelve (mens), I’m not entirely sure it’d be as wonderful for you, but might I suggest picking up one pair and giving them a try? Pricewise, they’re certainly very affordable, and I’ll be picking up a few pairs myself for the days ahead.

Because – as I said – I need just a touch of warmth around the house and I’m no fan of anything heavy, these socks from Dare Color are exceptional.

Highly recommended. Honestly, I probably get more excited over a good, comfortable pair of socks than most – so if you’re anything like me then you’d do yourself well to pick up a pair of these from Dare Color. They’re spiffy!

In the interests of fairness, I’m pleased to disclose that the fine folks at Dare Color provided me with sample testing product of their One-Size-Fits Most socks by request for the expressed purposes of completing this review; and their contribution to me in no way, shape, or form influenced my opinion of it.re exceptional. Highly recommended. They’re spiffy! product_title: Casual Socks Dare Color 6-Pack Dress Sock -One size fit most, Multicolor
review_headline: Good quality athletic short ankle socks.
review_body:
The moment I tried on the one-size-fits all unisex Dare Color socks, I knew that they were not for me. They were very tight on my size 13 feet. I passed them on to my wife who had no difficulty fitting her size 10 feet in them, put on her sneakers and off she went to tennis.

My wife wore the socks all day long - during 3 hours at tennis, ran a few errands, which was followed by a couple of hours of yard work. She reported that her feet remained dry without any discomfort. The socks were odorless at the end of the day.
It is a bonus when an item delivers what it promises. These socks are simply good.

They are ambipedal (same on both feet). The combination of different materials, seamless construction and anatomical contouring with targeted reinforcements provide great comfort while avoiding rubbing, chafing and foot blisters. The socks are available in one blue color and design. The package says "Hand wash and do NOT tumble dry" but the sales promo says "machine-washable and tumble-dry". That is "wishy-washy" to me!
In my opinion, these socks were not meant to fit anything larger than an 11 size male foot. There are similar athletic socks on the market of a more superior quality but are also more expensive.

I received a free coupon for a complimentary sample provided for testing & evaluation, but with no obligation to write a review. This is not a barter deal. I have no financial or personal connection with the manufacturer, seller or their employees.

product_title: Casual Socks Dare Color 6-Pack Dress Sock -One size fit most, Multicolor
review_headline: Nice socks -- ignore the washing instructions
review_body:
These Dare Color socks are very attractive, they fit well (I'm an 8.5), and they offer some minimal arch and foot pad support. I wore them on my regular morning walk, and they felt good and stayed in place (no slipping down inside my sneakers like with some no-show socks). Initially, I was skeptical because of the washing instructions included with the socks - the label on the packaging suggests that they can't be machine washed or dried without risk of shrinking. But I ignored the instructions (which said the socks should be hand-washed and hung up to dry) and tossed them into the machine with the rest of my laundry, and then dried them in the dryer. And there was no shrinkage at all. Yes, the socks felt a little bit snugger when I first put them on after they came out of the dryer (as happens with any knit fabric), but they quickly stretched to fit my foot. So ignore the washing instructions and treat these as you would any socks.

That's important, because there's no way I would ever hand-wash and hang-dry a pair of socks (who would?). But now that I know they can be cleaned along with my other laundry, I can enjoy wearing these socks. And so can you.

I can't attest to whether or not the socks are truly \\"one size fits most,\\" but they're good on my 8.5 feet (and my husband had no trouble getting them on his size 12's, although he did say they felt snug). For me, the socks seem to mold themselves to my feet in a way that's very comfortable. I was wearing them around in the house this evening without shoes, and I almost forgot I had them on.

Bottom line, these are very nice socks. They are more expensive than I'm used to paying, but the $7 per pair price isn't unreasonable (but I do wish they came in multi-packs at a lower price point). I do recommend them

review_headline: (1) Pair of LOW cut socks, One size fits all - Soft, good quality socks - Fit over my swelling feet without any pain!

Stretchy, soft and very comfortable low cut socks - 1 pair, one size fits most!

My feet swell often and when this happens I have no choice but to go without socks because I can't find any that will fit me, until now. The stretch in this pair of socks is amazing, they go right over my swelling feet without being tight and hurting them.

product_title: Casual Socks Dare Color 6-Pack Dress Sock -One size fit most, Multicolor
review_headline: the low-cut socks were good for a workout
review_body:
This review is for the low-cut socks.

My feet are women's size 7 and these fit. They were maybe just a touch loose, but they didn't move around in my shoes. So they would definitely fit larger foot sizes (though probably not smaller ones).

I used them during a workout. I felt that they absorbed sweat fairly well (they are 70% cotton, so that is to be expected) and they weren't scratchy or anything. The dye is fixed and did not come off on my feet.

Mine seemed well-made, with no holes or loose threads. (I prefer ankle socks like this for working out.)

My socks came with instructions that said to hand wash and hang dry. I have to think this is just a misprint -- mine have survived in the washer (on cold with like colors) and dryer (tumble dry low) a time or two. If something happens and they begin to fall apart, I will update the review. But for now, they are looking just fine. I also note that the product page says to machine wash and dry.

Overall, I was happy with these. There weren't any major flaws and I felt like they did a good job of keeping my feet dry while I was working out.

product_title: Veluxio Premium Money Belt For Travel
review_headline: Love my Veluxio Premium Money Belt
review_body: I need something to go walking with and going on vacation with that I don't have to carry so I can have my arms and hands free and can do whatever I want when I want to without a bulky heavy purse. The Veluxio Premium Money Belt is perfect for me because I can put it around my waist and clip it on and put whatever I need,such as credit cards, phones,cash stuff like that and take off and do what I wants with out that bulky purse or carrying a wallet and risking everything to fall out. It has zipper pockets to zip your stuff in and keep it safe. This is not uncomfortable at all. I think its very comfortable and  can barely tell it is on me when I'm out. I love taking it with me when I go on my walks now because my phone fits in it and so I don't have to worry about dropping it and I have my cash so I can stop by the store and pick me up a water:)  This has helped me out soooo much!!! I can't wait to take it on vacation with us:) I received this at little to no cost to me to provide my honesta nd unbiased opinion and that is exactly what I have done.

product_title: Veluxio Premium Money Belt For Travel
review_body:
When my elderly father was in Ireland a year ago, he was pickpocketed while touring a cathedral. After learning that, I looked in my local stores for a money belt for him and wasn't happy with the ones they sold. I found a nice one for him on Amazon, but he has since misplaced it. Recently, I was given the opportunity to try out the Veluxio Premium Money Belt and I was happy to see if it would compare. It's made out of a waterproof nylon material. The material that lays against your skin is a softer, material. It's surprisingly comfortable. I put it on one morning and went about my day. I forgot I was even wearing it until I was getting ready for bed. It's easy to adjust for all sizes. There's plenty of room for your travel essentials such as ID, passport, credit cards, money, & room key with a little extra room if needed. All the zippers are strong and secure and move easily. I will definitely be sharing this one with my Dad for his next trip!

*I received this money belt for the purpose of trying it out & reviewing it. My thoughts & opinions are my own.

product_title: Veluxio Premium Money Belt For Travel
review_headline: Very happy with this Veluxio Travel Gear Money Belt
review_body:
Very happy with this Veluxio Travel Gear Money Belt. It is very comfortable which was one of my concerns. Was able to adjust it.
I was also pleased that it was zippered as opposed to Velcro. Stays a lot cleaner without all the debris that attaches to Velcro.
I also felt safer with my money and personal items tucked away, best of all I was hands-free. Great bag, going to order one for my Mom who travels!

product_title: Veluxio Premium Money Belt For Travel
review_headline: perfect size for his cards and passport and it looks ...
review_body: I am so excited to give this to my Dad for a birthday gift.  He is going out of town soon and he always used to make my Mom carry his important things---not anymore!! This money belt is thin, perfect size for his cards and passport and it looks much more classy.  It comes just as pictured and shipping was right on time.

product_title: Veluxio Premium Money Belt For Travel
review_headline: Super recommend for the practical people.
review_body: Loved it. I am not skinny and I was wondering if I would be included in the users of it. Yes, I was. Loved all about it. I can now go to the supermarket, visit my friend, go out with my hubby for shopping and feeling practical, prompt and safe. I love in a smaller town now, so not too much paranoia now a days, but the practicality is still important to me. Real purses, just for social events for me. No more abandoned purses in the supermarket cart or anywhere.

product_title: Veluxio Premium Money Belt For Travel
review_headline: Secure your important items using this circumspect money belt
review_body:
A discreet money belt like this is one of the essentials for travelling. I’ve had friends who have gotten their pockets picked and wallets and items swiped while they were travelling in Europe. Good thing I was offered this product for testing and review, so I won’t have the same problem.

This particular Money Belt by Veluxio has the necessary amount of space for storage of important items—money, passport, important documents—while still being hidden enough that people won’t realize you’re actually toting money underneath your clothes. The material is comfortable against your skin.

The material of the belt is not quite waterproof, but it does protect your items from a little dampness, such as sweat or minor drizzling. However, anything more than that, you might want to further protect your items by putting in zipped bags before putting them in the money belt. The strap is elastic and is adjustable. There is a plastic clasp that you can click into place when you put it around your abdomen. The clip and strap seem to be a little weak, and I’m not sure if they will hold during extreme situations. However, this money belt is good enough for leisurely activities and travelling, so I am content with it.

I do wish that this money belt came in more skin-toned colors, like beige, grey, peach, or brown so they blend better with your skin. If I’m wearing a thin light-colored shirt, you can still see the black color underneath it. This would probably work best when you’re wearing dark-colored clothes if you want to be very discreet.

product_title: Veluxio Premium Money Belt For Travel
review_headline: So much better than a fanny pack, super discreet!
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:1b42f351d843ee8f613f0263cc21fb34]]I hate bringing my purse with me when we go out to like an amusement park or an all day trip. Purses get pretty heavy after lugging them around for a few hours and unfortunately they are all too easy to misplace. I wasn't completely sold on the idea of a money belt....it screams fanny pack circa 1990 to me, but I decided to go ahead and give it a shot.

I'm kind of surprised by how much I love this. I can put it on under my shirt, it's not super noticeable, it's comfortable and it solves the problem of where to safely carry my stuff. We're planning a family trip to Graceland next month and you can be sure I will be using this, and the best part is no one is ever going to be able to tell. This is great for obvious reasons, but also from a safety perspective.

It's also very well made; it has plenty of pockets to store miscellaneous items too. Obviously the more you put in it the more noticeable it will be. I think you could easily store cash, credit cards, and id's without anyone being able to tell you have it on. I definitely recommend this for traveling!

I received this product for free in exchange for my honest, unbiased review.

product_title: Veluxio Premium Money Belt For Travel
review_headline: This Veluxio Premium Money Belt is Great for Traveling and So Much More!
review_body:
This Veluxio Premium Money Belt is Great for Traveling and So Much More!
I walk about a half mile to the grocery store and I love that I can hide this Extremely Well Made Money Belt under my shirt without an obvious bulge.
I feel so much safer than when I used to bring my purse and it leaves both hands free to carry my groceries back home.
The overall 10" Wide x 5 1/2" Deep size offers Plenty of Storage Space!
There is a 9" Wide x 4 3/4" Deep Zippered Compartment on the Front of the Belt, which includes 3 Inner Compartments that measure
3" Wide x 3 1/2" Deep each.
They are the perfect size for carrying my ID and Credit Card.
The Pocket is plenty big enough to carry my Cell Phone and House Keys with room to spare.
Under the Top Zippered Pocket is Second Zippered Pocket which measures 7" Wide by 3 1/2" Deep.
Both Zippers are Sturdy and Easy to open and close. Veluxio has attached a 2" Fabric Zipper Pull to each Zipper Tab, which prevent me from having to search for the small metal tab when I need to retrieve the contents.
The 3/4" Heavy Duty Elastic Waist Band features a Thin, but Sturdy Length Adjuster Tab, as well as a Sturdy Buckle for securing it around my waist. The Buckle offers a Textured Release Button, so it's simple to locate and unlatch without looking at the buckle.
Stitching is solid throughout and I appreciate that Veluxio has secured Both Ends of the Elastic Directly into the Money Belt's Seams with a double row of stitching.
I really love that the Back of this Money Belt is covered in a Super Soft Netted Fabric to prevent skin irritation and sweating when wearing the belt against my skin.
It gets pretty hot throughout the summer months here in Florida and it's nice to know that I don't have to peel a sweaty, sticky money belt off my body when I return home from walking outside.
I have also used this belt for my walks on the beach and it's Water Resistant Qualities are a plus, because I have no worries about the mist off the ocean damaging the belt or it's contents when wearing it over my bathing suit.

review_body: One of my favorite aspects about this dress is the length.  I love dresses, they are so comfortable and classy, but I often find that they are made to come above the knee.  I love that on me, this dress falls about mid calf.  I think that that is a perfect length and it is appropriate for any event whether it be more casual or dressy.  The slip under the lace if very comfortable and soft.  The lace is gorgeous!  Very intricate and such a beautiful pattern.  It is sturdy and well done, not easily frayed or pulled.  The top of the dress if fitted to the waist and then flows down loosely from there.  The waist features a long ribbon that decorates the waist nicely when tied into a bow.  The neck is a sweetheart neckline that accentuates the chest area very well and gives this dress an even more feminine and elegant feel.  I really like the high neckline with the lace.  It is a conservative dress without being too conservative with the see through chest and upper back.  The back features a zipper that goes down to about the hip area.  It is a high quality zipper that moves easily.  This is a beautiful dress that compliments the body very well!  It would be great for just about any occasion. product_title: Leward Mens Casual Slim Fit Cotton Solid Multi-Pocket Cargo Camouflage Shorts
review_headline: Good build quality; nice look and fit (provided you up-size)
review_body:
I’m very pleased with these shorts. The build quality is quite good considering the price. There were a few loose/dangling thread ends (mostly on the inside pocket flaps and at the leg ends) that needed to be cut, but overall, the stitching was tight and even.

The fasteners on the leg and back pockets are snaps, and are of good quality. The waist fastener is a post and loop rather than a snap. The post is of decent quality (a bit lightweight, but OK). However, the loop (the hole the post goes into) is cut a bit small. It’s a little tough to unfasten at first, but after it breaks in it gets better.

The waist is the only area where the build quality could be better. It’s rather thin, which is good for comfort, but also makes it a bit prone to rolling a little. It could have used some facing or thicker material to give it more strength and rigidity.

The fabric is soft and, according to the product listing, is 100% cotton. It feels like cotton, but there’s no product tag that lists the fabric composition.

The fit is good provided that you order a size LARGER than you need. For example, I normally take a 34 waist. I got this as a 36 and the fit is fine. Very comfortable at the waist, and fits well in the seat without being baggy or too tight.

The legs are cut so that they are right at the knee. The overall look is very casual, so the cut is appropriate. I have it in gray, and I really like the color -- it's a blue-gray that goes with pretty much everything.

For the price, these are a solid value. Look nice and casual, fit well, and are decently made. The few build quality misses brings my rating to 4.5 stars, but I'll round up since I like the casual look.
[Sample provided for review]

product_title: Leward Mens Casual Slim Fit Cotton Solid Multi-Pocket Cargo Camouflage Shorts
review_headline: A decent pair of shorts with 1 big shortcoming  (shameless pun)
review_body:
UPDATE: After many weeks of wearing, the shallow pockets have finally gotten to me. Downgraded to 3 stars.

Original review:

I've been wearing these shorts all week, and overall i can say i like them, my overall feeling is 3.5 stars. I was offered this product in exchange for my honest review. It was definitely my style, so accept i did! Here's the thoughts:

-Overall construction feels good
-Fabric feels soft, tag says 100% cotton
-Styling is nice, good amount of details and character
-1 Button snap came broken
-1 Button snap is weak
-The zipper is cheap, can catch on itself.
-Main Pockets are rather short, regular items stick out when sitting

The pockets
These are the main reason for a star deduction, i have a regular wallet, and a droid turbo/5ish inch phone, and both have a tendency to stick out of these pockets. See the photos, i took that after making sure the wallet was as deep as it could go. They really should add a full inch to the depth.

The zipper
It seems like it's an older stye zipper, all metal and with that ancient tiny thin metal pull tab. It's not a big deal, it just tends to not zip up/down smooth/easy all the time and can be annoying/finicky.

Broken snap
Lemons happen, and i can live with it, but still worth mentioning. If you look at the picture you can see that inside the snap there is only 1 bar, there should be two, and thus it cannot snap.

If half stars were possible i would deduct a half for the zipper and broken snap, in this case i like the product enough to lean towards 4.

For the price i would say they are a fair deal, i've certainly had both better and worse in terms of quality in my short purchasing ventures.

product_title: Leward Mens Casual Slim Fit Cotton Solid Multi-Pocket Cargo Camouflage Shorts
review_body:
░░░░░DECENT OVERALL BUT SMALL POCKETS░░░░░

❖ These shorts are light weight and breathable. They are good for wearing in hot sticky weather because they will stay cool.

❖ The fabric feels very strong, though it's not very thick. So while it feels durable it won't offer any protection if you're wearing them while hiking and stuff.

❖ They fit as expected. The sizing is reliable.

❖ They do not come with a belt. It says NO BELT in the description but the pictures show a belt. This is confusing. But it does NOT have a belt with it.

❖ The one thing I don't care for is the pockets. They are tiny. I am only talking about the main side pockets, the ones you would put your hands in. They are barely big enough to fir your hands. A smartphone doesn't fit all the way in them. If you don't carry stuff in your front pockets, this it not a big deal at all as these are fine shorts otherwise. If you like to put anything in your front pockets, these are not for you.

I was sent a sample of this product at no cost for the purpose of thoroughly testing and reviewing.

review_body:
Looks good, great price, only minor qualms. Slightly small fit - please not the Casual Slim Fit really means just that. I'm 34 and the 34 waist works, but the fit over all feels a bit tight rather than the relaxed casual feel I was hoping for from the photo.
Ties on the legs are decorative tassels, the legs aren't long enough for them to matter - I'm 6'1''
NO BELT - I didn't read closely enough, my bad, but the photo was mostly why I bought this.
Small side pockets have been mentioned, I'd have to agree. Keys, chapstick, etc. fall out when I sit down if I keep them there, but...well, cargo shorts - plenty of pocket options.

One review showed bleaching/staining - my color was consistent, but I do want to note the shorts came out of the sealed plastic wrapping DAMP. No strong chemical or mildew smell, just damp and easily dried. Dunno how this happened, but seems like maybe there are missing QA steps from manufacturing to shipping that caused this and other quality/blemish issues reported in other reviews.

I would have liked to try the 2XL to see if being a little tighter would help - but decided against it because the cup sizes would likely be smaller on a smaller size and the cups on these barely make the cut. I'd say this particular bathing suit is perfect for someone with a full C or a small D cup. Also, try and get one that's tighter on you since it will definitely stretch out.

product_title: Miusol Women's Vintage Audrey Hepburn Style 1940's Rockabilly Evening Dress
review_body:
I ordered this on Thursday night and got it Saturday morning. The shipping was so much faster than I'd hoped!

The only negative: When I got it out of the package, it was pretty wrinkled and the fabric is kinda cheap-- it's the tiniest bit shiny in the light and the littlest bit plastic feeling, but nothing that wouldn't be anticipated with a dress priced so low. I dot think anyone near you would noticed unless they touched the fabric, so it will just be your little secret. The fabric is very, very sturdy and all the seams are straight, and that's what matters for my purposes. It also has the lace collar attached to the dress thoroughly, not just sewn on at the top, so it won't flop around or roll up. It also came with an extra button in case you lose one.

Further, the dress fits really, really well! I am a size 6 with a 34D, so I am generally a S/M, and the medium was expectedly a bit large. However, this dress is made from stretchy fabric so it fits but doesn't cling to my curves.

But I bought this dress for work (I'm a teacher) and I don't like my work clothes to be too form fitting. Further, the dress is very sturdy and I know it will stand up to hours of use and abuse and will probably stand up to some scrubbing when I get coffee and pen on myself.

In the end, I giving this five starts because it's perfect for the price and it's just what I expected.

product_title: Red Hood Mask Deluxe Cosplay Helmet Teens Adult Halloween Costume Party Accessory
review_body:
After deciding that I was going to do my first cosplay for the upcoming Boston Comic-con, I thought that Red Hood would be a great choice of my first cosplay character. The costume seemed easy enough if I could just get the helmet right. I first searched through all of the options Etsy had to offer, and while some of the options looked absolutely amazing (almost movie-prop worthy), I wasn't ready to spend over $250 for something I would wear for one or two days. I then searched Amazon, not expecting much, and to my surprise found this relatively cheap option by Xcoser. Given the price difference between this one and the aforementioned Etsy options, I was a little skeptical. I'm glad I took a chance though because it was totally worth it. Here are some of my notes:

Perfect size: This was very important to me. I had seen some pictures of other Red Hood cosplayers with HUGE helmets that looked kind of ridiculous. This one might be tight if you have a larger sized head but it looks very proportional.

Eye Holes: The eye holes give the helmet a similar look to the comic and animated version of the character (which I really like). It does limit your visibility a little bit though. I think it would look weird without it though.

Comfort: It is relatively comfortable as is, although I plan to add a little bit of padding on the inside. It is made of a lightweight flexible plastic, so it is probably not going to be as hot as if I wore something made of a heavy foam or fiberglass.

Appearance: It looks great, even for plastic. It has a nice shine to it, similar to ones found on Etsy made of fiberglass. My only complaint is that it was a little warped when I took it out of the box. A couple of minutes with a hairdryer should fix that.

As an added bonus, it even includes a free microfiber face mask (similar to a balaclava) and a xcoser keychain.

If you are looking to do Red Hood cosplay and don't feel like shelling out $250+ for something on Etsy, this is definitely the way to go.

review_headline: thinking I would choose the one I like and send the other back but

The only fit issue I had was in the shoulders which were a bit loose and baggy but this is a common problem for me as my shoulders are narrower and slope more than average (took a sewing class and, for the first time, discovered why I had this problem so often!)  The dress material is very clingy and feels a bit 'polyestery' but it's not unbearable, just don't expect a nice, soft jersey...the only other thing I would add is that the bow on the green dress is not a satiny, filmy material as it appears in the photo - it is made of the same material as the dress so isn't quite as dressy but it's still very cute.

product_title: Aocome Women's Print Sun Dresses Long Holiday Party Wedding a Dress Maxi Clothing
review_headline: This dress is absolutely beautiful. The material is super soft and hangs smoothly
review_body: This dress is absolutely beautiful.  The material is super soft and hangs smoothly.  Since the dress is one size, it will fit differently depending on your height and chest size.  I got this dress for my granddaughter.  She is about 5'4", average weight and large chested.  The dress is cut low, so if you are large chested, it will show more cleavage.  Since she is short, the dress was a little long so she wore boots with heels.  It is really about a Small/Medium size dress.  The middle is a wide, soft elastic that stretches, so you don't have to be super thin to wear it.  There is a fair amount of room in the hip area.  I love the design and lace accents.  It does not wrinkle easily, so it would be perfect for travel.  My granddaughter is totally in love with this dress and so am I.  I received this product for free or reduced price in exchange for my unbiased review without compensation.

product_title: Aocome Women's Print Sun Dresses Long Holiday Party Wedding a Dress Maxi Clothing
review_headline: BEAUTIFUL dress, sizing chart needs work.
review_body:
Disclosure: I received this free in exchange for my unbiased review. A VERY pretty and well made dress which I would have love to have worn but it was WAYYY to small on the top. Although I did look at the sizing chart which said a specific weight you really can't tell by that. I was under the weight suggestion however if you have a larger chest this will not fit you. I am 38DD and my daughter is 34C and it did not fit either of us. Made for the thinner woman which is fine, as I said it is SUPER cute. Just bummed that once again my chest comes between me and a pretty dress.
Otherwise looks LOVELY but this company DOES need to get a better sizing chart online which is the ONLY reason I give it less than 5 stars. Just not enough info to go on.
Love the dress, not the fit.

product_title: Aocome Women's Print Sun Dresses Long Holiday Party Wedding a Dress Maxi Clothing
review_headline: STUNNING but Not for every body type
review_body:
I was so excited to review this dress. It is absolutely stunning in person. The back is exquisitely designed with the lace flowers. The material for the is soft, cool, and flowy. The decorations are beautifully done and awesome colors that mesh well together.
When I put the dress on I knew I was not getting it over my breast. I wear a DD so that is always and has always been a major problem. But I tried very hard just to see. The dress would fit beautifully if it would go over my bust and is very long. I'm 5'8 and even with the hang up on my top it is almost to my ankles.
The top is very small I'm thinking the biggest bra size would be a B possibly C cup. Because of the way it's made the top has NO give what so ever which is a shame because the bottom is very flowy and the middle is stretchy. I sadly will never be able to wear this stunning dress. I was never small chested even at my smallest weight. But I gave it 4 stars because I LOVE it, it's beautiful and it's not an average dress. It's just not for my body type but it does not claim to be. It is one size fits all -- that should read most and I have never been one with that sterotype type body.
If this helps I wear a Large/ XL dress most of the time. I am a 38 DD and I'm 5'8 so maybe that will help you decide if this dress would be right for you.
I BEG Aocome to make this is a bigger size or even in sizes! I would buy it in my size immediately. I was very upset to see it didn't fit me. I received this product complimentary but the opinion expressed is all my own.

product_title: Splendid Exchange Tote Handbag, 15 inch
review_headline: Love this tote bag!!! Spacious and Durable!
review_body:
This is a great tote bag! I have been looking for a smaller tote for a "diaper bag". This fits the bill. I took it on vacation with me and used it to store things for walking down the boardwalk and ride area. I placed 6 diapers, a travel size wipe container, Snacks, my wallet, hand sanitizer, my phone, my camera and a bunch of other things. Nice durable material and i think will wash very nicely. AND some red soda spilled on it, and i wiped it away and only a few drops were left. I am going to wash it soon. I would like if the front pouch had a button for closure or something along those lines. But works just fine as is.
I did receive this at a discounted rate in exchange for my honest review.

product_title: Splendid Exchange Tote Handbag, 15 inch
review_headline: Not your cheap Tote Bag - Nice High Quality and well made!
review_body: I have been looking for a nice summer bag to carry items to our boat.  I do carry a big canvas bag but was looking for something smaller that could hold my wallet and keys and phone because they get lost in the big bag.  I was pleasantly surprised of the great quality of this bag and the Turtle is really nicely printed on.  The bag is well made and the straps are long enough to throw over my shoulders while I am carrying the other big bag. I have a ways to walk on the dock so I appreciate that it is very comfortable to carry.  When not in use it folds nicely.  It is the perfect size for me can hold a lot more than my wallet, keys and phone but not be too bulky.  I did receive this Tote Handbag at a discounted price for my honest review.

product_title: Splendid Exchange Tote Handbag, 15 inch
review_headline: Durable, thick bag with lovely graphic
review_body:
Even though I had read the dimensions of this tote before ordering, I was still pleasantly surprised by how spacious it is. The straps are generous and stitched into place with care - no danger of these pulling out under a full load of groceries. The design is crisp and well defined, befitting a much more expensive tote. The canvas feels high quality and durable, capable of bringing home the bacon - literally. If I decide to use this for a book bag, I'll be able to fit my phone and keys in the front pocket easily (I'll probably use some velcro tabs there to keep that pocket closed - I'm addicted to velcro!)

Even though the canvas is durable and thick, the tote itself folds easily for storage or fitting in the other grocery totes —or will carry several more totes inside.

Full Disclosure: I received a generous discount in exchange for a fair, unbiased and honest review, which I am very happy to provide.

product_title: Red Hanger Women's Stylish Solid Long Maxi Skirt - Made In USA
review_headline: I LOVE THIS MAXI SKIRT, IT IS VERY FLATTERING
review_body:
I love this maxi skirt by Red Hanger. I am curvy and petite, and this works to make me feel all pulled together without looking heavy. The maxi skirt is very comfortable and soft, and I love how the material glides over my hips then falls straight. Most maxi skirts I find flare out from the hips and it overpowers my small frame. The waist on this skirt is one of the fold over styles that is very common on yoga pants. It can be worn unfolded so the skirt looks high waisted or you can wear it folded over and let it sit on your hips. I personally like it folded over and sitting on my hips. Maxi skirts are my favorite thing to wear, as I can wear flats or heels. I can dress maxi skirts up or down, depending on what mood I am in. I am very pleased with this skirt, it is well made ( I checked the stitching-all was in place and tight), and flattering.
I purchased this product at a reduced price in return for an honest and unbiased review. I based my review on my own use and opinion of the skirt.

product_title: Slim Mens Wallets for Men - RFID with Strap Money Clip - Premium Quality
review_body:
Sadly unoriginal. This is confusingly similar to the Wally Bifold introduced on Kickstarter in January of 2014. What you see here, a billfold with simply two pull-tab pockets and money clip, didn't exist before my company (Distil Union) raised funding from our passionate Backers. Huskk has copied Bellroy and other designers before -- I guess Nate Justiss, my co-founder and the designer of Wally as the sole industrial designer of our tiny team, should be flattered they've copied us... but we are not flattered. Huskk even claims "We designed a rare and refined wallet" -- when in fact it is very clearly a copy.

CONS:
- I received one of these in the mail yesterday and can tell you, it feels like a cheap copy of the original Wally Bifold.
- The pull-tabs are strangely rigid, you don't receive the same satisfying tactile feedback Wally offers (we are informed and intentional in our material choices, for good reason).
- Wally offers organization at a glance, which this does not.
- This listing is for something that's doing a poor impression of a product we as designers have worked diligently to refine based on actual user feedback.

PROS:
- The box is nice (so is Wally's)
- It makes a great gift (as does Wally)
- Ordering this Huskk wallet will save you a few bucks -- but you will get what you pay for as your money goes to a company whose credibility is questionable at best.

Huskk: I invite you to regain integrity by taking down the pull-tab version of this billfold, which you claim to have designed when clearly you have not. Your second version lacking pull-tabs or money clip is perfectly fine, as it is your own take on the classic billfold. Knockoffs and copycats are all around, so why put effort into your brand (claiming to be "free thinkers" bringing "NEW" products using "honest materials") when you can't possibly be proud to stand behind it?

product_title: ABUSA Men's Breathable Cotton Relaxed Fit Casual Work Cargo Pants
review_body:
Low Rider - the second I put these pants on I thought of that song by War - Low rider don't drive too fast. I'm a 42 waste - yeah a guy that big shouldn't wear low riders. You guys that big, you know that. Low riders are for 32 and under waists. Slim guys that have something good to show off, not a belly.

Actually these fit incredibly well. The legs are really relaxed fit - they weren't snug at all, good solid fit. They are a good healthy 32 inch length. The waist was true to size - I didn't order a size larger like recommended in the sizing chart.

The material is thin cotton. That was clear in the description. These are summer pants. The construction is good and solid. Just because the fabric is thin, it doesn't mean they are cheap pants.

And the low rider - you can cover that up with an untucked shirt. Just don't let that shirt flip up to show off your plumber butt. Because, you are showing off your back parts with these.

The one thing I didn't like a lot - the two front pockets are tiny. My iPhone 6 Plus didn't fit in them. Yeah, I could drop it in the cargo pockets. And maybe I shouldn't have so much junk in my pockets.

All my friends know the low rider

Low rider is the one to meet, yeah

Low rider don't use no gas now
Low rider don't drive too fast

Just keep that shirt untucked you big guys. Nobody wants to see that crack in back.

product_title: Demarkt Men's Underwear Breathable Briefs G-string Thong Grey
review_body: My waist is 32-33, and the mediums fit me just fine. (11/19/16 Update: they changed their size chart - I would order 'Large' now.) I searched hi and lo for replacements for my King Style jocks. These Demarkt jock straps (they are NOT thongs) are super comfy, stretchy, minimalist yet solid, and durable. These jocks sport well-sculpted pouches, nothing too exotic. I've machine-washed my first pairs dozens of times with no physical degradation except a slight color fade. I order a pair or two every month or so, and will keep doing so until I have a whole drawer full of them. These are mesh, which means that in certain weather conditions (hot humid days do it for me), depending on how your skin responds to temperature and humidity, tiny nodules of your skin will get stuck in the pores of the mesh. I've worn many styles over the years -- and all mesh briefs are subject to this; when it's hot and humid, I have to peel the fabric away from my skin to regain total comfort maybe once or twice a day. In all other weather, it doesn't happen at all. 'Great product' I'm happy to report.

product_title: Mrignt Mens Casual Jogger Sweat Pants Cotton Active Elastic Waist Running Sports Trousers
review_headline: Ordered for my husband, but I'm keeping them for mysel!  So comfortable! Soft fabric, big pockets, comfy elastic waistband!
review_body:
I was excited to order these Mrignt sweatpants, knowing that my husband likes sweats that have elastic at the bottom so they don't drag on the ground. Now that I've received them though, I am totally claiming these pants as mine - he can fend for himself! The Mrignt sweatpants are amazingly comfortable, with a soft cotton fabric and elastic drawstring waist. I like the broad elastic bands at the ankle - they keep the pants from dragging down by my feet and also help to keep my legs warm, since no cold air is going to draft up the leg of the pants. I absolutely love that these have large, easy to access pockets - I don't understand why designers assume that women's clothes should have tiny pockets or none at all, so it is great with these that I can actually store things like tissues, my keys, or anything else I need handy while I'm lounging around the house being comfortable. I chose the light blue color, which I'm really happy with. It looks very much like a standard denim jean color, and I like the contrast of the grey pockets and waistband. I am definitely going to get a lot of use out of these pants - I may end up using them as pajama pants as well!

I'm very glad that I was able to order this as a free promotional sample in order to evaluate and provide my honest review.

product_title: Mrignt Mens Casual Jogger Sweat Pants Cotton Active Elastic Waist Running Sports Trousers
review_body: I was going to get these for my husband and these are for men.  He said he didn't want them.  His loss as I went ahead and got them for myself.  Girls are always swiping guys sweatpants to wear so why not?  So glad I did.  These are so comfortable.  They are made from 100% cotton.  I got them in a medium since they may shrink a bit.  They fit great.  They are a loose fit style but taper a bit down the leg going to the ankle.  This is why my husband didn't want them.  He's doesn't like that cut. product_title: Time Dresses Valveless Sequins Embellished Waist Sheer Bridesmaid Dress
review_headline: As soon as I opened the box my excitement turned to disappointment, This dress does not look as beautiful as ...
review_body: I tracked my package and when I realized that they did deliver it just to the wrong porch I was as giddy as a kid in a toy store. As soon as I opened the box my excitement turned to disappointment, This dress does not look as beautiful as the online pictures do. It is very poorly constructed, strings are hanging everywhere, the ends of the straps are hanging out of the back of the dress and only stitched on with on little stitch. The belt was embellished with tacky looking beads and sequins. The picture showed little jewels. I was expecting the dress to be a little more form fitted to myself since I measured myself, man was I wrong! The waist is a bit tight and the boob part is huge and I'm pretty busty. I am going to try and fix this dress myself in hopes to have a nice dress for a wedding but I have learned my lesson. All in all I will never purchase from this seller again.

product_title: Time Dresses Valveless Sequins Embellished Waist Sheer Bridesmaid Dress
review_body: Time Dresses showed excellent customer service by replacing a dress that did not fit with one that was customized for my measurements. The first dress I ordered did not fit right because it ran smaller than I expected. A small (size 4-6) was too small in the chest area for me because I have a 36" chest measurement. Since I live in the United States, I was not required to return the first dress due to high shipping charges. Not only did they make the situation right but, they were also efficient in replying to my emails, and always maintained a professional attitude. I am very happy with this customer experience, and will definitely order from them again in the future.

I was so excited to get this item and was lucky enough to receive a complimentary dress in the black color for evaluation and review. I tried it on as soon as I could get it out of the package and the large size fits my 5'6\\" frame almost perfectly (I might have been able to wear the medium after all -- be careful and be sure to look at the chart on the product page to select your size). It's just a little big in the bust and around the waist, but better than too tight (in my opinion).

I love the heavy and stretchy feel of the material and the cap sleeves. The garment is really attractive and quality made. You'll need to hang it to get the wrinkles out from the packaging, but I used a steamer and hung it in the bathroom and it turned out great. The retro style and the length of the dress suit me perfectly, and I can't wait to wear it. I'm currently looking for the perfect belt to emphasize the waist of the dress and to jazz it up just a little. I really wish I could have this in every color on offer!
