product_title: Anni Coco Women's Elegant Neck Pleated Bodice 1950s Vintage Swing Dress
review_body: My daughter is all about vintage style clothing which means that I'm always on the lookout for affordable retro/vintage clothing for her. My daughter had been looking at this style of dress for some time, so I was quite happy to get a discount on it and provide feedback.  Based upon the other reviews, I went ahead and purchased a size larger for her than she would normally wear. She normally wears either a size 6 or a size 8 depending on the fit of the dress. The large dress fit her perfectly. She's now on the look-out for the perfect belt to add to the dress for a pop of color and flair that fits her personality. She loves the fit and feel of the dress which says a lot since she's very sensitive to how fabric feels against her skin.  This dress looks fun and the wrap around collar adds a bit of class and extra detail to it. The hidden zipper gives a polished look to the back of the dress. The high quality fabric with durable seams and even stitching makes the dress feel like a more expensive dress. Also take note that the different colors of dresses are made of different fabrics. The black dress is 97% cotton and 3% spandex which creates a comfortable and form fitting dress with a slight give to the fabric. The dress does attract hair like crazy, so keep that in mind if you have pets like we do. The dress is machine washable, so you don't have to worry about getting it dry cleaned.

review_headline: good quality but runs way too small.
review_body:
I received this dress at a discounted price in exchange for my honest opinion. And honesty, this is a nice quality , good dress that runs way too small. I usually wear L or 12, in some small cuts 14. I read some of the reviews before picking a size and decided to pick XXL rather XL. It fits me but barely. I need to be a size medium in order to be comfortable in this dress. In other words, if you are usually wearing medium M, then order XXL and you should be very comfortable. For bigger gals like me, it fits but when I wear it, I feel this immediate urge to loose 10 to 15 pounds.

That is said, it is a very beautiful dress. The chest part, the bustier is beautifully draped, the fabric is nice and airy. Its length is ideal. I am 5f 7 and the skirt ends on my knees. The cut is actually flattering . The waist sits in exactly the right place, just below the ribs hence even if you are not super shapely like I am, it gives a nice contour to the body.

I wish they were making these a little but on the normal sizes or larger since the cut, the quality , the shape is really really good.

The fabric has a good amount of stretch to it, there is a zipper down the back, but with the stretch I was able to get the dress on & off without having to deal with the zipper.  This dress is not lined, except in the bust (see picture) but the fabric is thick enough where your under garments shouldn't be showing through.  The quality isn't as good as an Emily & Finn, modcloth, etc, but for the price it is just what I expected.  There are some random loose threads and a couple of the seams aren't 100% matched up. product_title: Women's Smocked Tube Strapless Jersey Wide Leg Pants Plus Jumpsuit Playsuit USA
review_headline: Super Soft Material and Very Comfortable!
review_body:
This Maitai Womens Strapless Wide Leg Casual Tube Jumpsuit is super cute. You can wear it for casual or dressy as well. The top has an elastic tube top type material at the top of it to hold it up with quite a bit of stretch to it. The stretch is not too much though where it does stay up and you don't have to worry about it falling down. There is also elastic at the waist. The bottoms of the legs are flare and this truly is a great jumpsuit. All the stitching on it is done well. They recommend to hand wash but I put it in a delicates bag on delicate cycle in my washer and then line dried and it came out just fine. Material is Polyester and Spandex and is nice and soft and feels very comfortable on your skin and to move around in.

My only downside to this is I personally thought it ran small. I wear a 2X top (16-18 in pants) and I checked the size measurements before ordering and the 2X should have fit me per the waist and hip measurements. If anything, the bust area might have been a little snug. Unfortunately, it was a little smaller on me than I would have preferred and should have ordered the 3X so you may want to order a size up. I had my sons fiance put it on so I could at least take a few for you all to see of it on and it actually fit her fine and she normally wears a large. The length was great on her too and she is 5'4" but was a little short on me and I'm 5'7". Other than the sizing, this is adorable and comfortable.
**I received this product with a promotional discount in exchange for an honest and unbiased review. No compensation for a positive review was provided. All of my reviews are based 100% off of my experience with the product and I never guarantee a positive review.ether or not to purchase a product and appreciate the feedback. Thank you for taking your time to read my review!

product_title: Women's Smocked Tube Strapless Jersey Wide Leg Pants Plus Jumpsuit Playsuit USA
review_headline: Cute & Comfortable Tube Top One-Piece but Order a Much Larger Size!
review_body:
I was so excited to get this jumpsuit. There are several cute colors to choose from. I decided to pick with my favorite color to wear black since it’s supposed to be a slimming color. This jumpsuit runs very small. I ordered a much larger size than normal and it still didn’t work for me. I do have a hard time with one pieces like this because I am fairly tall. I have a long torso and long legs, not to mention a large bust. Unfortunately this top did not have enough room for me. When I pulled it up where it needed to be, the crotch was too tight. So I probably needed to go to an even larger size which is a size that I would never have to order in anything else. I normally would wear a large or XL in most clothes. I ordered a 2X in this jumpsuit. These problems can all be corrected by just ordering another size up. One other thing about this jumpsuit is it’s not a great length for tall people. While I wear around a 33” inseam, this jumpsuit has a 29” inseam. It’s very short on me.

Measurements for 2X

Top Elastic Band: 12.75” wide and 2.375” tall

Top/Chest Area: 17” wide and 12” tall

Waist Band: 13.5” wide and 1.75”tall

Inseam: 29”

Bottom Leg Width: 17.5 wide

Other than the sizing problems, this jumpsuit is really soft and lightweight. I love the wide leg with the cut hem on the bottom. I ended up giving this to my sister who is much shorter than me. She really loves how comfortable it is. It definitely looks much better on her. I just don’t think my body frame is made for a one piece. I really wanted this to work for me. So make sure you order probably a couple sizes larger than normal and make sure a 29” inseam is long enough for you. I’m not basing my review on it not fitting my body but rather how this actually fits on the appropriate body type. This is really adorable with a cute belt. This can be casual wear or even dress it up. I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.or my honest and unbiased review.

review_body:

You could wear it by itself, put a top over it, put on a cardigan or shrug, fold down the top and just use it as pants. The list goes on and on!

I knew from reading through reviews that I would want to size up and I made the right choice! I normally would wear a XXL, but went ahead and got these in 3X and they are a nice comfy fit.
I also was worried about how I would look in flared pants, but love how fashionably chic these are.
The fabric is just super soft, stretchy, and allows you to move around or "flow" around more accurately.
I doubt there is anything more comfortable you could wear to do yoga, excercise, or anything else.
The material is quality with no loose threads. Length is just to tops of the feet, can roll the waist down to below hips, or over hips, whichever you prefer!
Love these so much!

*provided for my opinion and review

product_title: Women's Wide Leg Palazzo Yoga Fold Over High Waist Jersey Stretch Comfy Pants USA
review_headline: So comfy and lightweight. Perfect for a hot summer's day.
review_body:
It is so hot this summer, jeans are just sweltering when you are in the hot sun. I needed a nice light piece of clothing that didn't make me burn up. These wide leg yoga pants are my favorite new article of clothing. They have that new style no-elastic waistband that you can just fold down instead of having a horrible elastic line. I wear them everywhere!

The fabric is super soft and very stretchy. It is comfortable and forgiving of my post-partum body (especially since it is black). They would actually be quite comfy when you are pregnant too. It is quite lightweight, which is perfect for being in the hot sun for many hours.

I like that they are wide leg so they don't look like the typical legging style yoga pants or tight leg with a slight flare yoga pants. These actually look more like real pants, but have the comfort of yoga pants.

All in all I am very happy with my super comfy new pants. I'm so glad I received this item for free or at a discounted rate in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. I couldn't be happier with this product.

product_title: Fruit of the Loom Men's Boxer Brief (7 Pack)
review_headline: They're okay. Just not the best underwear I've gotten from FOTL
review_body:
I ordered the striped boxers and they showed up fast and were exactly as advertised. So why the three stars?

First...this is not "striped fabric" but rather white fabric that's silkscreened with stripes. And it's thin cotton, which makes it feel a little fragile.

Second...I'm well within the 2x range for the underwear, so the waist elastic is fine, but when I pulled these on they didn't really fit my body shape very well. They kind of grind to a halt about an inch below where my waist normally sits. I don't know if it's because I have thick thighs or whatever.

Finally...and there's no polite way to say this...but they're a little stingy in the front. If you have a lotta "potato" in your pants, these squash'em down a little.

In conclusion I don't think I'll order underwear online again. I need to try on a pair before I spend 30 bucks again.

review_body:
I was extremely surprised by this shirt. Picture does it absolutely no justice. I am 5'4, 105, 32/26/32, Ccup and this falls below my hips.. which is good, because even though I am relatively short, I have issues with most tops being too short for my taste.

The tag says it's 95% Modal and 5% spandex, lol whatever Modal is, and it is so soft and so comfortable. also fits me exactly as pictured, with the boat neck almost shoulderlength apart. it's a very flattering fit, for me anyway. I am pretty fussy about tops and tend to return more than I keep, and this was not on prime, so I knew I would end up having to keep it anyway.. but even if I could return this, there is no way I would. I am blown away with the quality of the shirt. sounds funny because the shirt is so plain and basic, but somehow, it all pulls together very nicely. it's also kind of shiny due to the material, which is cute. it's not your typical cheap rayon shirt; this should last sometime. I would wash it in the machine, but I'm not sure if I would dry it. The material doesn't wrinkle anyway, so there's not really a point in putting it in the dryer. I buy many items from sourpuss, but this is by far my favorite :)

This black leather wallet has RFID protection which works best when closed. There are 24 vinyl windows for credit cards, a driver’s license or other ID. It does not contain a place for coins so it is more of a wallet for men than women as I don’t know of a gal that carries coins in a pants pocket.

The instructions say to spot clean the wallet when needed but doesn’t say what to use. I would think a good leather cleaner would work.

4.5”x 5” is the size of this wallet. That makes it too big to for me to carry in a jean’s pocket but it would fit in my purse. I could carry my credit cards, restaurant gift cards and all those store rewards cards we all have and I would only have to search one place.

Size and capacity, as well as the leather feel are as advertised. It does fit comfortably into the front pants pocket and is relatively flat. I basically have all of the slots filled with credit cards / id cards withj the majority doubled.

Only negative at this point, is whether the slots (lightweight clear plastic) will hold up ... removal of a credit card is a tad difficult when you have two (back to back) in a slot. Would have preferred an millimeter of two of added space in each.

Will update in time.

review_body:
I LOVE IT. I was looking for something similar as my cards get damaged in normal wallets. In normal wallets, your card goes in horizontally in a cascade fashion. When you sit or bend, the stress is in the center of the card, causing damage and discomfort. In the Wonder Wallet, your cards go in vertically, so when you put it in your pocket, they fit horizontally to your body, the stress is between two cards, and the wallet flexes. So your cards are much less prone to damage and the wallet is more comfortable in your pocket.
*Tip: The cards fit tightly into the plastic. Cut a small wedge in the plastic so that you can grip the card easily with your thumb and finger and slide them out.

product_title: Ross Michaels Mens Leather Bifold Wallet
review_headline: Nice leather, but very few card slots
review_body: I received this item at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.  I was surprised when this wallet arrived in a mailing envelope without a box or anything, which would be a consideration if you are buying it as a gift...not very nice presentation. The leather itself feels like a good quality and well made, but there are only 3 integrated card slots (plus the ID window), which is rather disappointing.  They do include one of the flimsy plastic inserts to hold more cards or pictures, but my husband can't stand using those for his card storage. Overall this is an attractive wallet that could easily be much more functional.

product_title: Ross Michaels Mens Leather Trifold Wallet
review_body: It's a little larger than I expected but not overly large. There are 8 slots for cards plus one for I.D and three pockets for your 'secret' notes. Mine is chocolate brown and very soft and supple.  Very nice.

product_title: PattyBoutik Women's Cowl Neck Button Sleeveless Top
review_headline: Great material, stunning bold piece, and just perfect feel
review_body:
Gorgeous top. Heavier than it looks in the pictures, as everyone in the reviews stated. At first I thought it was too big for me and feared I would have to go through the tedious return process. Luckily though the top slide on perfectly and rested a little past my hips to a comfortable resting on my belt line. The buttons make the top pop and fascinated my son to no end. I thought the buttons would be tiny but they Re just the opposite in fact. I love the top and sincerely hope it does not end up tearing anytime soon.

The cowl part is in a gorgeous swoop downward on the chest area. Not alot of material is dragged down like some cowl neck pieces making it easy to even remember that the top is cowl neck at all. I bought the dark blue and it comes as a solid navy blue color.

This is my third piece by Patty Boutik and I fully plan on buying several more pieces now that I see their clothing is great material and holds true to the size ordered.Good job Patty, be prepared for a customer for life!!!

review_headline: These days with fringes in style this is the perfect top for the summers
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:53ec74af365c5cc87aa1cb52d4157fdb]]These days with fringes in style this is the perfect top for the summers. Its simple gorgeous. I love the detailing at the ends with the fringes well sown in place. The top comes just above my knee.

The top is white in color so you can pair it with any color bottom if you wish. You can wear it with jeans or shorts or just wear an inner and you are ready to go. It also would look great as a beach wear to cover you up.

The material is very comfortable. It has elastic at the waist line to accentuate your waist and make your figure look good. You can also tie any design belt to make this look even more stylish.

Sample received at discount or no cost for honest opinion.

product_title: Little Smily Women's Loose Fringe Hem Chiffon Long Sleeve Cover-ups Tunic Dress
review_headline: You can easily dress it up or down based on the occasion
review_body:
With a scoop neck line and a fringe hem this shirt looks the absolute stunner. I am a US size small and I got in 2/4. It fits me appropriately. The shirt reaches the top of my thighs. It can be worn with a pair of jeans or shorts and with a blazer or cardigan. You can easily dress it up or down based on the occasion. The waist is cinched so although the design of the shirt is loose, it gives the body a more fuller shape. Overall, the quality of the material is good. Chiffon is the best summer and fall time cloth. The stitching is seamless without any noticeable loose threads. I would definitely recommend this shirt.
Sample provided without any obligations.

review_headline: Amazingly comfortable pants. The material is thin and breathable
review_body:
Amazingly comfortable pants. The material is thin and breathable, but at the same time does a great job fitting snuggly to every curve on my legs. These are great for jogging and biking, because they reduce skin irritation and rubbing. So far with the cooler mornings (50-60F) I've been able to wear these just like basic tights under my shorts for early-morning biking, but I think if the temperature drops lower as winter approaches, I'll have to switch to an actual cold-weather style tights.

These pants are very thin and not meant to be worn alone. Definitely need to wear something over these as every crease, bump, and line is visible.

product_title: Mens Socks, Fun Socks 2 or 5 Pairs of Sox Per Gift Box
review_headline: For the young at heart – and spirit!
review_body:
MODERN MOTIF has produced some color in our life! These ‘power socks’ (not sure whether the company means visual POWER or refers to the fact that these spandex blend socks make your feet more powerful….) come in a wild variety of colors and patterns reminiscent of younger days when argyle socks were the rage and the socks worn by Dr. Seuss’ characters were a topic of fun conversation.

At any rate, the socks come five to a package, all rolled to show off the patterns and colors, and are made of 80% cotton, 17% nylon, and 3% Spandex. One size fits all – as long as your shoe size is between 8 and 12 probably 99.9% of men. The consistency of the material is lightweight yet substantial enough to give a comfortable cushion and arch support while remaining ‘breathable’. Another tricky little bonus is that the socks are anti-bacterial and have woven in moisture wicking properties.

Try them for casual events first and if the reception is positive, go ahead and make a statement at work. Or…you can always pass them along to your sons or grandsons.

All lighthearted kidding aside, these are genuinely high quality socks. You just made need cojones to put them on for that first outing. Grady Harp, August 15

product_title: RFID SAFE Alpine Swiss Men's Leather Wallet Hybrid Bifold with Flipout ID
review_headline: Nice feel, good quality. Missing a feature or two, but I'm hoping I'm protected.
review_body:
My first day of owning this wallet, and my impressions so far:

PROS- soft, nice leather. Folds pretty flat if you don't have too much in it.

The main reason I bought this is because I'm 99% sure that someone filched my credit card info by walking up to me with one of those scanners while I was at a St. Louis Cardinals baseball game. I live 3.5 hours away in IN. And 1 or 2 days after the baseball game, someone used my credit card to try to make 2 purchases at a Home Depot in a suburb of St. Louis. No, I was never there. The first charge went through at Home Depot (over $200) and the second charge attempt at the same store for over $500 was declined. The credit card company didn't make me pay, of course. But there was a big hassle in contacting all the companies that I have things auto-charged to. So, I'm hoping this works for the reason I got it: RFID protection.

CONS: I am hoping the leather loosens up a bit. But the credit card slots on one side of the wallet are smaller than the slots on the other side of the wallet. A card that slips in smoothly but snugly on one side has to be forced into the slot on the other side.
And I should've looked more carefully before purchasing this wallet to see if there are any others that have a zippered slot where the money goes, or at least a divider of some sort. This one does not, and I already miss not having that. I did make this wallet purchase in a hurry because after the credit card hacking incident, I had wrapped my cards in aluminum foil, a real hassle.

product_title: UV 50+ Side Snap Talson Sun Bucket Hat
review_headline: Nice feature for some I'm sure
review_body:
A bit tighter than I anticipated (L/XL size), and I don't need to cinch down the cord that allows you to reduce the effective hat-size. Nice feature for some I'm sure. I figure the hat will stretch a bit over time, so I'm happy with the size.

Material is nice, and the construction seems quite good. Lots of vents, so I know this will be my go-to hat when I'm active on a warm-to-hot day.

Another nice touch is the small(!) zippered pocket on the front for carrying something (a $10 bill for buying a beer at the end of a hike?!).

Overall, quite pleased with the hat, and I know I'll get years of use out of it. If I had to "complain" about one feature, it would be that the brim is not rigid (like a ball-cap) at all. Kind of makes it a crusher-style Bucket hat... and I'm fine with that.

product_title: Fastlace Silicone Moisture Gel Foot Arch Protectors Socks for Cracked Care
review_body: My son is autistic and was a "toe walker" until he was almost seven.  As a result he now has flat feet and requires inserts in his shoes to help build up an arch.  He is suppose to wear the shoes at all times when awake.  It's very uncomfortable for him to wear shoes all the time, so I bought these hoping he could wear them under socks and still have the support he needed without having to wear shoes while he's at home.  They are working so well - I couldn't be happier - neither could my son.  He is very sensitive to touch but the inserts are very soft and flexible while still providing enough support that he's building an arch without having to wear shoes all the time. I received a discounted price on this item in exchange for writing a review, but I am going to buy a few more pair, at regular price, because I absolutely love them.  They have made my son's life more comfortable, and mine much easier. I love this product and wouldn't hesitate recommending it to anyone.

I tried wearing them for a while, but they were just way to distracting at work. I had to take them off. The sleeves fit well, the pads were where the arch is (supposed to be). These just didn't work for me. They're not a bad product, & honestly I have to give a 4 star because they do exactly what is promised in the item description. They just don't work for me. product_title: Ekouaer Men's Stretch Cotton Underwear Sports-Inspired Boxer Brief
review_body:
My husband is very particular about his underwear as he dislikes binding, restrictive garments. His favourite style is brief or short-boxer, but he has a number of longer-cut styles as well. His main considerations are cut and comfort, and that depends a lot on the fabric. Out of the range offered to us for evaluation and review, we chose the smallest model of briefs, in a size Medium.

After a suitable testing period, my husband's view is that these are extremely comfortable, and the quality is excellent. The combination of 95% cotton and 5% Spandex is pretty standard and in this brand, it is very well executed, resulting in a breathable garment with enough stretch to fit closely to the body without being restrictive. The waistband elastic is supremely comfortable. The closed style at the front gives just the right amount of support. Sometimes what feels good standing up is not so comfy sitting down or when activity causes the skin to warm up and sweat. Today our outdoor temperature is 99 degrees F (36 degrees C) and the briefs feel great. One tricky area with briefs is the fit around the upper thigh. No problem here, the design allows movement while still remaining close-fitting, in fact these look and feel like a well-cut racing swimsuit more than bulky undergarments. Regarding size and fit, these briefs are on the small side, so if in doubt, you might want to try the next size up.

Regarding the colour, we chose the Blue and it looks just like in the photo, a dark midnight blue. The cut, however, is a little narrower; the picture of the white briefs is more representative. As for price, these compare very favourably with the brands we normally buy and, in particular, the pack of 3 represents great value for money.

product_title: Anni Coco Women's Sexy Backless Print Dovetail 1950's Vintage Swing Dresses
review_headline: This dress is well made and has gorgeous fabric
review_body:
I ordered this dress because I loved the pattern. The style is also very vintage, which appealed to me.
The first thing I noticed upon arrival is that the fabric was very nice. It wasn't thin or cheap. The dress is well made. The blue flower pattern is gorgeous in person. The image doesn't do the rich blue of the flowers justice, you'd have to see it in person! I also liked that the skirt has a lining underneath. I got a small, which I expected to be a little big on me, because it said it was for US sizes 4-6. I normally wear a size 2. I assumed I would have to alter it, but I usually have to alter all my clothes because of my size and frame. I was happy to discover that it actually fit me very well. The waist is a bit short on me, but I'm used to this due to the fact that I have a very long torso. Because of this, I will be wearing the dress with a belt to make sure the waist falls correctly on me.

One thing I'm going to change is the hem line. The skirt is a hi-lo skirt, which isn't my style. If you like hi-lo skirts, you'll adore it. I'm going to alter mine to be straight across the hem. I think it will be cute either way depending on your preference. The white of the back of the skirt will show for the hi-lo part. ( you can see this in the photo.)

Note: I received this product in exchange for a review.

review_body: I decided on this waist trainer as a followup to the Flexees Maidenform waist nipper (ordered it here for a GREAT price),  The flexees was more firm "fabric" instead of latex so it conformed to the body better and was less bulky.  You could wear it under clothes without it showing as much.  In my opinion, this made it easier to exercise in and I'm glad I started with this as my first waist trainer.  I lost about 3" with the flexees and it stretched out (and so did my weak child bearing muscles over time) and I needed a product that started off smaller.  This Ekouaer has latex as part of the construction so it fits tighter, like a girdle to start off and doesn't conform just holds you in...tightly.  If I would have started with this, I would have given up because it feels too much like a girdle.  But! After a few months wearing a waist trainer, this product help maintain my stomach pouch ( the muscles have been weakened).  This is tight so I haven't worn it long (say about 2-3 hrs.) yet so I think this will do the job.

product_title: EKouaer Women's Latex Sport Girdle Waist Training Corset Waist Shaper faja
review_body:
Well, wow. I was a bit leery about trying this, but I really wanted something that would FIRMLY hold my waist in, give me back support, and perhaps improve my posture. I ordered a size large after consulting with a company representative and providing my measurements and I would highly suggest you do that in order to get the right fit. The garment is TIGHT but it needs to be in order for it to give you that "girdle" effect that you are likely purchasing it for.

When it arrived, I immediately took it out of the package and sort of held it around myself. I was dismayed that even with the 3 rows of hooks, it took a lot of tugging for the fabric to come together. I stripped down to my underwear, determined to get this on. I was surprised to find that it fits totally under the bra, so be aware this is not a corset, but specifically for the abdominal and upper hip area. I started at the bottom of the garment puffing and pulling until I got the bottommost hook secured and then pushed and pulled and readjusted all the way up to the top on the loosest hook. Whew! But wow -- I had a waist!! A lovely waist with no muffin top at all.

It fits quite tight, but when I sat down I was still able to breathe and my stomach stayed tucked up inside the girdle. It is thick, so you can't wear anything that is skin tight over it because the edges will be obvious, but with my regular clothes it was amazing the difference in my look. The bottom can also curl up a little when you are sitting, but I just smooth that down as unobtrusivelly as possible. When I wear this, it looks like I have actually lost between 5-10 pounds around my stomach area.

Although as I said, it took me some effort to get this on, my hope is that one day I will actually be able to fasten this and wear it on the 2nd level of hooks. The material is stretchy and the garment is very high quality. I love the products by Ekouaer, especially because they are commited to getting you into the right size. I received this waist trainer for free for evaluation and review, but I can honestly recommend it to anyone looking to feel slimmer and look more curvy in clothes.is waist trainer for free for evaluation and review, but I can honestly recommend it to anyone looking to feel slimmer and look more curvy in clothes.

I woul definately buy this item again!

product_title: CharmLeaks Women's Pro One Piece Athletic Sports Swimsuit
review_body:
Fits nicely, and shapes my body very well in this one piece athletic sports swimsuit.
I am curvy 34-25-34, wear B, usually dress size 10. Medium fits me very well.
I haven't purchased a swim suit in years. I was very skeptical and dreaded looking at the mirror. But this suit fits like a light body shape.

I enjoy the way it looks. The basic color is traditional navy blue, the exact seawater color, making me integrated with water while swimming.
Highlight part is the moving water-like curve in the front, fairly energetic and dynamic. Also, the vertical curve shapes a long rather than a big body.

I love the way it covers. The materials appear to be sufficiently thick and constructed well. The wide straps and U back leave enough freedom of movement. Chest is padded with sponge and designed with strengthen support. I'm soft thru the hips and legs, and this suit does not make me bulge.
Very nice!

product_title: niceEshop(TM) Girls Adult Bowknot Princess Mesh Puff Tutu Skirt
review_headline: Poorly constructed - elastic waist not sewn properly
review_body:
The tutu was the exact gray color shown, was extra poofy, was not transparent, and was a good length (for a petite woman). However, the elastic band in the waist is not sewn closed properly. Normally when you buy a skirt or a pair of pants with an elastic waist, the elastic band is sewn shut/together at some point. This was the strangest I've ever seen: There is an opening in the hem, and the white elastic band jutted out and was looped on a black button. I thought it was weird, but was like, "whatever." Then, when I pulled it up over my lower legs, the elastic band just suddenly burst loose from this button set-up and went springing into the hem.

To fix it, I would have had to open up the entire hem, retrieve the elastic, sew it together properly as it should have been done by the manufacturer, and then resew the hem shut. This is far too much work to put into a skirt that I paid more than $5 for. The whole point of buying a skirt was to avoid sewing one myself.

I have no idea about the sizing/fit since I never got it past my lower legs, which are quite slim. The slightest amount of pressure/stretching made the elastic snap off the button contraption. I took a photo to show this oddity to you.

You should also note that there is a strong plastic / unpleasant smell on this skirt when you remove it from the packaging. You may need to air it out for several days or hand wash immediately. I was going to use it for a costume, so I wasn't too concerned.

product_title: Simplicity Women's Lightweight Fringe Modal Cashmere Large Scarf Wrap
review_headline: Very versatile scarf, perfect for every season.
review_body:
Extremely extremely soft.Made of 90% modal and 10% cashmere.It's 7 ft width and 3 ft in length. Material is not see through but still breathable.When I bought it I thought I will only be using it during winter as it's 60 degree in San Francisco right now but after seeing it I realize that it's so long and breathable that I can easily use in any season.
1.I love to wear my scarf in different styles and bunny ear and waterfall are my favorite, but I can't wear them with every scarf as these style requires a very long scarf.I was so happy with the length of this scarf, I can easily wear it in my favorite styles.
2.I loved the color it really compliments my complexion. Very pretty and vibrant dark red color.Looks very good and goes with almost everything.
3.As it's soft and breathable and not see through I also love to use it as a wrap up on swimwear.
4.Perfect to wear as shawl to complement your dress during breezy nights.

I would highly recommend it, it goes with almost everything.I got this at discounted price in exchange of my honest opinion.

product_title: Cocoship Retro Red Leopard Polka Floral Print High Waist Bikini Swimsuits(FBA)
review_body:
For the price, this is a great swimsuit. I'd looked everywhere in my area for a high waist bikini. I even tried Victoria's Secret online, but everything I liked was either out of stock or on back-order. When I found this on Amazon.com, I loved the look. I read size charts, which were confusing, and read reviews. I'm 5'2", and weigh about 165 (size 10-12). I'm very also top heavy, wearing a 36DD. Many women who are about my size said they ordered the 3XL, but the bottoms were a little loose. I went with the 2XL. The bottoms are a still a little more loose/less supportive than I'd like, and there was an area about an inch long where the outer layer of fabric had pulled apart at the seams, but nothing a few stitches won't fix. I may even try to put a hem on the sides to tighten it up. As far as the top goes, the cups fit perfectly, but, as a few reviews have said, they are a little far apart, at least for my tastes. Again, nothing a few stitches, or a cute retro brooch won't fix.

Overall, for the price, I don't mind doing a few tiny alterations, as they swimsuit looks great. I would have ended up paying more than double at VS for a similar suit, or at Target for something I wasn't as happy with. I'm only giving four stars, due to the fabric that had pulled away from the seams, and due to the confusing size charting. I'd say if you normally wear a 10-12, go with an XL.

product_title: YSJ Juniors Mini Skirt High Waist Floral Cotton A-Line Knee Length Swing Skirts
review_body:
I love the pattern, the colors are almost the same, the blue is a tiny bit darker than in the pics. The skirt has a nice body (it sticks out) like in the photo, and it stayed like that for the 4 hours I was wearing it. I think the style they're going for is like a stiff casual skirt, kinda like an uniform or something, what with the thick seams on the front and the belt hoops and big button, but you can't really tell, so it just looks like a nice "swing" style skirt, exactly like the photo.
The material is thin, cheap, and probably 50% elastic.
Because it's rather stretchy, it's not too uncomfortable, but I wouldn't reccommend buying one that was snug on you, even a little, because there isn't much material in the pockets, and if it's stretched it easily shows the lining of the pocket. it also bunched up on me, around the hips, because it was a bit too small. (See the picture.) I am usually a small in US size (2-6), and i ordered a medium.
It's not too bad, I'd keep it if it was my size. It's a flattering skirt, even from the side.
Just rememer it is pretty cheap. I'd say the pattern is the best part about the skirt.

product_title: Meaneor Women's Scoop Neck Maxi Long Dress with Elastic Empire Waistband Solid Black XXL
review_headline: Comfortable & Versatile High Waisted Long Maxi Dress
review_body:
This adorable Meaneor Maxi Dress comes in four fashionable colors. I chose the black dress. It feels like it’s made with a Rayon and Spandex blend. The dress is very comfortable and soft against your skin. It’s not too thin but not too thick either. You are not able to see through it. The material allows for a good amount of stretch.

The design of this dress is more of a high waist dress. The fitted top ends slightly below the bust area and not right underneath it. The skirt area is gathered at the top and has a slight loose fit flow to it. I’m 5’7” and this dress hits right under my ankles. I love the ¾ sleeves because I hate showing my huge arms.

Measurements for XXL

Bust: 18.5” across

Middle Bust/Waist Band: 16.5” across

Arm Length: 11.5” long

Arm Width: 5.5” wide

Overall Dress Length: 55.5” long

These are approximate measurements lying flat. The material does allow for stretch. I suggest going up at least one size large than you would normally wear. This XXL is like a US dress size 16.

Overall this dress is an excellent price. It gives you a long and lean look. This dress is very versatile. You can wear this casual with flip flop or dress this up with gorgeous jewelry and heels. It would be really cute with a fashionable belt or scarf. There are so many ways to change this dress up. The best part is, the dress is super comfortable. It seems to be great for all body types. I love my black dress! I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

product_title: Oiwas Light Weight Nylon Women Shoulder Bag Ladies Cross Body Bag
review_body:
This is a really cute Crossbody bag. It's cute and as soon as I took it out of the package, the first thing that I noticed was the super adorable key ring that comes attached to the side of it. I usually don't have accessories on my bags, but this one is staying there just because it adds a cute factor to it.

It is a really good size for daily use, the shoulder strap is pretty comfortable, I like the fact that it's adjustable easily, and that it has a really good extension. I like the extension part of it because if we do travel anywhere, I can extend it to attach to my luggage. Which is a REALLY good thing.

It seems to be really well-made, and although it's not overly thick, it will hold a lot. Well, a lot more than I thought it would. The zippers are kind of thing but seem to be in perfect working order.

I would recommend this.

I received this product at a discounted rate for an honest review.

product_title: Croft & Barrow Women's Swimwear D-Cup Classic Halter Tankini Stripes Multicolored
review_headline: The seller was fantastic at refunding my money
review_body:
This is NOT a D-Cup tankini. The cups are VERY small. It is a push-up top. There is so much padding that anyone with more than a small B cup will have cleavage to their chins and under their arms. The seller was fantastic at refunding my money. I think their description was a mistake, but since it is still listed this way, future customers should know what they are getting.

True Croft & Barrow D-cup swimwear has the cup size included on the size tag. Like 10D. Look for that to know that you are getting a correctly sized top. See attached example of what the tags should look like.

product_title: RJC Women's Beachside Breeze Hawaiian Smocked Sundress
review_body: At first I was leery about buying this dress as every description stated that it could be small for some women.  I'm not a small woman - normally a size 16 on top (42") and 16-18 (46") on the bottom and 5'10" tall  Finally though, I found an actual size chart on another one of their dresses in this style which pegged me as a "Large".  I decided to give it a try and I'm very glad I did.  The dress just grazes my knee, the bodice fit perfectly - enough stretch, but still of such quality that it gave me great support (B cup).  The drape of the rayon fabric is flattering and falls straight, just skimming the hips and since the bottom of the bodice which hugs about 2" beneath the breasts is comfortably cinched in, there is the illusion of an hourglass figure.  I bought the blue & white, which is an attractive blue/gray color.  Love this so much...I'm shopping for another one to take with me on my trip.

product_title: Onzie Long Legging Jungle Fever
review_headline: Struggled with size and ultimately performance initially
review_body: According to the size chart on the Onzie website I fall into the category of M/L. I have a 29 inch waist and fit a size 8 jean on average. When I received my leggings they arrived as pictured. When I put them on they looked like they fit beautifully (no muffin top). However as soon as I started to move vigorously in them (mostly from chatarunga to down dog) they started to slide over my hips. Then I started to hop in them and the leggings were sliding off! I will say customer service at Onzie ( I purchased from them directly) was very friendly, helpful, and exchanged my leggings for a size S/M. When the new size arrived I want to say the pattern looked differently than pictured or from the previous size M/L (looks like the pattern on the capri with more pink splashes in front than angry cat faces. I'm all about the angry cat face!). I will say the S/M does not slide off my body but I have a mild pinch of a muffin top that I can live with. I do not feel like the material is too thin and I don't feel like my "business" shows when I bend over. I need leggings that allow for repeated movements and deep bends (anything from a down dog to a kettlebell goblet squat). While I think the S/M size is better for the work I do in the gym or studio Im sad that the pattern didn't stay consistent. I can not speak for how the leggings wash or hold up with repeated wearing and that will ultimately decide if I purchase again.  UPDATE: I wore these leggings through a workout and they held up well. One thing that bothered me a little is that the waistband rolls down or flips down so I had to adjust it on a few occasions. The other thing of note is when you start sweating the leggings really cling to you and even feel a bit better. With that said most workouts don't start with you covered in oceans of sweat. I think these leggings would be phenomenal for hot yoga and definitely not bad for other activities but it certainly is a benefit halfway through your workout when you startto perspire. I also appreciate the level of flexibility they give for my deep squats with no awkward pulling in the crotch or seat of the leggings.

review_headline: It is really hard to get suitable plus size swimsuit for large body like me. The balance between abdomen and curve is ...
review_body:
Bought one as present for my wife. here is her commet.

My shape 45-38-47, D cup. And i choose XL, Blue color.
It is really hard to get suitable plus size swimsuit for large body like me. The balance between abdomen and curve is an art. This CharmLeaks Women's Retro Plus Size High Waist Floral Print One Piece Swimsuit really cheers me. hahahahaha……

The description is objective and reliable.
One piece swimsuit usually shapes the body fairly nice. That is my golden rule on swimming product. And this one is fully lined at the front with slight plunge V neck and deep U backless high waist, which leaks body shine properly. Typical retro style.
The wide shoulder bandages support the body and leave the most comfort.
The material seems excellent too. High spandex allows for exclusive endurance and provides freedom of movement.
it fits multiple occasions, sports swimming, family gathering , beach entertainment, hangout on beach……
oh, blue color. fashionable and modest. Floral print is neither too large nor too small. the other black and grey color are also alluring.
I love it and glad that I snapped it up. It makes me proud of my beautiful curves.
Great fit, great price, highly recommend.

review_headline: This one piece modern swimsuit is perfect for the swimming pool environment
review_body:
This one piece modern swimsuit is perfect for the swimming pool environment. It adapts extremely well to women's body hugging it therefore slimming it. Shockingly it is very eye-catching.
Despite its adjustability to the curves it still remains comfortable and flexible. I am usually a US size 12 and ordered XL. It fits me perfectly. Not too loose not too tight. After swimming in the water, you would find it secure and modest. All stay in the place. It is so good than all of my swimsuits before.
I like its waist shape best. It makes me look slim although I have hips, a bum and boobs... the color is vivid and attractive and provides sense of elegance. Traditional blue with floral print seems energetic and youthful. Fixed shoulder strap and cut of the back it is ideal for professional and occasional swimmers. Movements are not restricted at all. waist support is maintained. Mid cut legs make it feminine. Anyway, I felt very confident of my shape and figure when wearing this.
Highly recommend it for who are looking for a both casual and sport swimsuit.

review_headline: Great Toddler PJs, 100% soft smooth cotton, tag-less, well made and durable! Really glad I found these online!
review_body: Great Toddler PJs, 100% soft smooth cotton, tag-less, well made and durable! Really glad I found these online!  I am very happy with the Babyroom product in cotton pj's. I believe this is a product made and marketed in China.  I am not that up on where name brands get their product; however, this may be one of those that sells to different high end brands and then that brand puts their label on them.  Regardless, I really like the look and feel of this PJ; it is quality and buttery soft cotton.  This is the first time I tried the brand and am pleasantly surprised with the quality. In my opinion it is very similar to the quality of other well known name brands such as Carters (this Babyroom brand in my opinion is better in feel, stitching and certainly price). All cotton and tag-less pj's for toddlers are hard to find in the department stores and very expensive. These are well made, soft, true to size and wash/dry very nicely.

As a consumer, it was very nice to see them not just stuffed in a bag and a tiny box.  When I opened the tissue paper I found the beautiful amethyst twist top.  The color is so rich and beautiful looking with a royal look and luxurious feel to it. The fabric is 95% rayon and 5% spandex. It makes this too lightweight with a stretch.  The front has a v-neck with a twisted design look at the bust.  The shirt is a solid amethyst purple.  The top does run smell, I normally wear a large and ordered a 1x and it fit me perfectly. review_headline: Perfect Femininity ... And Made in the USA!
review_body: I am so excited about this top! It has been a long time since I have found a really cute top that I love as much as this one. It is so pretty! The color is beautiful (I got the Forest Green). I've hand washed it twice so far and the color has not faded. And because it requires hang drying, it has not shrunk at all. (I didn't literally hang dry it, I put it in the dryer on NO HEAT Tumble Only for a few minutes then I laid it out with a towel inside of it ). The fit is just wonderful (and I don't use the word 'wonderful' often). The twist makes it unique, the sleeves are light and look very feminine. The material is soft and smooth Rayon and Spandex, and the shirt lightly lies on your body without being 'clingy'. This shirt goes with everything. You can wear it with jeans, or it would look so beautiful with a long lacy skirt. It would be perfect for work, a date, or just hanging out with friends. The V neck is not too high, not too low, it's just perfectly right and accentuates my ... well ... my chest area. Took me a minute to think how to say that without sounding crude, but it really does make your chest look good! I really do love this top. And then to learn its made in the USA just made me love it even more. I am absolutely getting another one. Just as soon as I decide on which color to get because I want them all! product_title: Two Piece Tankini Swimwear Plus Size With Boyshorts
review_headline: Unfortunately, this item is shipped from China, meaning ...
review_body: Unfortunately, this item is shipped from China, meaning it takes two weeks to arrive and also that the sizes are not even close to US sizes, no matter what the size chart indicates. According to the Amazon size chart I am a 16, therefore I ordered a 5x. Tried the top on, the waistband under the chest was a bit tight and the flowy part underneath was flowy as expected, but not nearly as long as it is in the picture. The real kicker was the chest area. I am a size 38C and the top did not even BEGIN to cover my chest. If I were to attempt to wear this, everything would fall out everywhere, very unlike what I wished in buying this suit. And after holding the shorts up to my hips, I determined they weren't worth even trying to put on. I measured them and they are the equivalent of a US 12. Don't let the "plus size" headline fool you: this suit may be plus size for Asians, but this would barely fit average to small US sizes. (Another note, "plus sizes" do not qualify for Prime prices or shipping on Amazon, so keep this in mind when shopping.)

product_title: ACEVOG Women's Elegant Deep-V Neck Cap Sleeve Vintage Bridesmaid Dress
review_headline: Pleasantly surprised with this steal of a deal...
review_body:
A friend showed me a link to this dress and I loved it. For $20 you couldn't beat the price. I got it for $20.99 with free shipping from the buyer and then saw it was coming from China. I was totally skeptical and then started to worry it may be too small or not come in and then thought whatever, it's only $20. Plus, the image looks like it's a slinky or silky material and the review said cotton blend, so I immediately thought it would be like a t-shirt material type dress. Well, it came in yesterday. The first thing I did was open the bag to feel the material to see if it was a t-shirt like material. From outside the bag I could already tell it wasn't. I'm not sure exactly what it is but it's like a blend, somewhat cottony, somewhat slinky. It's nice and I gotta keep it away from my cats because I can see it snagging easily.

PROS:
So first thing first, it is a better quality material than I anticipated. +1. Estimated delivery date said between August 31 and September 8th, which was a major downer for me. It came in like a week early and I was totally surprised. +1. The fit is on point. Actually, it may be a little better fit for someone with a bigger bust line, because it would probably hang a little better from top down, but for me, I'm happy with the fit. Everything seems to hang where it should belong. +1. Overall craftsmanship I give it a +1 because it's made really well. No weird seam flaws, no straggler threads, no odd creases, or any weird flaws. Hidden zipper on side of bust works great, material is nice, cut is nice, looks great on.

CONS:
The photo shows it as a kind of true red, in real life it is more of a raspberry. Since I got this to wear to a holiday party, I was hoping for the more true red, but you know, the raspberry is actually really pretty in person. Anyway, if you're looking for a true-to-photo shade of red, you'll be disappointed. If you're looking for something in a red-color range, you'll be happy. (I give it a +1 because I like the color, others may not).

Overall score I gave it 5 stars. Totally worth the $20, more even. I'd pay up to $45 for this specific dress with shipping included. So if you're looking for a cute dress at a very affordable price and OK with waiting a few weeks to get it, this is a pretty major bargain.a +1 because I like the color, others may not).

Overall score I gave it 5 stars. Totally worth the $20, more even. I'd pay up to $45 for this specific dress with shipping included. So if you're looking for a cute dress at a very affordable price and OK with waiting a few weeks to get it, this is a pretty major bargain.

product_title: Rove On Neck Wallet ID Badge Holder Lanyard
review_body: Very high quality natural leather and brass product. This should last you several years before it wears out.

product_title: Rove On Neck Wallet ID Badge Holder Lanyard
review_body:
Very clever and functional design. Many of us have to wear badges, this allows you to have a nice-looking badge holder that doubles as a wallet. If you're throwing your back out sitting on a wallet, or are wearing clothes without pockets and don't want to carry a purse, this is a slick alternative. It's also small enough to tuck under your shirt and use as a smaller version of those around the neck travel passport pouches. The waxed nylon cord looks like many modern necklace cords, so tucked under a shirt it might well be mistaken for a cord necklace. You could also put your belt through the cord and put the wallet in your pocket, using the cord like a wallet chain. Obviously it can be cut through, but if you're worried about a casual pickpocket or simply falling out, this would be a good solution.

The stitching and construction are very precise and good quality; the overall impression is of an expensive leather accessory. The backing for the photo id pouch is cheap cardboard though, which makes me wonder about the durability of the faux leather. The wallet will secure a photo id and has six other card slots. A few of the slots could hold more than one card, or a small number of folded bills. The design is such that none of it should fall out.

I received this free or virtually so for product testing and review. I am under no obligation to provide a positive review and receive no incentives or rewards for doing so. My aim is to highlight features and drawbacks that I would want to know about as a buyer, not hype the product for the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.

product_title: Rove On Neck Wallet ID Badge Holder Lanyard
review_body: I was tired of constantly replacing the plastic/rubber cheap card holders. I have to pull my ID card in and out several times daily and they would always rip and eventually the rip grows and my two ID cards would end up on the floor. This is a great solution and looks professional. It's perfect for the business casual environment. My one con is I wish the necklace part was a little longer.  Not sure about durability as I just got it, I'll see how it stands the test of time.

product_title: Rove On Neck Wallet ID Badge Holder Lanyard
review_headline: Love this for under my nurses scrubs!
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:930a9145bb1709d786631cc18ca9720a]]This review is for the Rove On Neck Wallet ID Badge Holder Lanyard.

This is a GREAT neck wallet I purchased to wear under my nursing scrubs at the hospital. I like to keep my cash, cards and ID extremely secure and putting these items in my scrubs pocket just doesn't cut it. I always feel like I will lose them.

This wallet features an antique brass snap and a nice coated cotton rope material lanyard that is 17" from top to bottom. It also has a lariat for adjusting the tension on the lanyard and making it more secure. If you decide you don't want to wear the lanyard for a day, open the antique brass hook from the loop on the wallet and place the wallet in your pocket sans lanyard. It is versatile and secure both ways however you decide to use it.

The material is faux leather but extremely soft, and almost fooled me into thinking it was real. The accent color runs though the center credit card slot. It gives the neck wallet a little pizzazz.

Inside the wallet is more card slots, a slot that could be used for tri-folded cash bills, and the back has that nice clear vinyl ID slot to keep your identity with you at all times. 5/5 stars for design, materials and functionality.

If you have any questions please post below and I would be happy to answer! I received a discounted promotional sample of this item for my honest and unbiased review.

product_title: Rove On Neck Wallet ID Badge Holder Lanyard
review_headline: Great for throwing in a gym/yoga bag
review_body: When I was in college and beyond, I had a keychain with place for an ID and cards.  I loved it and had one until it finally fell apart.  I have started going to some yoga classes lately and was looking for something similar to throw in my yoga bag rather than locking my purse in the trunk or taking it with me.  I have heard that bad people will sometimes watch and break into cars in gym parking lots because they see people leave their purses there.  The yoga studio doesn't have locker so I wanted to find an alternative.  I found this and have been very happy with it. I put my drivers' license, debit card, and a couple of bucks in it and just leave it in my purse with my wallet and other stuff.  My purse often functions more as a carry-all since I have a toddler.  I really don't need to have suckers and bandaids and whatever else it is that a toddler may need with me at the yoga studio, so I just grab the ID badge holder and put it in my bag and leave my purse at home.  That way I don't even have to worry about my purse being with me.  If I have to stop somewhere on my way home, I still have the essentials with me.  This seems well made and serves my purpose well.  I purchased the item at a discount in exchange for an honest review.  However, my review is unbiased and reflects my own thoughts.

You can also carry it in you pocket by detaching it from the lanyard! The only thing that would make this better is to have the RFID blocking protection but you can buy separate sleeves for that.  It is perfect for cruise ships, hiking, going to the gym, shopping, and going out on the town. There are really so many places that this would be prefect and not having to carry your entire wallet.  It has 6 card slots and a window for your ID and a lobster claw on the lanyard.  I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for an honest review. I am happy with this wallet.

product_title: Hard Tail Women's Old School Sweatpant
review_headline: These are cute and comfortable, but really thin for a 'sweatpant'
review_body:
These are cute and comfortable, but really thin for a 'sweatpant'. The thinness does have its advantages: makes them perfect for lounging, yoga, walking, running errands in the Summer or Springtime. Also, they don't have that bulky sweatpants look and do have a trendier fit with the low-waist. I'm 5'7 about 130 lbs and the 'small' fits well right out of the dryer, but being so thin, they kind of stretch out and gives me that 'droopey drawers' look by end of the day. But, some of you may have been blessed with more booty than myself ;)

I would recommend them for those who can drop $72 on thin, decent fitting, non-sweatpants.

review_headline: This Strapless Bra Was The Missing Piece To My Wardrobe
review_body: I was offered this Strapless Lace Seamless Bra for a great deal to try and share my honest opinion about it. I ordered one in black, because I have lots of outfits and tops that I could use this with, one dress in particular. It fits perfectly and is a great width because sometimes you need these to be more than just a nipple cover. I have this dress that I usually wear a black tankini under because it is very low cut in the front and the back. This Strapless Lacy Bra actually adds something to the dress that my other option didn't have...oh, it's called flare. I definitely recommend this Full Lacy Strapless Bra for every wardrobe, it could be the missing piece.

review_body:
This is the Women's Full Floral Lace Strapless Seamless Stretchy Bandeau Tube Bra Top by Top Leggings.
This is really a gorgeous lace bandeau bra. This is available in so many beautiful colors.
It is made of 95% COTTON 5% SPANDEX, so it is stretchy and soft, very comfortable.
I find this is something that is great fit and easy to wear. No matter how you wear it as by itself or under a dress or shirt you will have comfort and style
This really is a beautiful floral lace bandeau bra. I love lacy things.
I received a promotional discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased opinion.

product_title: TL Women's Full Floral Lace Strapless Seamless Stretchy Bandeau Tube Bra Top
review_headline: Cute and sexy, not bad for the price.
review_body: I picked up this lace bandeau bra top mostly to wear under low-cut tops that might be too revealing. I think the little bit of lace peeking out is cute and sexy, and the lack of straps makes it useful with all kinds of outfits. It seems to run true to size, with a little bit of stretch to help hold it up. It definitely doesn't offer any lift or support for your breasts, so expect to have to wear a normal bra underneath in most cases. It's a little flimsy, but for the price it isn't bad. The lace wasn't stiff or scratchy-feeling on my skin. Basically what you'd expect for an inexpensive item- not amazing quality but not bad.

product_title: TL Women's Full Floral Lace Strapless Seamless Stretchy Bandeau Tube Bra Top
review_headline: It is not scratchy and uncomfortable like I was worried it might be
review_body: This is very soft lace. It is not scratchy and uncomfortable like I was worried it might be. It fits true to size and stays up well. The color is very bright and vibrant. I am very happy with this order! I received a discount on this item in exchange for my honest review.

product_title: Champion Women's Jersey Banded Knee Pant
review_body: I bought the XL after reading the other reviews and noting how large the sizing was reported. Between a size 16-18, I may have been able to pull off a size L. I would not return these!!! The pull string adjust entirely, so as I shrink they will too. The waist is very comfortable and doesn't fold down onto itself. The inseam is high enough not to give me "chub-rub" on fast paced walks, while still able to easily get into a low squat and not worry about busting seams. Light weight fabric makes it very summer friendly. The cuffs around the knees are a bit loose, even for my very developed calves. If they're a bother, the pants can be cut to any length short, but I'll be leaving them as is. I'm going to order the other colors available in a size down. Love them!!!!

product_title: Champion Women's Jersey Banded Knee Pant
review_body: Comfort 10. Style 10. Price on Amazon Prime 10. The top elastic is just thick enough and stretchy enough. Perfect for those lazy Sundays.

review_headline: Best No slip socks I've ever owned
review_body: Four out of five pairs are perfect. One pair does bunch up but all the others stay up! I've tried many brands of these "no slip" socks that end up bunched up my arch which is as bad as it sounds. My favorite are the lace pair. review_headline: My new favorite in no-show socks
review_body: These are a bit more than I've spent in the past on no-show socks but worth every penny. I have size 7 narrow feet so very few no-show socks actually stay hidden in my shoes. These are not completely hidden but shape of the sock and stitching allow for the little bit showing to look like it should be showing and the typical stretched curve of other no-shows. I especially look the look of the lace socks with anpair of my ballet slippers. As far as feel, these socks are very comfortable and stay on better than other no-show socks.

product_title: Dahlia Women's No Show Non Slip Liner Dress Socks - (4 Pack)
review_body:
These are really great socks. I am a non-sock wearer. I wear flats in most days and my hubby complains that my feet and shoes stink, and it's from not wearing socks. So I got these, not really expecting much, but I really like them. I do sometimes have issues with the backs falling down, but the little grip pad they have back there helps to minimize that. Also, I have smaller feet (6-6.5), so if your feet are a little longer, you may not have that issue. The grips on the ball of the feet are also great and stop my feet from sliding around in my shoes. These are also cut really well. I can hardly see them with my ballet flats (Cole Haan). I have noticed that my feet don't really smell (as bad) since I have started to wear these, so that is a bonus and they are going to make my shoes last a little longer.

They are a good investment. I wish they were a little cheaper. I think $30 for 4 pairs is a little steep, but I do feel like I'm getting my money's worth. I will be purchasing more and would recommend them.

review_headline: Minimalist Wallet - It Really Fits the Bill
review_body: After having used this wallet for nearly a month, I can with confidence say that it is by far the best minimalist wallet I have ever used. I have tried many different types of wallets and money clips which, ultimately, were all too bulky or cumbersome. This design allows for flexibility when deciding how many cards you might want because, well, it's literally flexible. I only carry 4 cards and it holds them amazingly well. I have never worried about anything falling out. In fact, it was a little difficult removing cash and cards when I first started using it. Now, having learned the technique and understanding that the material is designed to be stretched, it isn't an issue to get the cards out when making purchases or showing my ID to the police. This really does fit the bill as being a great minimalist wallet with a fantastic aesthetic design and outstanding build quality.

product_title: Minimalist Wallet & Credit Card Holder Men with Slim Design by Raw
review_body: I got sick and tired of bulky wallets and always having to take them out of my pockets before sitting down. With the Minimalist Wallet I have everything I had in my old wallet and it is half the size! It is so nice to have a wallet that can remain in my pocket unnoticed until I need it. My cash, credit cards, and business as fit nicely and tight. With cell phones, keys and other necessities you cannot beat the price of having a wallet as slim and usable as the Minimalist Wallet.

product_title: Minimalist Wallet & Credit Card Holder Men with Slim Design by Raw
review_body: I'll be honest I've always been a money clip person so I was hesitant to try something different. I can say that I absolutely love this wallet. Organizes my cards so much better and you can have one dollar in it or a stack and it still functions great. Hands down I recommend this wallet to everyone. I'm buying a second one now for my dad.

product_title: Minimalist Wallet & Credit Card Holder Men with Slim Design by Raw
review_headline: Perfect Travel Wallet Becomes Daily Driver
review_body: I work in the airline industry and travel extensively, both domestic and internationally. I've been looking for the perfect layover wallet especially when in foreign countries and you don't want to carry too much with you out exploring the city, etc. This is a great wallet for out on the town when you want to just carry the minimum essentials, but it can also fit a surprising number of cards and cash.  It is quickly becoming my go-to wallet for daily life at home as well.  It's made of quality materials and construction is top-notch. Opening the box it's even smaller than you would imagine, but functions perfectly as described. I have already ordered more as gifts for family and friends.

I purchased the special "candidate" sized shirt, but when I put my arm in it to pull it on, that was it. It only covered my arm. So I thought, "Ok, at least my arm is covered." But I no sooner stepped outside when 3 dogs started chasing me.
This shirt did look good on my arm, so I would say give it a try, just pick a size other than "candidate." And don't wear it outside unless you like running.

product_title: Lace Shapewear Compression Corset Waist Training for Women Weight Loss
review_body:
I wear an extra large shirt, and bought an extra large which works on the tightest setting. I like the product so well that I bought it in large and on the loosest setting I get much more 'cinching.' The girdle part starts right below the bust and ends where the hips meet the legs. It doesn't ride up or down like the other waist cinchers I have tried. The straps are very, very comfortable. They are adjustable, and the adjustment part is on the front, which is super convenient. I find the corset 'stays' very comfortable, no pinching or riding. I've worn mine for up to 9 hours at a time and have found them to be quite comfortable, especially compared to other products of this type. Highly recommend for women who run large through the middle, like me!

I got discounted price for exchange for a honest review!

product_title: Lace Shapewear Compression Corset Waist Training for Women Weight Loss (XX-Large, black)
review_headline: I was a bit disappointed by the support
review_body:
I am no stranger to shape wear so I was very excited to get this Lacey number to help smooth my abdomen and I had hoped for some bust and back support as well. I was a bit disappointed by the support. I felt is have me creases in places they weren't before and because of the mixed textiles the fat was just distributed to the areas of weaker elasticity making a pooch in that area. The design is good, it is cute.
I wear a 12/14 and ordered an xxl which by the size chart should have been too small but I was able to put it on the last hook because the elasticity was so loose (not compressed) just hugged the body. It may be better if it had some boning for structure to improve the silhouette and the quality of fabric was a bit better on contained more elastic. I purchased at a discount for my honest review.

product_title: Genie Hourglass Waist Training Belt
review_body: This belt is of a really thick and durable fabric. I love how it has two layers that can be adjusted. You can make this as tight or loose as you wish. It did help hold my belly in place. I do feel like I had a fit issue, though. It wasn't long enough to cover my whole belly in the front, but too long in the back.It was slightly uncomfortable while sitting, and had to be adjusted. I could probably stand it for a few hours a day, but not all day, every day. I was hoping to wear this for exercise, but I don't think that would work well. I surprised her with this awesome t shirt. I bough her a red one in a size small and it fit her perfectly.  She is a regular sized teen and small is perfect for her. The shirt is made of 100% cotton and has a very nice black well made print. She has used it and it was a hit. All her friends ask where she got it and they love it. Perfect gift for a dragon ball z fan or anime fan. Comes in various colors.  A t shirt for everyone I would call this a unisex shirt. It feels soft and we already washed it and keeps looking great. It is my daughters new favorite shirt. Well Worth getting one. All fans should own one. No defects and print looks great after washes. If you want to last longer hand wash. I recommend this t shirt. review_body: After much flattering and reasoning I was able to get my husband to try out the Roc Bodywear Mens Shaper Tank.  Even though he denies his insecurities in front of "the boys" about his body, they are most definitely there! He decided that this shaper was worth a try! Now the first time he wore it he wore it all day through work, which he said made his sweat even more than he already does.  Keep in mind his work is mostly outside, but he tried it out again underneath a suit in what I consider a normal day to day setting! Wearing it under a nice dress shirt made him feel very tucked in and he was indeed more confident and even kept his jacket off most of the time. This is an item that is meant to be a man's secret undergarment.  It seems to me that this item is very similar to a woman's shaper-one that holds you in and contours the best parts.  This product is great for any man that wants to feel good without killing himself at the gym for a body builder look!

product_title: RockWearZ Bodywear Men's Body Shaper Tank Top Slimming Compression Under Shirt
review_body:
The Roc Bodywear Men’s Body Shaper Tank was a great investment. My girlfriend and I moved to a foodie city recently and our evenings out have been catching up to me. I got the Body Shaper in black for that added slimming effect and when I put it on I instantly felt like I had six-pack abs! You do have to use a bit of muscle to get the shirt on at first, but after that, the shirt does the rest of the work.

I wore it under a t-shirt that I hadn’t been able to wear in months and when my girlfriend got home, her words were, “Hey, it fits again!” She couldn’t even tell I had anything on underneath! If you’re going to wear this slimming top under a buttondown, I advise you purchase a white one for light shirts so that if it is noticed, it doesn’t stand out from any regular tank top undershirt.

Simply put: I recommend this product for those guys out there who are tired of looking and feeling overweight. Stop sucking in that gut like I’ve been doing and let this shirt do that job for you!

product_title: FeelinGirl Women's Waist Trainer Corset for Weight Loss Hourglass Body Shaper
review_body: Ok ladies. I am going to do my best to review this item for the curvy girls that want details!  So here goes. I purchased the Atrous style/version of this cincher. The material of the garment is great. It feels like a typical waist cincher, with heavy elasticity in the waist.  It looks just like the picture. The problem is, the size is not correct.  I am 5' 10, a 42 D in the chest, a 38 in the smallest part of my waist, and 51in in the hip area. Yes I am super vivacious. (Jessica Rabbit Body) However, I typically wear a 2X or size 16 in clothing. I ordered the 5X. This garment should have fit me. Sadly, it only came to mid stomach.  It was about 3 inches shy of fitting around my whole stomach.   I was unable to buckle the hooks (the hooks are similar to the ones you find on the back of a bra) over my stomach.  I am no where near a 5X, but I ordered a 5X based on some of the honest reviews, and I still was off. I am giving this item one star because the vendor should have their own sizing chart, true to size, using US measurements. I stopped ordering clothes from Amazon a year ago, because I got tired of spending $$ on sending items back that don't fit due to misleading measurements.  Out of the clothes I purchase from Amazon, I would say that only 20% fit well.  There has got to be an easier way. Vendors should always pay for returns and shipping for items that just don't fit.   If you have a tummy, or if you are curvy, I would order 4 sizes up.  I believe these sizes are Asian sizes.

product_title: FeelinGirl Women's Waist Trainer Corset for Weight Loss Hourglass Body Shaper
review_body: Don't expect a great cincher. For the price is just okay. The little bars across keep popping out and I have to constantly fix them and sewing them back here and there. It's not really comfortable, but it's a cincher and thanks to being stretchy it doesn't feel like it's choking your intern organs, which I guess is a good thing. Doesn't show through your clothes (standing or sitting).  Edit: I had to come back and take stars back and wish I could give zero. I'm hating this cincher every day more. The bars keep popping out through the holes in the fabric or just through the holes made by the poor sewing. Result: the bars keep stabbing my skin. Have to take it off and on every 30 minutes to fix it. Also, I'm already on the second row of hooks but I'm pretty sure is because the fabric is getting looser. I have not thrown it away yet because I'm waiting for a new one. Picture shows how bad it is (didn't pull the bar out myself. It just does that all the time).

product_title: FeelinGirl Women's Waist Trainer Corset for Weight Loss Hourglass Body Shaper
review_body:
I was between sizes, so I went with the larger option and, the first time I put it on, it was snug. It fit wonderfully and it made my back feel great and my figure look banging.

By day three it was already broken in. The ribs were way flexible and felt as though it was more the elastic construction supporting and shaping my figure.

The elastic is porous, so it did breath well, but it would bunch up at the small of my waist. It left red marks and was generally uncomfortable to wear, but I made it for 8-10 hours for days 3-6.

Day six was when I ordered my next corset from another company. I did lose a half inch from my waist, but the waist cincher split.

This served its purpose, but more as a girdle than anything else. I'm glad it was cheap because of how quickly I had to replace it.

This is a trainer for a waist trainer, not something I would recomend to the serious, but something for someone completely new to the waist training practice.

review_body:
I've never used a waist trainer before so I really didn't know what to expect.
My waist is 33 inches, so I got mine in XL in Aubergine. When putting it on there was a struggle but nothing long and crazy. I realized I should've went a size down because I had just got it and was already on the 3rd set of hooks.
When wearing the trainer it hasn't been uncomfortable at all. There's nothing poking into me or anything. It's actually really helping my posture. With it on I don't slouch, and it's so weird lol.
I like what I see when I put the trainer on. I like how I have more curves. I'm excited to continue this journey and see how small and curvy I can get. I would recommend going a size down. I would rather mine be too tight than be too big!

review_headline: Really sexy & defines my waist good
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:7cf0f100cb439d9769375784503d1a40]] The trainer is breathable, and lightweight compared to a latex trainer. Despite the fabric being thinner, it's still very tough and good quality. I don't think it will tear easily. The lace detail is a pretty touch without it being too much lace. PLEASE go up a size as the other customers mentioned. I wear a size Medium 125 lbs 29\\" waist and would have to get a large in this trainer. While it still fits, I won't be able to go smaller with the prongs due to it already being so tight. The material overall was comfortable, but it cut under my armpit as the arm holes could be a little bigger for comfort. If you wear a sleeved shirt it won't bother you as much. Thus that's why I give it 4 instead of 5 stars.
I do think that it defined my waist more however, possibly because it was tighter. So that was definitely a plus.
