product_title: FeelinGirl Women's Spiral Steel Boned Steampunk Gothic Bustier Corset
review_headline: The support lines are flexible and make for a comfortable wear. The entire corset has an elegant yet ...
review_body:
The western look.

The Brocade Steampunk corset is made well from a polyester materiel. All stitching, straps and chains are intact with no,loose ends or missing pieces.

The corset closes in the front with a set of 6 heavy duty, metal buttons. Running from the bust area to mid waist is a leather strap and buckle This leather decoration looks as if it would be able to hold your bullets as you ride of to a a gun fight. Just below the strap a double chain hangs down to the waist line and attaches to the back of the corset. This chain is able to be moved.. On the left side of the corset I find 2 more leather and buckle sets. The support lines are flexible and make for a comfortable wear.

The entire corset has an elegant yet sexy feel. The dark brown fabric has a light leaf design throughout. Around both the bust line and waist line there is a bit of a lighter brown leather like material that lines and ascents the bust and waist line perfectly.

A matching thong made from the same material as the corset is also included in the package.

I would say that this corset would be perfect for everyday wear, a night with your special someone or a great addition to an old west costume.

I was offered the opportunity to review this product for my honest an unbiased opinion.

This corset screams sexy! The red and black striped silk like material is very flattering to the figure. The corset closes in the front by 2 methods. first a heavy duty zipper and then a set of 5 belt buckle looking locks. Both the sipper and locks work well and are free of defects.

Through out the corset I found little silver buttons that accent the piece very well. Running from the front to the back on each side there is a very cute little silver chain,

The bottom of the corset has little black woven ribbons that mimic the ones found to tie up the back of the corset. The ribbon that closes the back can be tightened or loosened for a more comfortable fit. Along the bust line there is a simple yet elegant line of lace that points upward toward the neck. There are thin straps that run over the shoulder. This straps are adjustable and made of the same red and black material with a little buckle to secure them in place. It top came with a cute thong made with the same material as the corset.

This corset would be perfect for a pirate costume, everyday wear, an anniversary gift, those special bedroom nights or over a tank like a lot of ladies are doing right now.

product_title: Meaneor Women's Baggy Fit V Neck Turn Up Tunic Tops Loose Basic Shirt
review_body:
I was kindly provided with a reviewer's sample of this product for honest reviewing purposes.

* About the material:
Described as a cotton blend in the product description, the fabric is one of those blends that feel more on the blend side than on the cotton side. It feels silky, very smooth and has a good stretch to it. Thickness-wise, it's on the thinner side which makes the whole shirt more lightweight and comfortable.

* About the fit:

- General fit: After carefully examining the measurements in the Product Description, I ordered the Medium size. This fit me really well with plenty of room to spare. It's a lovely loose fit so that it is flattering even if your body isn't as toned as it could be and it hides my sticking-out-belly really well - you can't see it at all with this shirt on which is great!

- Sleeve fit: The sleeves are a really nice length - not too short, not too long.

- Shirt length: The shirt is on the long side. On me it reaches about 2 inches below my butt.

* Other things to note:
It may not be obvious from the product photo: at the end of the sleeves, they are folded up and loosely-sewn into place so that they stay folded up - just an observation that I didn't notice until the product arrived so thought I'd point it out in case it's helpful to anyone.

* Overall:
Overall, I really like this shirt. Nice fit, comfortable silky material and looks flattering on. I'd happily recommend it.

product_title: Camellias Double Steel Boned Breathable Corset Heavy Duty Waist Training Shaper
review_headline: Not perfect, but great for the price
review_body:
The first one I received was a dud (arrived very dirty and with broken seams), but thankfully I have prime, so was able to get an exchange. Even on this new one, the side ribbon tapes attached to the busk tore on the first fitting, as it did with the first corset I ordered. Luckily, I don't think the side tape matters in cinching your waist in.

While quite heavy, I also found the bones don't fully extend all the way down the corset, so there may be a half inch or less of mesh fabric that is unsupported, and thus becomes bunched or tucked near the bottom. I think this is what a previous reviewer mentioned as the hips "sticking out." As I use this for historical costuming, the small bunches are hid under my skirts and I don't notice. But, if you are planning on wearing this under a cotton t-shirt, you would probably notice.

That being said, its definitely nice and cool yet sturdy; not perfect, but great for the price. I have a 29" waist and bought the medium and it fits well.

review_headline: I should have known better to try to buy a top like this without ...
review_body: I should have known better to try to buy a top like this without trying it on, but the price was right so I made the attempt. I generally wear a US women's size Med (sports bra and t-shirt, size 34A bra) so I went with a large on this, knowing that it was asian sizing but that I have practically no boobs, so I thought that XL, or bigger would be huge. It did not fit well. I'm guessing that the 'padded sports bra' part of the top is around a 30-32 B or C. The elastic was so tight I barely got it on or off and I could have almost stuffed the cups with apples. Rather than returning it, I cut out the bra portion and will be using the (still tight-fitting) tank as a workout shirt or something. I highly suggest this top, size large, IF you are possibly a size 30-32B. Those of us little A cups and those 34+... beware of this top!

product_title: Zxzy Hot Fashion Women Galaxy Printed Sleeveless T Shirt Vest Tank Tops
review_body:
I received this product for free or highly discounted in exchange for my honest review.

First off, I would have given this product three stars but because they had a tank with the Hogwart's crest, they automatically get an extra star. Beyond the image, I really did not like this product, but I do not hate it either. I really want to wear it, but I think an undershirt is going to be needed. The material is thin and really tight. There is a small amount of stretch, but it is still somewhat small. I am 5'9" with a long torso, broader shoulders, and small chest (36A,) and it was skin-tight on me everywhere. I could still fit into it but just fit. Nothing else. I do not know if I will wear this shirt, if there was a HP themed party or something, and I wanted to wear a cheap shirt that I would be OK getting dirty or ripped and then throwing away, I would think about it, but overall, you are better off saving your money to get a better quality one at the HP website or somewhere like that.

Overall, I do not recommend.

review_body:

Sewing and stitching is great quality and this dress is a fantastic value for the money. Would recommend!

product_title: Minka In Jade Strapless Backless White Lace Wedding Bra with Carrying Case
review_body:
I wanted to love this bra. I NEED something like this because I am big chested and going without a bra is not an opinion. So when I was able to review this backless/strapless bra I was so excited.
When I opened the package the case is beautiful. It's a hard shell zipper case so the backless bra is very protected. It's pretty compact so it woudl easily store in a drawer or closet. Zipper glides easily open and closed. It's pink with black felt flowers on it.
The bra is a fancier version of the adhesive silicone cups you can buy. It's really pretty with a lace front and snap close front. The snap is easy to open and close.
Now I am a DD but can wear a D sometimes so I ordered the D.The minute I took it out I knew it would not fit me. But I was determined to try it anyway because you never know. But just as I suspected it was a no go.
I'm not a bra measuring expert but I would bet this runs small and is probably snug for a D cup. It was so small on me it was like I had a little larger coverage than if I was wearing pasties. It did not support me in anyway. My breast sagged like I had no bra on, which basically I didn't. There was coverage over my nipple so if my breast was perkier on it's own I may have worn the backless bra but I could not do it.
It is very easy to stick on and take off. I took the bra off within 10 minutes of putting it on and it came off with no problems. But once it's stuck it stays in place. I moved around, jumped a little. I was rocking and rolling but the backless/strapless bra did not come off.
I would buy this product in a heart beat if they made it in a bigger size. But as of right now this product is just okay to me but that is only because of the sizing issue.
I received this product complimentary in exchange for my honest opinion but the opinion expressed is all my own.

product_title: Minka In Jade Strapless Backless White Lace Wedding Bra with Carrying Case
review_body: This adhesive bra is made of quality material. The lace work is beautifully done and adds an elegant feel to this bra. The silicone adhesive material does not irritate the skin or cause any discoloration. You can easily peel the bra away from your skin without causing any pain. Once the bra is on, it will stay on. The clasp in the middle comes a loose so you can position the bra how you need to (I wish it had more adjustable leeway to tighten it to my liking) . I wear a 32C and the C size works well for me. If you are above a 32C you might want to get the D size because my sister who is a 36C tried to put this bra on and it looked like pasties. When it comes time to clean the bra you need to hand-wash it and let it air dry. The case that the bra comes in securely stores the bra and the case is super cute.  I received this product free to review, but my opinions are my own.

product_title: Minka In Jade Strapless Backless White Lace Wedding Bra with Carrying Case
review_body:
I have been looking for a backless strapless bra like this one, but not like one of those weir silicon ones most places sell. This bra arrived, and I had failed to notice, that it has a cute little- non collapsible carrying/ storage case! It a really pretty fuscia color with a sort od black lace print... Very pretty color--
It has a little satin handle, you can hang it in the closet or on a the back of a door.... It unzips and there is a divider- to keep the self adhesive bra from becoming dented or misshapen.
The bra is so lovely, the cups are lined with an ivory lace type print, and the inside of the cup is the adhesive, it comes with restickable cup protectors...
I normally wear 34B or 36A in most bras. I ordered thi in an A cup size- I want to have the push up effect! It works perfectly, I think you should think about a smaller size, if you are like me and want the cleavage!!! You just peel back the protector, (for deep push up) Squeeze your breast, stick the cup where you want it to start- it will warm to your body temp---- Then push your other side together and waa laa.... cleavage
I like to use a bra like this to wear under a push up bra, also- for extra enhancement...
I did receive this product for free, in exchange for my honest and unbiased opinion!! This bra should be a staple in all of your wardrobes!!!

product_title: Minka In Jade Strapless Backless White Lace Wedding Bra with Carrying Case
review_headline: I am not too happy with this bra to be honest
review_body:
I am not too happy with this bra to be honest. I have put it on my clothing just to try, and it would fit well. I have a ton of clothing that this bra would work well with that I rarely wear or have to wear in layers due to too much skin showing, and my regular bras showing, so having a strapless bra like this is the solution.
I think this bra is perfect for weddings. You put it on, do the wedding, then you can take it off and put it away. I am not sure I could wear it daily. What I am worried about is the sticky layer that makes the bra stay on the skin. I am extremely sensitive to sticky stuff on my breast skin. I am breastfeeding right now and am wearing pads with somewhat sticky surface. Sometimes these pads get stuck on my breast, and it can get quite painful to remove them. This bra has a very sticky surface, and I am not sure how I could wear it. I would die of pain taking it off I think. So, for that reason, I have the bra, I think it will fit well, but I will wear it only when I really need it - on some special occasion only, not every day. I wish there was a way to get a bra like this without the sticky surface.
I have received this product for free for a review.

product_title: Meaneor Women's Cherry Floral Print 1950s Vintage Rockabilly Strap Party Dress
review_body:
I had my doubts about a dress at this price point, and have had sizing issues with some imported clothing in the past. This was a very pleasant surprise.

First- it's a woven fabric, about mid-weight, and heavy enough that the skirt has a nice flair even without petticoats. It doesn't just lie limp.
The front bodice is lined with a silky fabric, the back is smocked with elastic. It is a little compressing if you are very curvy. You might want to buy a size up. The smocking makes the top very fitted before spilling out to the full skirt.The skirt is gorgeous, it really is a flattering silhouette.
At 5'4\\", the dress is about 2-3 inches above the knee.

It has a nice vintage flair, and it would work great as a costume or party dress. It's nicely constructed and finished.

I got the item free for reviewing- this is my honest opinion and experience.

product_title: Kimlee Duffle Bag with Shoe Compartment for Men & Women
review_body:
My new Kimlee Duffle Bag is the perfect size for packing a quick change of clothes for the gym, softball practice or even a 1-night trip. It’s spacious enough to easily hold a pair of jeans, sweater, make-up and other essentials.

The bag is quite durable and should last a very long time. Materials are high quality and it’s well sewn with reinforced stitching at the straps. The nylon shell is a beautiful Magenta color with gray/black trim. The product description says the bag is “Unisex” -- the style of the bag could be considered unisex but I don’t think many men that would like the color.

My favorite features are the side compartments -- one side has a drink holder with a bungee cord that keeps your drink snugly place and the other side has a nice zippered shoe bag. It’s great being able to keep my dirty shoes separate from my clean clothes -- the compartment even has side vents to air out your shoes.

Appreciate that OIWAS stands behind their product with a 30 day return policy and a one-year warranty against defects in material and/or workmanship. I received the Kimlee Duffle Bag at a discounted price in return for my unbiased review.

review_body:

The material is soft and well made. It is not a flimsy fabric and should hold up fairly well. It is not too thick or thin but perfect for a nice spring or fall day while still being so comfortable. The fabric is not clingy and drapes beautifully accenting the frame while still being forgiving to imperfections. I do wish the fabric strap on the shoulders was a bit wider so that it would hide my bra strap completely but I just use my clear bra straps with it and it works fine.
I love this top and need to get some more colors to add to my wardrobe. I received this at a discount in exchange for an unbiased review.

product_title: LL Womens Quilted Biker Jacket
review_headline: Great jacket, order by size chart
review_body: I originally ordered this in a medium based on others' reviews and fears that the fit would be small and have now had to re-order in a small to get a correct fit. This jacket fits as described in the size chart, and the one or two inches difference between the small and medium was most noticeable in the shoulders, creating a less than flattering silhouette. My one concern with ordering a small is that the sleeves may be too short. All in all, it was warm and seemed well-constructed. The shell fabric is soft and not plasticy like many other faux leather items, the zipper was smooth, and the seaming is especially flattering. This is a great looking vegan leather jacket that will go well with dresses, jeans, pretty much any look. I would recommend ordering by the size chart to avoid the inconvenience and expense of returning an ill-fitting item.

review_body:
My daughter and I disagree about the stars on this shirt. Since I ordered it with her in mind- I went with her 5 star rating.

So the reason I would have gone 4 stars is because the sleeves are a bit on the long side, and because the fabric feels more synthetic then cotton. It's a nice silky feeling fabric, but not what how I expect cotton to feel. It's not thin, it's a jersey with some body to it.

The shirt is really attractive. The fabric has a lot of drape, and the fit is very true- the knit has a lot of stretch so if you have broad shoulders or are on the curvy side, it will fit.

The blue is gorgeous. It's just a great bright pop of color.
I got this at no cost to review- and my daughter is thrilled with it!

product_title: Joansam Womens Faux Leather Waist Trainer Corset/Bustiers for Weight Loss
review_body:
Beautifully crafted faux leather waist corset with matching g-string. I normally wear a size 8, 36c bra, I got the medium, it fits great. When your corset arrives, the clasp "bones" are stiff, but once you move them around a bit, they fit comfortably. The inside of the corset is like a fleece fabric, so soft on your skin. The lace up in the back, is gorgeous. The satin ribbons are high quality, no loose strings. The grommets for the satin ribbons are Attatched well. I cannot even explain the attention to detail that has gone into this corset. It is so well made. It really is gorgeous. Every stitch and seam is straight and tight. I felt the g-string ran a little big. Overall this is an amazing corset, it is extremely sexy. And actually comfortable after you wear once or twice. (I've never worn a corset before ). I definately feel sexy when I wear this...and it does hold my soft belly in nicely. I highly recommend this product!!
I received this product at a full discount in exchange for my unbiased review. Opinions are my own.

product_title: Zxzy Mens Hipster Hip Hop USA American Flag All-Star Crewneck T-shirt
review_body:
I got this t-shirt for my boyfriend, who loves American flag apparel. It’s just his taste and way classier looking than a lot of similar t-shirts. That said, I was a little nervous about ordering it since the sizes were not American sizes but it looked so good I figured I would take the chance. We ordered the Asian 4XL hoping it would fit as he typically wears an XL in US sizes.

Turns out we shouldn’t have worried! The shirt fits perfectly. It also looks just better in real life than it does on the page. In addition, it’s very soft. I love softer t-shirts so that’s a definite perk for me. I am very impressed and happy with the quality and would absolutely order another product by the same brand. If you’re on the fence about it, give them a shot. I’m glad I did.

I received this product at a discount or for no cost in exchange for my honest review. If you found this review helpful, please let Amazon (and myself!) know by clicking yes underneath my review.

product_title: Alain Dupetit Men’s Two Button Suit in Many colors
review_body: I was attending a wedding out of state when the airlines lost my luggage... and with it my suit. My options were not great locally so I searched online. I needed something quick so I searched with my prime delivery and I found this suit.  I own a few beautiful suits so I did not want to spend a lot of money.  I was skeptical because the price seemed too good to be true.  When it arrived I was happily surprised to find a well made and quality fabric suit.  I purposely chose a suit color I did not already own and have worn this suit three times now.  I may tailor the jacket a bit so it really fits perfectly, but out of the box it has been great.

review_headline: It's more like a medium turquoise
review_body: I purchased this shirt in the "Oasis" color. I was expecting a pale turquoise, but it's actually a lot darker than the photograph. It's more like a medium turquoise. The reviews said that the fabric was thick enough that your bra won't show through, but this is not the case, at least with this color. I could see my bra through it, and it's not even stretched tight across my chest. I am 5'8, and the length of the shirt is perfect. It fits more like a "tall" than a regular. I don't think I would have to worry about it riding up in the back if I bent down to get something. The sleeves are a good length for those who have a little extra in the upper arms. It's a nice shirt, but I'm just really disappointed that it's semi-transparent, and the color is way off.

review_body: I love this cap.  I have the pink and green lace one.  I fell in love with it as soon as I saw it.  It's very pretty and soft and the pink and green lace is lovely.  The cap fits nicely and is very comfortable.  It is made of a soft, white stretchy material that conforms well to the shape of my head. product_title: Lace Sleep Cap for Women - Cancer Sleeping Hat, Sleeping Cap for Women, Chemotherapy, Chemo Night Cap Sleep Hat
review_headline: Feminine and pretty for all age ranges, should fit head sizes up to about 22 inches.
review_body:
Free product provided for evaluation and review.
I received the black one.

This is well made. It's pretty - the lace is stretchy and soft. Nothing about this cap is itchy or stiff. The main material, which is also under the lace, is 100% very soft stretchy cotton. The lace feels like a nylon/ spandex blend though it is not noted on the label. It's the sort of lace that is often on nice panties. It's lightweight, and small enough to fit in a pocket.

The cap is fairly light, but should be fine for months that are cool or warm. For deep winter, other caps might be a warmer choice. (This cap is more like a t-shirt than a coat, for your head. )

It's well sewn, with straight seams that are surged. It should be durable and could be machine washed if you wanted, though I'd definitely wash the black in cold water.

It should fit head sizes to about 22" comfortably. (Measure around the head at the forehead.) It will stretch a bit more, but I'm not sure how comfortable it would be much past 22". It might even fit younger girls - the head reaches full size actually quite early on. My niece wore a similar cap like this when she was 10 and going through chemo/radiation. They are really cute and feminine for all ages.

product_title: Aimery Women's 2015 Summer Style Fashion 3D Tank Tops Printed Sleeveless T Shirt
review_body:
This shirt is so funny! As shown in the picture, it is Jaws coming up to eat a very happy and unaware Ariel.

The shirt is made out of a polyester blend, and very silky feeling. It is very comfortable to wear, especially on a hot day.

It isn't the most flattering fit for me, but at the same time, it wasn't horrible. I am a size ten, but once I lose some weight at hit a size 8, I think it should fit perfect. It is a bit stretchy, so thats a plus.

The seams are visable, which is strange, but they mostly seem secure. There is one little snag on the top shoulder area, but it doesn't look like it will come unraveled.

The shirt does have a bit of a smell, so make sure to wash it before wearing it. One wash and the smell was gone.

The coloring on the shirt is pretty good. Very bright and vibrant. No running of colors after I put it in the wash either.

I would definitely get another from here but in a different design.

I received this for free in order to give my honest and unbiased review.

product_title: Lttcbro Women's Latex Waist Cincher Spanx Shapewear Waist Trainers
review_headline: Firm and Comfortable Waist Training Corset
review_body: This is my first latex waist corset and I like the feel of this corset. This corset is good for beginners as this is more flexible than the fabric and ribbon corsets. The outer layer of this corset is made of high quality latex that is stretchable and the inner layer is made of cotton that provides comfort. This corset is soft to touch and it has 3 columns of hook-eye closure. I chose the nude color as it can be worn under my light colored clothes without being noticed by others. First day I found it very difficult to wear as it took around 10 minutes of struggle to get into this corset and it was very uncomfortable. After two days, it was easy to wear and more comfortable as I forgot that I was wearing a corset. Now I enjoy wearing it and it provides the right amount of support and flexibility. This firm corset provides good compression as it is made of elastic latex and the hook-eye closure helps to adjust this corset for comfortable wearing and effective waist training. This corset doesn't roll up from my hips and it supports my posture. This corset made me more confident to wear figure hugging clothes. I am really happy with my purchase and I am waiting to see amazing results. I received this waist training corset at a discounted price for an honest review.

product_title: Lttcbro Women's Latex Waist Cincher Spanx Shapewear Waist Trainers
review_headline: Make sure you order by using their sizing guide, and it will fit perfetly!
review_body:
I have been wanting to buy a corset/waist trainer for a very long time but haven't found any that I really liked. Once I saw the pictures of the Lttcbro corset I loved it! I bought the black one so it can match many items in my wardrobe. The quality is amazing, the outside is a leather material and the inside is so soft and luxurious feeling. I did read the reviews before I bought it and I read in quite a few reviews that they suggest ordering 2 sizes up. I did end up ordering 2 sizes up and it fits perfectly! When I'm wearing the corset its very comfortable feeling, doesn't dig in to my body anywhere and I forgot I was even wearing it. I am hoping to buy more in a few different colors next time.
I received this item for a discount in exchange for my 100% complete and honest opinion.

product_title: Lttcbro Women's Latex Waist Cincher Spanx Shapewear Waist Trainers
review_body:
This is a review on the Lttcbro Women's Latex Waist Training Corset Steel Boned Underbuster Rubber Cincher

I was pleasantly shocked that the Waist Training Corset actually fit me. I’m a large lady so I thought it wouldn’t. I did have to order two sizes up since it does have a smaller sizing sheet.

I loved that it was rubber with a softer material on the inside for our comfort. I felt like an old Victorian lady wearing a girdle but in a sexy way. I love the fact that it comes in a lot of colors. I plan on order another one…maybe the purple one.

I received this product at a discount for my honest unbiased review. This is 100% my thoughts.

product_title: Lttcbro Women's Latex Waist Cincher Spanx Shapewear Waist Trainers
review_body:
I received this for free in exchange for my honest review.

This runs really small. Make sure you check and double check on what size to get. You want it to be able to close.

This is really well made. It is not cheap or chinsey like other waist trainers I have seen. The clasps are very strong and sturdy. You don't have to worry about breaking it because it would be impossible to break.

Can you breathe in it? Not really, but you will get used to it. This is also not a permanent solution. You would still want to diet and exercise.

Again, check the size. If you are not sure, go up a size.

product_title: Lttcbro Women's Latex Waist Cincher Spanx Shapewear Waist Trainers
review_body:
This is a beautiful, well-made training corset. I have used other shapewear before, and the quality was lacking. I really like wearing this corset. I can wear it conspicuously under my regular clothing. The corset stays in place and doesn't bunch. It is easy to put on and is comfortable to wear all day. The corset can be adjusted to 3 different sizes, similar to a bra. 16 clasps hold the corset in place and the ribbing offers support and a feminine contour. The corset fit a little small, so I suggest ordering one size up.

I received this product at a discount for my honest and unbiased review.

product_title: Lttcbro Women's Latex Waist Cincher Spanx Shapewear Waist Trainers
review_headline: and because I hate ordering offline and the item doesn't fit
review_body: Lttcbro Women's Latex Waist Training Corset Steel Boned Underbust Rubber Cincher is everything I imagined! I have seen the latest craze of the waist trainers, and to be honest I was quite intrigued. After looking around at the prices I was completely turned off. I couldn't fathom spending as much money as some of these companies wanted (upwards of $150). I wanted a waist trainer because I still carry around baby weight and when I got on birth control after my little I started gaining even more and haven't been able to lose it. I was nervous ordering because I haven't measured myself due to not really liking how I look, and because I hate ordering offline and the item doesn't fit. But I know if I really want results I have to just face it. I wear a size 14/16 US pants and L/XL shirts. I ordered a size 4X because of the measurements provided. I put the cincher on and was amazed at how smooth my stomach looked under my shirts and how easy it was to button my pants. Immediately there was no bulge or muffin top.  I am able to secure the clamps on the first row. The trainer is very comfortable, the cotton on the inside is very soft. I don't feel as though I am about to burst at the seems but it's tight enough to where I feel it's going to work. It's very well made and makes me excited about this waist training journey I'm about to take.  I received this awesome Latex Waist Training Corset Steel Boned Underbust Rubber Cincher from Lttcbro at a discounted price in exchange for my honest review.

product_title: Lttcbro Women's Latex Waist Cincher Spanx Shapewear Waist Trainers
review_body:
I am a woman that loves wearing corsets and was quite excited to receive this one...upon opening my package, it was nice to see that it came in a zippered pouch that you could definitely reuse if you wanted to pack your corset to take on a trip with you. The corset is also very well made with metal hook eye closures, which for me speaks volumes, it means that the manufacturer did not cut any corners in the construction of this garment. It was easy enough for me to hook on by myself, but if you have the chance to have someone help you to put it on, you could get it on much faster. After having it on and wearing it for a bit I found that this corset was very comfortable as well and wore well over my Cami and under my clothing. When ordering this corset, please be sure to pay close attention to the sizing chart, because if you do not you may find that the corset will be two sizes too small. All in all though, I am very pleased with this purchase and would not hesitate to try other garments from this company as well.

*Disclaimer: I received this item at a reduced rate in exchange for my honest and unbiased opinion.

review_body:
It's true that it's comfortable, constructed well, and durable. If you are of average height and torso, by all means, this is an excellent choice. But damn it all - it does not fit petites! I am 5'1", and even when pulled to the very end of my hips, the top of the corset will dig into my chest. Very uncomfortable. I really love everything else about it, but it is simply too long. If you're on the short side, you'll have to look elsewhere.

If you're the maker of this corset, PLEASE consider making a 'short' version. It would have been perfect if it was just 3-4 inches shorter.

review_body: These were a very pleasant surprise. product_title: VIRGIN ONLY Women's Slim Bootcut Jeans ( Medium Dark Wash, Size 31)
review_headline: These jeans are made of such nice quality material
review_body: I anticipated these jeans being a bit small since most of the clothes I order are, and I'm typically a size 28, but I bought a 30 and they fit me perfectly.  These jeans are made of such nice quality material.  There are no loose strings hanging off anywhere and the material is super thick, but stretches nicely.  There is also a satin material lining the edges of the pockets.  The back pockets as you can see in my pictures have nice rhinestone designs and gold stitching.  These are very nice quality jeans that should last a long time.  Just order a size or 2 bigger than you need.  I wore these out the other day and I got a lot of compliments on them.  I also own another pair of jeans from this same company that I also liked and I love those too, they are the same great quality as the first.  I will definitely be purchasing from them again.  Their prices are fair, and it's definitely a great quality item.  I'm definitely happy with my purchase and highly recommend trying these jeans.  I did receive mine at a discount in exchange for my honest opinion.  I did purchase the second pair on my own with no discount simply because I loved these jeans.

product_title: Basico Women's Printed Leggings Small to 2XL SIZE
review_body:
They're a great fit for my body type (curvy). Love how they look. Love how comfortable and light weight they are, and that they seem more durable than your average legging. I wore a pair of leggings one time, and they literally ripped holes in the butt, and not at the seams, but the material was that cheap! I can tell that won't happen with these.

Also, all those reviews saying to buy them sizes up.... Whaaat?! I wouldn't suggest that. I don't think they run small at all. I recommend buying your regular size or they will probably be too big. I bought a pair at my regular size, and then a pair a size up, the bigger ones are too big for me, but my regular size is great fit.. hugs the body as leggings are meant to. You don't want leggings drooping. But, we all have different body types, so everyone may have a different experience with this. Still, I recommend buying your original size first to see how that goes. :)

review_headline: Color shown is a little more off than it should be, but the fit is fantastic!
review_body: The color when it arrived was definitely warmer than is pictured. It's more of an OLIVE than the green olive as shown. Under warm light it looks closer to brown (especially the solid parts) and under cool light it is a warm olive green, which is the only reason I deducted a star. I know that colors can vary, but I felt that this variation deviated a little TOO much from the picture for my taste. But oh can I tell you about the fit?! THE FIT!! I'm a 6' tall girl with long limbs, and I can never find sleeves that go all the way to my wrist and these do and comfortably too! And the design lay perfectly, with the tie dye pattern starting exactly at mid-point on the bustline. Even though I have hips, the handkerchief hem still drapes well and delivers a very satisfying swish, and the waist nipped in perfectly. I wish I could have rated it "Fit better than expected"

review_body:
I gave this 2 stars instead of 1 because the bottom fit.
The top was REALLY small, not true to the measurements, and very barely stretched.
The material of the bottoms almost feels like a really old swimsuit, when they start getting hard.
If you are all around small, I would assume this suit will fit you beautifully and you'll look awesome. If not, pass on it. There are plenty of cute swimsuits that will fit well that you'll look super hot in.
For instance, that black swimsuit in the second picture is sold by tons of sellers at larger sizes and it fit really well. Just make sure to check the measurements and don't hesitate to size up!

product_title: NYDJ Women's Janette Seamed Dress
review_body: I searched for hours at Nordstrom for a professional dress to wear to work-- I'm a physician, so classic conservative with maybe a pinch of flair was my ideal dress type. Once I put this on, I felt amazing and looked great! The built in shape wear really helps. I mean REALLY helps. The lower portion shapewear is a little snug at the bottom so it hugs your thighs just a bit-- not uncomfortable at all, but you won't be able to take very large steps. Not that you would want to anyway while wearing this dress, as that's not too lady like and you CERTAINLY feel like a refined woman strutting down the street. Honestly, I loved it so much that I bought more NYDJ dresses with built in shapewear the next day. VERY pleased.

product_title: Just Love Women's Scrub Sets/Six Pocket Medical Scrubs (V-Neck w/Cargo Pant)
review_body:
These scrubs are soft and comfortable. The fabric is lightweight and breathable yet not flimsy. I ordered the black and they were good quality, not noticeably fading after being washed. The top is a v-neck, short sleeves with three pockets to hold everything you need. The pants are roomy and comfy, also with three pockets and an accommodating stretch waistband. These are perfect for doing serious work while still keeping you looking professional. These would be great for anyone in the healthcare profession or even for just working around the house.

I have received free products to help facilitate my review but all opinions are my own.

product_title: Just Love Women's Scrub Sets/Six Pocket Medical Scrubs (V-Neck w/Cargo Pant)
review_headline: Great for the Price!!! Highly encourage any doubters to give them a try!
review_body:
These scrubs are really comfortable, and fit well. I was really hesitant, because of the price, but now that I know, I will be ordering more! I especially love that they have the breast pocket, for my phone, which most women's scrubs don't offer! And the waist tie is not one of those like the unisexes that gets all knotted/stuck once you tie! It's an elastic waistband with the tie. The length is a little long for my petite bottom half (I am a true petite and usually purchase the petite bottoms) but they almost taper a little (without becoming a skinny leg bottom) so they kind of bunch up and stay at ankle and don't get caught below my shoe bottom. The only downside is that the fabric is a little thin, perhaps not the best quality fabric, but a) I wear these to work, not out to dinner and b) at $15.00 a pair they are nearly disposable. And I purchased black, so no see through pantilines to worry about.
I could not be any happier with the purchase.

product_title: Just Love Women's Scrub Sets/Six Pocket Medical Scrubs (V-Neck w/Cargo Pant)
review_body:
Cute set of scrubs! I ordered these for my best friend because she works in the medical field. I ordered her a size medium in the black, and they fit her perfectly. There's a nice amount of space so she can move around freely throughout the day without any discomfort, and the material is nice enough quality to not cause her any irritation or chafing.

They have a VERY nice, professional look to them, so they were perfect for her to wear to work. They are very strict at her hospital with their black uniform scrubs, and these fit right in. I am very pleased with the quality, and my friend was very happy to have a new set. I would definitely buy again. (I received this product for free in exchange for an honest and unbiased review.)

review_headline: Comfy, flattering fit for a great price
review_body: These scrubs are soft and durable. Very comfy, fit very well. I don't feel like I am swimming in them like I do some scrubs, they have a flattering fit. I received these for an honest review in black, and I am going to purchase the other colors now! Great buy for a nice set!

product_title: Just Love Women's Scrub Sets / Six Pocket Medical Scrubs (V-Neck w/ Cargo Pant)
review_body:
Nowhere, I repeat NOWHERE will you ever find a brand new set of scrubs at this price point. Especially not a set that is decent quality. Until now, that is. I just have to say, WOW! I am so impressed with everything about this set of black XL scrubs by Just Love. I Just Love these scrubs!

The fabric is 55% cotton and 45% polyester that is machine washable. I tried these scrubs on before washing and they fit as expected. After washing and drying they still fit as expected so shrinking was minimal, if any. The fabric is very breathable and not hot at all which is important when you are running around on a 12 hour shift. It is also easy to move around in this fabric, very comfortable.

Between the scrub top and scrub bottom there is a total of 6 pockets which is fantastic for all of my tape, scissors, gauze, alcohol pads, meds etc. I am really liking this scrub set and have already received compliments on it from other people at work.

These scrubs are great for anyone in the health care, dental, or veterinary field. However, this scrub set is comfortable enough for anyone to use to lounge or work around the house in.

product_title: stripsky Women's Floral Print Vintage High Waisted Bikini Bow Swimsuits Swimwear (L)
review_headline: Very cute print but the top and bottom sizes didn't match up on my frame. They sent a smaller top.
review_body: *second edit* The company was kind enough to send me a medium top when I wanted to return it, it fit better with my bust, but I'm still not a huge fan of the way the bottom fits. I took the top with me on my vacation and it was perfect to wear under my jumper, swim cover and instead of a bra. It's extremely comfortable and stays up well in the right size even without the ties. Recommendation: have that figure or  contact them first for the right sizing? I'm very pleased with the top, and still love the print of the bottoms.  *edit* It's more like a 3.5 I like it but I can't wear it because of my figure. It's okay, for someone else.  The quality of the fabric is good and I really love the print for the bottoms. But the style just isn't for me. As for fit, the top was too big and the bottoms, made me look funny - but I've come to realize the style isn't for me. I folded the top of the bottoms under and made the waistline lower, then they were a-ma-zing. But there was nothing I could do to fix the bandeau. ------  Here are the measurements for a large according to the manufacturer***: L: Bust 35"-38", Waist 28"-30", Hip 37"-40" And here are my measurements: Bust 35/36B (problematic)" Natural Waist 30" Hip 37" 5"5" 134lbs  I'm pretty sure now that the waist mentioned in the measurements is the waistband of the bottoms... so that's something to take into account when ordering.  -------  The bandeau on the other hand was harder for me to judge. It didn't sit right on my smaller bust, it was just tooo big. The loops for the tie hooks were very small and pulled awkwardly on the bandeau, even though they are hidden behind the bow points. Those strings are very thin and are not meant for support. Unfortunately the bow didn't look right on me without them, so I grabbed the single hook strap from another bandeau I owned and attached to this one. It held better, but still pulled oddly on the loops. The top is lightly padded and adjusted right the bow does look pretty, but without an ample chest (see my measurements below) it's hard to do the top justice or determine how it would actually look.  The quality of the bottoms is great you'd never think you paid so little for them, even if I dislike the style, a lot. The bottoms have a very almost vintage fit. The leg holes are tight, but not uncomfortable (my leg-hole opening is 22"). It's sort of reassuring knowing that I'd never be adjusting swimsuit in while glancing around slyly or embarrassed. The waistband sits in a odd location on me and it doesn't flatter my stomach at all. It's too high yet too low to be flattering on me with my slightly squarish rounding stomach. Not quite a high waisted bikini not quite a mere modest bikini, the shortened distance (or lengthened distance compared to other high waisted bikinis) of skin only served only to make my chest smaller and my stomach, hips and butt bigger. Not that I couldn't use a bigger butt, but I could do without the rest.  Conclusion: Love the pattern. Hate the style. The top runs on the large end of the manufacture measurements. The bottoms run true to size.  Recommended for those with large busts.

product_title: Von-Röutte Ultra Slim Leather Wallet for Men - Business Card Holder Leather with Thin Card Sleeve Wallet / Premium Design Money Bill Wallet and Slim Credit Card Wallet [4 Inches only]
review_headline: Awesome, slim leather wallet that holds a lot
review_body: I've been searching for the perfect wallet for a while -- my requirements were pretty simple. If it holds all of my cards, is easily pocketable and most importantly SLIM, I'm good. I don't carry a lot of cash so a card sleeve wallet was on my radar. Found this one on a recommendation and it was PERFECT for my needs. I only have eight cards including my driver's license, and this little wallet fit everything like a champ. The construction on it was solid and I like the real leather details and the thatched cloth trim on it. Looks vaguely vintage but still functional.

product_title: Guardians Star Cosplay Lord Mask Light Up Lifesize PVC Helmet Adults
review_headline: Great mask that looks fantastic, but not without a few caveats.
review_body: Looks great.  Mine did not come flattened in the box as other reviewers have stated, and unlike the description states, the lenses and lighting were pre installed for me.  Be warned that batteries are not included.  The LED lights require 2 button cell batteries (CR2026, if I remember correctly).  Vision in the mask is decent provided you leave the lights turned off.  With the lights on, it is difficult to see.  Great mask overall!  I recommend it for any Starlord cosplayer.

product_title: Guardians Star Cosplay Lord Mask Light Up Lifesize PVC Helmet Adults
review_body:
The Mask is great quality but it fits a little tight and gets a bit stuffy. There is a Large version of it which has a bit more space but the eyes are a bit further apart.

Regular mask - 22-24 head / eyes are 1.5 inches apart corner to corner.

Large mask - 24-26 head / eyes are 2.5 inches apart corner to corner.

product_title: Guardians Star Cosplay Lord Mask Light Up Lifesize PVC Helmet Adults
review_headline: The paintjob was done better than I expected
review_body: Bought the V5 Painted version of the helmet. It came squished as the seller said it would. I put a blanket in it for 10 minutes and that issue was fixed. The paintjob was done better than I expected. Im assuming the older cheaper versions aren't done as good. The helmet fits perfect, although its not painful on the head, im adding some extra padding for comfort. The lenses in this version are pre inserted and the LED's are already inside (Just add 2 of those large flat batteries). The LED's have a flashing mode and a steady red light up mode that looks great. The lenses are clear enough to easily see out, but when its lit up red it becomes difficult to see. A suggestion is to get blue tinted transparent paper that can cancel out the red. I actually love the mask. Its a bit pricey at around 85$, but its accurate and fits a cosplay well.

product_title: Guardians Star Cosplay Lord Mask Light Up Lifesize PVC Helmet Adults
review_body: very realistic, but wtf with the more expensive diy version? wake up xcoser

product_title: Guardians Star Cosplay Lord Mask Light Up Lifesize PVC Helmet Adults
review_headline: Looks good in pictures, bad in real life.
review_body:
This mask is supposed to be for heads 24 inch round. My head is exactly 24 inch round. I have to wiggle the helmet on. And can't stay in it a long time. It should be larger. Especially since it's for adults.

There is a GIANT foam pad with two holes in it for the front of the mask, which is taking up space. Presumably to keep the lenses away from your eyes, but they should have set the lenses further out into the eye-holes and used less padding. When I removed the mask the padding and lenses detached and came out.

The lenses were crooked. The left lens grid was oriented up/down left/right, the right lens grid was diagonal. The lenses also move freely in and out within the eye-holes.

The ribbed area on the back of the helmet wasn't even painted. Should be the same "Gold" color as the front of the mask.

There was sticky glue all over the inside.

The mask was taco'd in half and folded to fit it into the box. So it's out of shape.

Overall I cannot recommend this product. It simply is not any good. They are not taking any care to assemble or paint these correctly.

product_title: Apt.9 Womens Junior 100% Cotton Capri Cropped Cargo Shorts Work Pants Trouser
review_headline: I'm a 12/14 and these fit nicely. However
review_body: These cargo capri's fit as expected in the waist and butt area.  The waist is a little low for my tastes and requires a belt but that's not unusual with a lot of capris.  I'm a 12/14 and these fit nicely.  However, they were longer than expected.  If you don't roll them up, they are a short pant.  If you roll them up to where the button is, they are just a shorter pant.  They are the longest capri's I've ever had.  You can roll them up past the button but for them to stay, you have to iron/starch the crease.  Overall, they look nice and they are comfortable.  I ordered the grey hoping that the grey they sent would be darken than the khaki color shown for the grey option.  It was BY A LOT.  It's definitely a dark, dark grey.  Almost a dark blue/grey.  This was a pleasant surprise for me, but might not be what others want.  There is no label indicating it's Apt. 9, but considering the price and the quality, I would say if it's not, it's just like an Apt. 9 product. While the capri's aren't the highest quality and probably won't last long if you are rough on your clothes, they are what I expected for the price they are and they will do fine for camping trips and lake days.  I'm pleased with the purchase.

If you are buying this from Promotion&Beyond, don't expect the same color font that you order. The first I received was orange, very far from the advertised color. After I contacted the seller they said they would send me the correct coloring, and the coloring was still off. It was red, but just red, not this dark/maroon showed.

Although the seller was very understanding and sent me the second shirt AND refunded my money after I told them it still wasn't correct, they should be able to deliver what they advertise. If you just want the funny saying and don't care much about color, go for it! It's cheap and you'll get a few chuckles when you wear it.

product_title: Pull-on Pencil Skirt, Women Stretchy Printed Styles for Business Office Wear
review_body:
I got the opportunity to purchase this skirt at a reduced rate in exchange for my honest and unbiased opinion. I love to wear skirts, but sometimes it is difficult to find one that is stylish and comfortable. This pencil skirt is as comfortable as sweatpants, but gives off the appearance of an expensive faddish skirt. The sizes run very standard and match the sizing chart provided. The skirt fits well at the waist, hugs the hips and falls narrowly down to mid-knee or lower depending on your height.

The material feels amazing and makes the colors look vibrant. Since there is no zipper, just an elastic waist band you do not have to worry about hiding the zipper or ensuring that the zipper is done all the way to the top. Some skirts prevent you from being able to have the full range of motion with your legs, but not this one. Even when you get up and down, the skirt does not need to be readjusted a lot. This skirt can be worn to a formal function or just for fun for a night out with the girls.

product_title: Pull-on Pencil Skirt, Women Stretchy Printed Styles for Business Office Wear
review_body: The skirt is really cute.  I love the length of it. I did find the size runs on the smaller side. It is nice the fabric is strechy. But its strechy enough that it does not slide up as you walk. I have experienced with some stretch skirts seem to bunch up and become shorter when you are walking. This skirt does not do that. The skirt is comfortable. I like that it is wrinkle resisitance. It makes it so easy when getting ready for work in the morning. I do not have to stop and iron. I would recommend the skirt but make sure you do order it one size larger. This is the reason why I rated it a 4 start I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest review.

It hugs the hips and falls to just below the knees. It is perfect for the office or for a night out with my husband. It can even be worn when I am with my kids as it is long enough to allow me to run and bend. The material is nice and soft, and is perfect for the hot California weather this summer. There is no zipper, which I love because I don't have to try to fight to zip up in the back, and it means the skirt doesn't have a defined front or back. I received this skirt at a discount in exchange for my honest review.

product_title: Vertical Sport Men's Active Basic Jogger Athletic Fit Fleece Sweat Pants
review_headline: I haven't yet tried them on an extended hike, but so far these pants have performed fairly well for exercise and short hikes
review_body:
This pair of men's jogging JG2 sweatpants is sold by Vertical Sport and fulfilled by Amazon. (I could not find a website for Vertical Sport.) I received them from Amazon as part of a multi-item shipment. They were packed in a clear plastic bag. The pants are designed with two side pockets and a single open back pocket (i.e., no closure flap). They were made in China out of 100% polyester with the exception of the two side pockets (not the back pocket) which are 96% polyester and 4% spandex to allow stretching. Even though the material is advertised as fleece, it is actually "polar fleece", in which synthetic polyester fibers are woven into a soft nap. There is no organic material or wool in the pants. The material has a somewhat slick, soft feel to it. The 2 1/2" wide elastic waistband can be cinched with a front tying drawstring and the ankle cuffs are 2" wide elastic bands. It has this odd fake men's fly flap sewn into the front of the crotch...kinda strange...anyway, there is no zipper or opening, just a flap design. The pants seem to be sized about right.

On almost all outdoors forums the consensus seems to be that cotton and denim are bad choices for hiking and camping ("cotton is rotten") because they take time to dry out while polyester is good because it drys quickly if you get wet (e.g., you get rained on or have to wade a stream, etc.). I do not necessarily agree with this since I have hiked and camped quite a bit wearing denim jeans and cotton t-shirts with no problems. In my experience, 100% polyester material usually has breathability and wicking problems in which limited moisture wicking traps perspiration between my skin and the material. It can feel very uncomfortable over a long hike or extended work on a hot day. Surprisingly, I found the JG2's to be fairly tolerable in that respect. Even though they don't have the comfort level of cotton, the pants seem to have a limited level of breathability. I really liked the design of the elastic ankle cuffs that your can tuck into your hiking boots or that keep your pants clear of your shoes when jogging. (Most hiking pants have open cuffs that go over the tops of your boots.) Although I haven't yet had the opportunity to try them on an extended hike, so far these pants have performed fairly well for exercise and short hikes. As for the material, you may want to also try a cotton/polyester blend that supports some kind of wicking technology. I have found blended material to be more comfortable than 100% polyester clothing.

product_title: I Love Support My Gay Son Parent of Gay Child Young Mens T-Shirt 2XL Turq
review_headline: Great product, but check with your son first
review_body:
This shirt has a great trim fit, and the soft cotton still feels good even after a few washes. Unfortunately, my son got really upset with me for wearing it.

During high school my son watched a lot of shows on the E! Television network. He even DVR'd an entire season of Kourtney and Kim Take Miami.

I purchased the shirt to wear at my son's high school graduation party. I thought I would be the most supportive father in the world by wearing it as I operated the grill.

Billy's friends started arriving to the party, and some of them started laughing at my shirt. I expected this, but I told them that I support Billy with the decisions he makes.

Billy finally came outside to greet everyone. As he made his way over to the grill, I handed him a polish sausage and he threw it on the ground and started screaming at me.

I then realized Billy had not come out yet. It gets worse. Billy told me that he was not gay at all. I asked him about all of those E television shows and he said it was his new girlfriend Eliza who DVR'd them.

It turns out I did not know Billy as well as I thought I did. I now try to only wear this shirt for yard work and volunteering at PTA events.

I am a size 3-5 depending on the brand(I got a size Medium). I have a tiny waist, but bigger hips because of my BJJ style. It is very very hard to find Grappling gear that fits me because of my curvy shape(either waist is too big or my hips are about to bust the seams), but these fit awesome. Not to mention they look very cool and everyone knows when I step on the mat. ;-) I love the bright colors and custom feel!

review_body:
Honestly, I just got it for the sake of Price. But was completely surprised with such an amazing response from my WIFE, moreover many folks in my pool can't stop tuning their heads to have a glimpse ;) I swim almost 4-5 days a week and was tired of the branded swim briefs (they loose the shine due to chlorine and the snug too) and hence started looking for the cheaper ones. This is really a great swim brief! Fits perfect and the price is surely a deal breaker! Swimming in a co-ed swim pool, this gives me the just needed decent look ;) The good thing is, it fits perfect from the rear so when you are getting out of the pool, you don't have to worry about covering your rear.

This is my general caring tip:Take a minute or two after you swim and rinse the pant with cold water. ASA you get back home, use some fabric detergent and soak the pant for around 15 minutes and then wash it with cold water, and set it for drying. Don't wash it in washing machine. And if you have an alternate pair, try using this every other day. This way, it drys and at the same time lasts long.

The wait time is worth waiting, both for the price and the quality!

review_body:
This is a beautiful romper and the quality is far better than I imagined for the low price they're asking for it. Did it fit me? No. Not quite. So why am I leaving a five star review? Because the romper IS a five star romper! It is not helpful to anyone to leave a one star review when an item does not fit you because you did not do your research before buying. Reviews are not meant to be a place for you to air your grievances. You can email the seller for that if you must. When you buy clothing from Amazon and the price is this low, that means it is most likely Asian sizing and you need to read reviews to know how many sizes to go up. It is your own responsibility to understand how things fit and to not bring down a seller's reviews when you receive and item and find it's is smaller because it's Asian sizing.

This is a genuine review of the product so that other buyers can make an informed decision. I am 5'6" and a curvy 160lbs with a small waist and wider hips and shoulders. This romper in an XL did fit me but it was just a bit snug and the lovely fabric does not have a lot of stretch to it so it would not have held up well in the seams when I sat down. It would work fine at this weight for someone with smaller hips and booty than I've got. I wear a junior's size 13 jeans so if you wear an 11 or less, this will be fine on you.

On these rompers that have the adjustable straps, you can wear a matching lacy bra cami under it with the straps let out if you are long waisted just so you don't have to wear a strapless bra or worry about showing more than you want to.

It is a gorgeous romper and long enough to cover your upper thigh so you don't have to worry about dropping your keys. If you have a slimmer and more athletic build, this will look wonderful on you. If you are over 155 and curvy, the largest size will still be a bit small for you.

product_title: TWINTH Womens Short Sleeve V-neck Handkerchief Hem Loose Fit Long Tunic Top with Plus Size
review_headline: Great product! Beautiful, comfortable and flattering.
review_body:
First of all, I ordered this tunic because I knew I'd like it, the mix of rayon/spandex is my favorite fabric of all time. It's lightweight but not see through (unless you stretch it out to max capacity) soft, but durable. Stretchy, but doesn't lose it's shape. Slowly my wardrobe is switching to consist almost solely of this fabric.

I thought this product was going to come from china, but it actually got to my house in two days! I was so surprised!
The sizing chart suggested I get a 4xl (5'3, 230) but since I'm really familiar with this fabric, and I knew it was so stretchy (I normally get an xl or 1x) I opted for a bit smaller than suggested. I ordered a 3x "to be safe" because, again, I thought it was from China, where the sizes are much smaller.

When it arrived, I tried it on and realized that it was a big bigger than I expected based on the chart. This depends on how you want to wear it though. I was planning on wearing it around the house with some leggings, so I wanted it to be fitted like the other shirts I have. If you prefer it to be a little big and more flowy, then you can follow the sizing chart, or chose one size smaller. If you've ever had a shirt like this before, then feel free to follow whatever size you normally wear. For me this is safely 1 size too big for me to be comfortable, loose and flattering, and 2 sizes too big for my preference.

However, it's still really comfortable! Since I'll be wearing it at home I'll just belt it at the waist.

Last notes: The color was EXACTLY as expected, bright kelly green. The angles of the bottom seam are asymmetrical, meaning that the points don't match up in exactly the middle. They mirror each other, but they're more on one side than the other. I don't think that's a mistake, just the style of the shirt.

Let me know if you have any questions for me!

*I received this shirt at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review*But nobody tells me what to do or say and I'd tell you if it was crap, I promise.

review_body:
I am a big fan of tunics. This one is adorable. Some shirts that have been labelled as tunics are the same length as my regular shirts. That is not the way I like my tunics. I have a few Thanth shirts and they are my go to shirts. They are easy to dress up and down and are very comfortable. I love that they are a bit longer as I love to wear leggings and skin tight yoga pants so this covers my butt so the outfit overall becomes a bit more presentable. This shirt fits very true to size and there are not any features that may make me think otherwise, like a baggy style, etc. Putting on some pearl jewelry with some nice flats and a blazer can really dress up a simple top like this and I am able to wear it to work and look professional and fashionable yet be extremely comfy at the same time. The only complaint, as noted in the video, was that when I got splashes of water on the shirt the spots never faded so be mindful when wearing.

Tips for making your cheap clothing last longer:
1. Do not over wear.
2. Do not over wash.
3. Hand wash, or wash on a delicate cycle. If your washer doesn't have a delicate cycle, just do a short/cold cycle.
4. Air dry, or use a no/low heat cycle in the dryer. But the best option would be to air dry if you are able.

product_title: Tidetell Halter 50s Retro One Piece Bathing Suit Swimsuit Swimwear
review_body: I LOVED this suit, quality was as expected for the price...the only problem I had was the length. There weren't any other reviews from tall ladies, so I thought I'd add one. I'm 5'9", bra size 36 C/D, around 150 lb and the suit wasn't long enough. I ordered an XL (supposed to be size 8-10). I often have this problem with one-pieces, so I wasn't surprised, but disappointed none-the-less! I loved the underwire and molded cups (the bra size was a good fit for C/D), great for support, but the length probably won't work for anyone over 5'6" or so, unless you have a short torso. I also found the "connected tankini" style a little bit strange...I would have preferred it to be just a straight one-piece.
